<HTML>
<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
  <TITLE>Why HVDC? - Lower Losses</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" ">
<H2>
  Lower losses
</H2>
<H4>
  An optimized HVDC transmission line has lower losses than AC lines for the
  same power capacity. The losses in the converter stations have of course
  to be added, but since they are only about 0.6 % of the transmitted power
  in each station, the total HVDC transmission losses come out lower than the
  AC losses in practically all cases.
</H4>
<H4>
  HVDC cables also have lower losses than AC cables.
</H4>
<H4>
  The diagram below shows a comparison of the losses for overhead line
  transmissions of 1200 MW with AC and HVDC.
</H4>
<P>
<CENTER>
  <IMG SRC="l35349.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
</CENTER>
<P>
  <HR>
