<HTML>
<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
  <TITLE>HVDC Technology - Control System</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" ">
<H2>
  Control system
</H2>
<P>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="2">
  <TR>
    <TD>
      <IMG SRC="board.jpg" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
    </TD>
    <TD>
      <H4>
	The control system is the brain in an HVDC transmission system. A modern
	HVDC station is equipped with a well integrated microprocessor based control
	and protection system. The MACH&reg; system developed by ABB Power Systems
	is fully digital. All functions for control, supervision and protection of
	the stations are implemented in software running in a family of microprocessor
	circuit boards.
      </H4>
    </TD>
  </TR>
</TABLE>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="2">
  <TR>
    <TD>
      <IMG SRC="hidraw.jpg" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
    </TD>
    <TD>
      <H4>
	Most application software for the MACH&reg; system is produced using a fully
	graphical code generator called HiDraw&reg;. This significantly reduces the
	time to produce the code needed for a new application and it improves the
	quality of the documentation considerably.
	<P>
	By means of a fully symbolic graphical debugger HiBug&reg;, on-line debugging
	of the software is greatly facilitated.
      </H4>
    </TD>
  </TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="2">
  <TR>
    <TD>
      <IMG SRC="samprov.jpg" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
      <P>
      <I>Factory System Test of HVDC control equipment.</I>
    </TD>
    <TD>
      <H4>
	The control equipment for each HVDC project built by ABB is checked out
	extensively before delivery by connecting it to an analog HVDC simulator
	representing the high-voltage circuits of the HVDC transmission and the AC
	networks. The time needed for commissioning in the field can thereby be much
	reduced.
      </H4>
    </TD>
  </TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
<P>
  <HR>
