<HTML>
<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
  <TITLE>Capacitor Commutated Converters, CCC</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">
<P>
<A NAME="DDE_LINK2"><IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif"
    alt=""> <IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" "> <BASEFONT size=3></BASEFONT>
<H2>
  Capacitor Commutated Converters, CCC
</H2>
<P>
<CENTER>
  <IMG SRC="sk6548.gif">
</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>
  <I>The CCC main circuit configuration</I>
</CENTER>
<H4>
  In ABB's HVDC 2000 concept, commutation capacitors are connected between
  the valve bridge and the converter transformers. This location has been found
  to be advantageous for several reasons. The capacitor stresses are much lower
  in this position than outside the converter transformer, as both the operating
  current and overcurrents are controlled by the valve bridge. The capacitor
  overvoltage protection can thus be handled by a varistor of reasonable size.
</H4>
<P>
<TABLE>
  <TR valign=top>
    <TD>
      <H4>
	With a CCC there is no need to switch filter banks or shunt capacitors banks
	in and out to follow the reactive consumption when the active power is changed.
	This is the case for a conventional converter where it is normally necessary
	to subdivide the var supply in several breaker-switched banks.
      </H4>
      <H3>
	Performance improvements
      </H3>
      <UL>
	<LI>
	  <A HREF="l11621.htm">Robust and resistant to disturbances</A>
	<LI>
	  <A HREF="l11622.htm">Dynamic stability improved</A>
	<LI>
	  <A HREF="l11622.htm#Bottom">Reduced load rejection overvoltage</A>
      </UL>
      <P>
      <H3>
	Equipment considerations
      </H3>
      <UL>
	<LI>
	  <A HREF="l11624.htm">The commutation capacitor</A>
	<LI>
	  <A HREF="l11625.htm">Influence on other equipment</A>
      </UL>
      <P>
    </TD>
    <TD>
      <CENTER>
	<IMG SRC="sk6550.gif">
      </CENTER>
      <CENTER>
	<I>The reactive power conditions for a typical conventional converter station
	and for a CCC</I>
      </CENTER>
    </TD>
  </TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
  <HR>
<P>
<CENTER>
  <IMG SRC="abbhand.gif" ALIGN=TOP> | <A HREF="home.htm">ABB Power Systems
  Home Page</A> | <A HREF="http://www.abb.se">ABB Sweden</A> |
</CENTER>
<P>
