<HEAD>

<TITLE>Optical direct current transducer</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">

<P>
<A NAME="DDE_LINK2"><IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A>
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" ">
<H2>Optical direct current transducer</H2>
<P><H4>ABB Power Systems has developed a simple, reliable and very accurate optical direct
current transducer, OCT. The new DC-OCT is already in operation in recent HVDC projects.
The measuring principle is based on a high precision shunt. The electronic A/D converter
on high potential is powered by light sent to the device in a separate fibre.</H4>

<center><IMG SRC="sk6561.gif"></center>
<P align=center><I>Block diagram, OCT</I>

<P><H4>The new DC-OCT meets or exceeds the performance requirements normally prescribed for
direct current transducers. The accuracy is better than 0.5% in the frequency range
from DC up to 7kHz.</H4>

<center><IMG SRC="l36970.jpg"></center>
<P align=center><I>Optical current transducer</I>

<HR>

