<HEAD>

<TITLE>ABB Power Systems-SC System Technology</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">

<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">.
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" "> 
<H4>SC System Technology </H4>

<P>
ABB Power Systems' philosophy is that the series capacitor bank
should be designed to give at least the same degree of reliability
as that of the transmission lines, to permit integration in the
power transmission system without reducing availability.
<P>
Series compensation in a transmission system improves voltage
control and reactive power balance, because the reactive power
generation in series capacitors increases as the transmitted power
increases. In this respect, the series capacitor is a self-regulating
device.<HR>

<P>
<CENTER><B>Benefits of series capacitors in two parallel lines
</B>
<P>
<IMG SRC="sctech01.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></CENTER> 
<P>
The transmission system configuration and the requirements regarding
protective equipment and reinsertion time determine the protective
scheme to be adopted. The time, i.e. the time from when a faulty
line section is disconnected to when the series capacitors are
again in fully operation is often the most essential factor to
be taken into consideration.<HR>

<P>
<A HREF="r29.htm"><IMG SRC="grn_bull.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> Single-gap protective principle </A>
<BR>
<A HREF="r30.htm"><IMG SRC="grn_bull.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> Metal Oxide Varistor (MOV) protective principle</A>
<BR>
<A HREF="r31.htm"><IMG SRC="grn_bull.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> Controllable series capacitor technology</A>
<HR>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="abbhand.gif" ALIGN=TOP> |<A HREF="home.htm">ABB Power Systems Home Page</A>
| <A HREF="http://www.abb.se">ABB Sweden</A> | </CENTER><HR>

<P>
<A HREF="copyrajt.htm">Copyright </A>ABB Power Systems Sweden 1995. <BR>
