<TITLE>ABB Power Systems-SC Mechanical Design</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">

<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">.
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" "> 
<H3>SC Electromechanical Design </H3>

<P>
ABB power Systems' series capacitor banks are designed to provide
maximum safety for personnel, simplify layout and minimize the
need for maintenance. The well-proven design minimizes the required
ground space.
<P>
The capacitors and protective equipment for the high voltage system
are placed on steel platforms, fully insulated to the earth. The
equipment for each phase is located on individual platforms. These
platforms are fenced-in and suitable inspection corridors are
provided.<BR>
Via the inspection corridors, access can be obtained to the operating
device of the by-pass breaker for the purpose of inspection and
performing local operations. The platform mounted equipment is
electrically connected to the platform at one point only, but
is otherwise insulated from it.
<P>
The protective relays required for the series capacitors are normally
installed in a control building.
<P>
<CENTER><B>A typical layout of a 3-phase 500 kV Series Capacitor
bank</B> 
<P>
<IMG SRC="scconn.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> 
<P>
<CENTER><B>A typical layout of one phase of a 500 kV Series Capacitor</B>

