<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>SIMPOW - General Features</TITLE>
<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant 
for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<H3><IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" "> </H3>
<H1><CENTER><B>SIMPOW<BR>
<FONT SIZE=5>General Features</FONT></B>
</H1></CENTER>
<P>
The following list presents a brief description of the 
general features 
and functions contained in SIMPOW.<BR>
For more information click on the indicated search words 
or scroll to the end of the page.<BR>
<P><LH>
<FONT SIZE=3><B>System Features:</B></FONT></LH><BR>
<P>
<UL>
<LI><I>Multiterminal</I> HVDC systems<BR>
<LI>Phasewise controlled SVC for <I>load balancing</I>
<BR>
<LI>Unsymmetrical, <I>nonlinear</I> and timevarying 
load<BR>
<LI><I>Arbitrary </I>number and types of <I>faults</I> 
can be 
applied at any location<BR>
<LI>Unlimited number of nodes
<LI>Contains models for <I>FACTS</I> devices
</UL>
<P><LH>
<FONT SIZE=3><B>User Features:</B></FONT></LH><BR>
<P>
<UL>
<LI>Interactivity<BR>
<LI>Graphical user interface<BR>
<LI>Dynamic Simulation Language, <A HREF="h04.htm#dsl"
>DSL</A>, for
building of user defined control systems and net elements
<BR>
<LI>Single line diagram graphics
</UL>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=4><B>Key Functions</B></FONT><BR>
<UL>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=3><B>Steady-state conditions:</FONT></B><BR>
<LI>Power Flow, <A HREF="h04.htm">Optpow</A><BR>
<LI>Short Circuit, <A HREF="h04.htm#stapow">Stapow</A><BR>
<LI>Harmonics Distortion</UL>
<P>
<UL><B>Electromechanical transients:</B><BR>
<LI>Long Term Dynamics, <A HREF="h04.htm#dymt">Transta
</A><BR>
<LI>Short Term Dynamics, <A HREF="h04.htm#dymt">Transta
</A><BR>
<LI>Machine Transients, <A HREF="h04.htm#dymt">Masta</A>
</UL>
<P>
<UL><HL><B>Electromagnetic transients (models are being 
implemented):
</B></HL>
<LI>Saturation and Resonances<BR>
<LI>Switching Transients<BR>
<LI>Lightning Transients</UL><BR>
<P>
<UL><B><A HREF="h04.htm#linear">Linear Analysis:</A></B>
<LI>Eigenvalues and eigenvector calculations<BR>
<LI>Sensitivity analysis<BR>
<LI>Data scanning, makes it possible to see how an 
eigenvalue moves while modulating one parameter<BR>
<LI>Frequency scanning<BR>
<LI>Damping scanning<BR>
</UL><HR>
<P>
