  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
  <TITLE>ABB Power Systems - HVDC Submarine Cable</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">
<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" ">
<H2>
  HVDC Submarine cable
</H2>
<P>
<TABLE CELLPADDING="2">
  <TR>
    <TD VALIGN="Top">
      <IMG SRC="kabel.jpg" ALIGN="BOTTOM">
    </TD>
    <TD VALIGN="Top">
      <H4>
	This is a sample of the 200 km Fenno-Skan HVDC submarine cable interconnecting
	Sweden and Finland since 1989. It has a capacity of 500 MW and a rated DC
	voltage of 400 kV. ABB High Voltage Cables, Karlskrona, Sweden is the ABB
	company manufacturing DC (and AC) cables.
	<P>
	The cable has a copper conductor and the insulation is made of oil impregnated
	paper. There is a lead alloy sheath outside the insulation. Mechanical protection
	is achieve by steel tape and steel wire armoring.
      </H4>
    </TD>
  </TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
<IMG SRC="seacable.jpg" WIDTH="300" HEIGHT="195">
<P>
<I>Laying of a sea cable.</I>
<P>
<CENTER>
</CENTER>
