<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>CCC - Robust and Resistant to Disturbances</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">

<P>
<A NAME="DDE_LINK2"><IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> 
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" "> 
<H2>Robust and resistant to disturbances</H2>

<H4>The voltage contribution from the commutation capacitors supports
the commutation of current from one valve to the next. This means
that the CCC will continue normal operation even during large
AC voltage disturbances since it is much more robust than the
conventional HVDC converter. Typically, a CCC can tolerate a sudden
15-20% voltage drop without causing a commutation failure.</H4>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="sk6551.gif"></CENTER> 
<P>
<CENTER><I>Remote single phase ground fault on the inverter AC
network</CENTER> </I><HR>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="abbhand.gif" ALIGN=TOP> | <A HREF="home.htm">ABB Power Systems Home Page</A>
| <A HREF="http://www.abb.se">ABB Sweden</A> | </CENTER><HR>

<P>
<A HREF="copyrajt.htm">Copyright </A>ABB Power Systems Sweden
1996 
</BODY>

</HTML>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>WT12-B38-61</DOCNO>
<DOCOLDNO>IA063-000363-B034-126</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://www.abb.se:80/pow/l11622.htm 138.221.250.99 19970112023117 text/html 2257
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Server: Netscape-Communications/1.12
Date: Sunday, 12-Jan-97 09:39:12 GMT
