<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>CCC - Influence on other Equipment</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">

<P>
<A NAME="DDE_LINK2"><IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></A> 
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" "> 
<H2>Influence on other equipment</H2>

<H4>An important influence from the capacitors on other equipment
is the reduction of valve short-circuit current. A capacitor located
between the converter transformer and the valve bridge will build
up a counter-voltage at transient currents, reducing the valve
short-circuit current typically to less than 50% compared to a
conventional circuit.</H4>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG align=center SRC="sk6556.gif"></CENTER> 
<P>
<CENTER><I>Valve shortcircuit current</CENTER> </I><HR>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="abbhand.gif" ALIGN=TOP> | <A HREF="home.htm">ABB Power Systems Home Page</A>
| <A HREF="http://www.abb.se">ABB Sweden</A> | </CENTER><HR>

<P>
<A HREF="copyrajt.htm">Copyright </A>ABB Power Systems Sweden
1996 
</BODY>

