<H3><IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" "> <BR>
</H3>
<H1><CENTER><B>SIMPOW </B>
<FONT SIZE=5>Packages</FONT></H1>
<P>
SIMPOW is currently executable on UNIX-computers.
<BR>
In the near future it will also be available for use on 
Windows
NT.<P><HR>
<P>
<B><U>Standard Utility Package:</B></U>
<P>
- Power Flow, 
<A HREF="h04.htm">Optpow</A><BR>
- Short Circuits, 
<A HREF="h04.htm#stapow">Stapow</A><BR>
- Transient Stability, 
<A HREF="h04.htm#dymt">Transta</A><BR>
- User Modeling Language for Regulators, 
<A HREF="h04.htm#dsl">DSL</A><BR>
<P>
<B><U>Advanced Utility Package:</B></U>
<P>
- Power Flow, 
<A HREF="h04.htm">Optpow</A><BR>
- Short Circuits, 
<A HREF="h04.htm#stapow">Stapow</A><BR>
- Transient Stability, 
<A HREF="h04.htm#dymt">Transta</A><BR>
- User Modeling Language for Regulators, 
<A HREF="h04.htm#dsl">DSL</A> <BR>
- <A href="#lina">Linear Analysis Functions, group A</A>
<P>
<B><U>Advanced Utility and Industrial Applications 
Package:</B></U>
<P>
- Power Flow, 
<A HREF="h04.htm">Optpow</A><BR>
- Short Circuits,
<A HREF="h04.htm#stapow">Stapow</A><BR>
- Transient Stability, 
<A HREF="h04.htm#dymt">Transta</A><BR>
- Machine Transients,
<A HREF="h04.htm#dymt">Masta</A><BR>
- User Modeling Language for Regulators,
<A HREF="h04.htm#dsl">DSL</A><BR>
- <A href="#lina">Linear Analysis Functions, group A</A><BR>
- <A href="#linb">Linear Analysis Functions, group B</A> 
<P>
<B><U>Available Optional Functions:</B></U><P></CENTER>
<P>
<UL><UL><LI>DSL Primary: Access to the facilities in DSL 
for modeling
of primary components.<BR>
<LI>DSL Library 1: Access key to Library 1, i.e. the new 
and extended
HVDC model.<BR>
<LI>DSL Libraries 2, 3 and so on: Access keys to corresponding 
libraries.</UL></UL>
<UL><LH><FONT SIZE=4><HR><P>
<B>Technical Definitions</FONT></B></LH>
<P>
<LI><I><A HREF="h04.htm#dymt">MASTA</A>: Access to the 
library of R, L and C net elements for
instantaneous value models.<BR>
<LI><A HREF="h04.htm#dsl">DSL</A>: Dynamic Simulation 
Language for implementation of user defined
regulators.</I>
</UL>
<UL>
<a name="lina"></a>
<P>
<UL><LH><B>Linear Analysis Functions, group A</B> 
<A HREF="h04.htm#linear">(More about Linear Analysis)
</A>:</LH><BR>
Group A contains among others;
<LI>Calculation of eigenvalues: Basic eigenvalue 
calculations based on the QR-method.<BR>
<LI>Improvement of eigenvalues: Enhanced method for 
calculation of eigenvalues and eigenvectors.<BR>
<LI>Sensitivity: Calculations of sensitivity on 
eigenvalues.<BR>
<LI>Frequency scanning: Facility for frequency scanning.
<BR>
</UL>
<a name="linb"></a>
<P>
<UL><LH><B>Linear Analysis Functions, group B</B> 
<A HREF="h04.htm#linear">(More about Linear Analysis)
</A>:</LH>
<LI>Harmonics: Harmonics distribution calculation.<BR>
</UL></UL>
<P>
