Content-length: 5754
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<!doctype html public "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">
<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>ABB Power Systems-More about CSC Technology</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 1.0Z">
<META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="ABB Power Systems AB">
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="paper.jpg">

<P>
<IMG ALIGN=RIGHT BORDER=0 HEIGHT=30 SRC="abblog5.gif" alt="">
<IMG SRC="powlog1.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM">.
<P>
<IMG width=100% SRC="redline.gif" alt=" "> <BR>
<B>More about Controlled Series Capacitor Technology</B> <HR>

<P>
Controllable series capacitors (CSC) have the possibility to optimize
their degree of compensation over a wide range under various network
conditions, partly or fully by means of thyristor switching, thereby
offering themselves as an active component for power flow control
in networks.<BR>
By adjusting the degree of compensation to the network operating
conditions, control of the level of firm power delivery through
a specific line is possible. A distribution of power flow through
several parallel lines can be achieved to secure the transfer
capability in case of an outage in part of the system, or in order
to ascertain the lowest possible transmission losses.<BR>
In networks interconnected by weak links, active power oscillations
may occur as a result of a disturbance to the system. The thyristor
controlled series capacitor can furthermore be useful as a means
for damping of such power oscillations<HR>

<P>
<B>Mechanically Switched Series Capacitors</B> 
<P>
A straightforward implementation of a controllable series capacitor
is offered by mechanically switched segments. Careful selection
of size for a few segments provides a large variation of the inserted
capacitive reactance with adequate resolution.<BR>
The obvious attributes of the MSSC are freedom from harmonic generation
in sustained operation and negligible conduction losses. The typical
speed of response is 50-100 ms from command to execution of by-pass
or insertion of a segment. The frequency of operation is limited
by the maintenance interval of the mechanical breaker.
<P>
<IMG SRC="sctech05.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> 
<P>
The characteristics of an MSSC are:
<UL>
<LI><B>General design as for fixed series capacitor installations</B>

<LI><B>Adequate for steady state control of power flow</B> 
<LI><B>Adequate for limited number of daily adjustments of compensation
degree</B> 
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
<B>Thyristor Switched Series Capacitor</B> 
<P>
Thyristor switched series capacitor TSSC is an extension of the
MSSC principle where the mechanical switching is replaced by power
thyristors. The thyristors are made fully conducting or fully
blocking for any number of half-cycles as desired.<BR>
The inserted reactance response follows the command within one
half-cycle of the main frequency. Sequences of reactance changes
can be performed within any period of time. Further, unlimited
number of operations can be performed without any need for maintenance.
No sustained harmonics are generated due to the switching mode
operation of the thyristors.
<P>
<IMG SRC="sctech06.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> 
<P>
The characteristics of a TSSC are:
<UL>
<LI><B>General design as for fixed series capacitor installations</B>

<LI><B>Simple control system without any requirements on advanced
sensors in the main HV circuit</B> 
<LI><B>The integrated thyristor scheme in the capacitor overvoltage
protection reduce the energy rating of the metal oxide varistors</B>

<LI><B>Unrestricted number of operations and sequences</B> 
<LI><B>Adequate for frequent adjustment of compensation degree
for loadability control and damping of electromechanical oscillations.</B>

</UL>
<HR>

<P>
<B>Thyristor Controlled Series Capacitor</B> 
<P>
The capacitor bank is provided with a parallel thyristor controlled
inductor that circulates current pulses which add in phase with
the line current. This boosts the capacitor voltage beyond the
level that would be obtained by the line current alone. Each thyristor
is triggered once per cycle and has a conduction interval that
is shorter than a half-cycle of the rated mains frequency.<BR>
If the additional voltage created by the circulating current pulses
is controlled to be proportional to the line current, the transmission
system will perceive the TCSC as having a virtually increased
reactance beyond the physical reactance of the capacitor. Due
to the sub-cycle conduction interval of the thyristors, harmonic
currents will be injected into the capacitor. Harmonic currents
increase with the boost level. In fact the scheme can provide
an accurate setting of the compensation degree, with a high resolution
as well as an SSR immune series compensation even at high compensation
degrees.
<P>
<IMG SRC="sctech07.gif" ALIGN="BOTTOM"> 
<P>
The characteristics of a TCSC are:
<UL>
<LI><B>Hardware design is geared to the maximum voltage that is
to be handled</B> 
<LI><B>Mvar rating of the capacitor bank is proportional to the
product of the maximum voltage and the corresponding maximum current</B>

<LI><B>Advanced controls, particularly for the SSR mitigation
mode</B> 
<LI><B>Unrestricted number of operations and sequences</B> 
<LI><B>Accurate setting of the compensation degree</B> 
<LI><B>Adequate for frequent adjustment of compensation degree
for SSR mitigation and damping of power swings</B> 
</UL>
<HR>

<P>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="abbhand.gif" ALIGN=TOP> |<A HREF="home.htm">ABB Power Systems Home Page</A>
| <A HREF="http://www.abb.se">ABB Sweden</A> | </CENTER><HR>

<P>
<A HREF="copyrajt.htm">Copyright </A>ABB Power Systems Sweden 1995. <BR>
<B>Latest updated 18-Mars-1996</B> 
</BODY>

