<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB Infosystems News</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="infback.JPG" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#FF0A11" VLINK="#FF690E">
<IMG ALIGN=Right SRC="logo.gif" WIDTH=116 HEIGHT=55>
<P>




<TABLE CELLSPACING=4 CELLPADDING=2 BORDER=0>
<TR>
		<TD  height=120 WIDTH=180>&nbsp;</TD>
  <TD WIDTH=*>&nbsp;</TD>

<TR VALIGN=LEFT>
	<TD HEIGHT=240 WIDTH=180></TD>
	
<TD WIDTH=400>
<B>ABB Infosystems and Sdra Data join forces.</B><HR>
<BR>


The operations of Sdra Skogsgarna's former data specialist Sdra Data AB were integrated with ABB Infosystems on 1 April. For ABB Infosystems, this brought a welcome addition of competence and an even wider range of skills, not least in the forestry industry. For the customers, Sdra Data's services for applications such as maintenance control, economy control and order, stock and invoice processing benefit from a boost in resources for further development. The benefits are seen both in terms of a new functional approach and in an upgrade in the technology used, which in turn means added security for those who already use these services or expect to use them in the future.<P>

<B>Facts about Merit</B><P>

The Merit maintenance system is a powerful tool used by maintenance departments in industry. The system was developed by Sdra Data, formerly part of Sdra Skogsgarna, and it is installed in various branches of the forestry industry, in the chemical industry, engineering and power suppliers in Sweden and Norway. Merit is a standard system which is installed in any number of modules to suit individual needs.
<LI> Basic module
<LI>Plant module
<LI>Drawing and Document Register
<LI>Parts handling
<LI>Preventive maintenance
<LI>Work-order processing
<LI>Follow-up module
<LI>Stores and Purchasing
<LI>Project handling<P>

Merit is used in the UNIX environment for various hardware platforms such as HP, SUN Digital IBM, and with a free relation database (Ingres, Oracle, Sybase). A readymade interface permits integration with other systems such as economy and finance, production, CAD and other systems. There are also functions for multimedia. The workstations may be anything from simple terminals to X-terminals, PCs operating under Windows, dedicated work-stations and Macintosh computers. <P>

Further development and maintenance of Merit take place continuously and in such a way that there are no differences in standard software irrespective of environment. Individually tailored applications are separated in dedicated modules which are specific to each individual customer.<P>

Merit's user association, which ties together customers from different backgrounds and countries, helps ensure strong, motivated and functional development of the system. Both users and ABB Infosystems want to continue developing Merit with flexible and integrated functions within the customer's overall IT requirements.<P>

Want to find out more?<BR>
Contact Bengt Alsed<BR>
ABB Infosystems in Klippan Tel +46 435 120 90<P><HR>
<A NAME="isdn"></A>
<P>&nbsp;<P>

<B>Sverigentet ABB SN grows with ISDN</B><HR><BR>

ABB Infosystems offers ISDN connections with ABB's fixed Swedish network. ISDN (Integrated Services Digital Network) is a communication architecture which integrates speech, data and graphic transmission simultaneously and on the same line. The telecom industry's ISDN expansion has increased considerably in Europe over the past twelve months, paving the way for numerous integrated applications. The main benefit is high transmission speed at low cost.<P>

<B>Cheap supplement</B><BR>
The ISDN transmission speed is normally 64 kbit/s, compared with the dedicated line network which has transmission speeds from 64 kbit/s to 2 Mbit/s. In the dedicated network, the lines are connected round the clock and are intended for continuous intensive traffic. With ISDN, you only pay for the duration for which you are linked up. Irrespective of where in the network the nodes are located, the cost is only for a local or national call. All this taken together means that the total cost for an ISDN connection is often less than half that of a fixed line of corresponding capacity.<P>

<B>Far lower costs</B><BR>
ISDN thus offers LAN client/server environments for LAN communication at a far lower cost than for a dedicated line. The break-even point for cost-efficiency is around 4 hours link-up time per day. For a small office with just a few staff members who only need to use the net occasionally, it is an excellent choice. Within ABB, there are still many company offices which are not connected to the Swedish network but with ISDN technology, the number of subscriptions is expected to increase sharply.<P>

<B>Links to small offices</B><BR>
ABB Flkt's branch offices/regional subsidiaries and ABB Installation are examples of companies which have begun linking up their smaller regional offices to ISDN. As demand increases, ABB Infosystems will increase the number of ISDN nodes in the Swedish network.
 <P>


Want to find out more?<BR>
Contact: <A HREF="mailto:stig.skogstedt@seinf.mail.abb.se">Stig Skogstedt</A><BR>
ABB Infosystems. Tel: +46 21 323 674<P><HR>
<A NAME="easy"></A>
<P>&nbsp;<P>


<B>Easy Flow - a 40-million kronor agreement with ABB Industrial Systems</B><HR>
<BR>

ABB Industrial Systems chose ABB Infosystems as partner and integrator for implementation of the German SAP R/3 standard system. Easy Flow is the name of the implementation project which will continue for two to three years.<P>

And now it is time for ABB industrial Systems to leave the AROS environment. Functions such as order handling, purchasing, engineering, manufacture, economy, invoicing, logistics etc which today are handled in the mainframe environment will work more smoothly in a flexible client/server environment. SAP R/3 is a modern tool which will help improve our operational processes in our bid to offer customers all-inclusive solutions of world-beating standard.<BR>
"Our choice of ABB Infosystems as partner offers us an excellent basis for carrying through the project successfully with our combined resources," says Lars Linde, President of ABB Industrial Systems.
 <P> 

After a detailed assessment, SAP R/3 was chosen as the basic system to support the company's activities in plant operations, development, production, sales, economy steering and quality follow-up. The system will be introduced at all seven of ABB Industrial Systems's divisions at ten sites in Sweden. The order is valued at 40 million Swedish kronor and covers a comprehensive undertaking whereby ABB Infosystems is responsible for the introduction of SAP R/3 and training in its use. The agreement covers licences for 1,500 users and maintenance for four years. The delivery agreement also includes an option for ABB Industrial Systems to place an order for operation of the new system at ABB Infosystems throughout the project duration, and additionally for a further two years. This option is valued at just over 10 million kronor. ABB Industrial Systems is conducting several projects with T50; with this latest operational development and backed up by SAP R/3, the intention is to establish reliable system support for these projects. Some of the goals are to streamline and increase the degree of automation in the order handling and production processes, and to improve the quality of the plant project's operation and follow-up.<P>

SAP R/3 is a flexible tool which supports a simple working approach and assists forthcoming operational changes. One important aspect in the partnership with ABB Industrial Systems is that Kjell Gustafsson in the ABB Infosystems executive management takes up a position as project manager at ABB Industrial Systems. ABB Infosystems has also signed an agreement with its suppliers SAP Svenska AB and Management Application Support, both of which have several years of experience with SAP R/3.<P> 

Do you want to find out more about SAP R/3?<BR>
Contact: <A HREF="mailto:johan.berg@seinf.mail.abb.se">Johan Berg</A><BR>
Tel: +46 21 323 492<P><HR>

