<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB Infosystems Security / Threats</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../infback.JPG" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#FF0A11" VLINK="#7E0B06">
<IMG ALIGN=Right SRC="../logo.gif" ALT="ABB Logotype" WIDTH=116 HEIGHT=55>
<P>




<TABLE CELLSPACING=4 CELLPADDING=2 BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD  height=120 WIDTH=180>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH=*>&nbsp;</TD>

<TR VALIGN=LEFT>
<TD WIDTH=180>
<A HREF="_welcome.html"><IMG SRC="../secbte+.JPG" ALT="Security" WIDTH=140 border=0 HEIGHT=35></A><br>
<IMG SRC="servpic.JPG" ALT="Threat" WIDTH=140 HEIGHT=120><P></TD>
	
<TD WIDTH=400>
<FONT SIZE=+2>How big is the threat?</FONT>
<HR>
<P>
There are many opinions about how big the threat against computer security is. One of the best reports we have found recently is: <BR>
<B>Information Security: Computer Attacks at Department of Defense Pose Increasing Risks.</B> Chapter Report, 05/22/96, <A HREF="http://www.gao.gov/bestsellers/ai96084.pdf">GAO/AIMD-96-84</A>. <A HREF="http://www.gao.gov/bestsellers/bestitl.htm#5">[Brief citations]</A> <P>
In this report from the United States General Accounting Office, issued in May 1996, the following facts were stated: 
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE><LI>250.000 computer attacks were estimated against Defence during 1995 
<LI>65% of all attacks were estimated to have been successful  
<LI>Only 4% of all attacks were detected by the target organizations 
<LI>Only 27% of those detected attacks were reported and further investigated 
<LI>The number of attacks are doubling each year </BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>&nbsp;<P>

<HR>
<P>
</td>

