<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB Infosystems Security Audit</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../infback.JPG" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#FF0A11" VLINK="#7E0B06">
<IMG ALIGN=Right SRC="../logo.gif" ALT="ABB Logotype" WIDTH=116 HEIGHT=55>
<P>




<TABLE CELLSPACING=4 CELLPADDING=2 BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD  height=120 WIDTH=180>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH=*>&nbsp;</TD>

<TR VALIGN=LEFT>
<TD WIDTH=180>
<A HREF="_welcome.html"><IMG SRC="../secbte+.JPG" ALT="Security" WIDTH=140 border=0 HEIGHT=35></A><br>
<IMG SRC="revis.JPG" ALT="Revision" WIDTH=140 HEIGHT=120><P></TD>
	
<TD WIDTH=400>S E C U R I T Y &nbsp;A U D I T
<P>

<FONT SIZE=+2>Information Systems Auditing</FONT>
<HR>
<P>
During a security audit we examine and evaluate the security by a number of criterias, and write a report over our findings. The first step is to examine all relevant documentation and the effectiveness of the security policy. At the same time we also do interviews. The next step is to do a number of tests based on checklists and manual hacking methods, as well as with computer based scanning tools. Of course we do follow commonly accepted <A HREF="itrev.html"> Information Systems Auditing Standards </A> and practicies.
<P>
<HR>
<P>

</td>

<tr>
<td WIDTH=180><A HREF="../seinfbe.html"><IMG ALIGN=Left SRC="../pil.JPG" WIDTH=31 HEIGHT=19 BORDER=0></A></td>
<td><IMG ALIGN=Left SRC="../infolog.JPG" WIDTH=112 HEIGHT=15><P>
</td>
</TABLE>

</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
