<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB Infosystems Security Policy</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../infback.JPG" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#FF0A11" VLINK="#7E0B06">
<IMG ALIGN=Right SRC="../logo.gif" ALT="ABB Logotype" WIDTH=116 HEIGHT=55>
<P>




<TABLE CELLSPACING=4 CELLPADDING=2 BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD  height=120 WIDTH=180>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH=*>&nbsp;</TD>

<TR VALIGN=LEFT>
<TD WIDTH=180>
<A HREF="_welcome.html"><IMG SRC="../secbte+.JPG" ALT="Security" WIDTH=140 border=0 HEIGHT=35></A><br>
<IMG SRC="policy.JPG" ALT="Policy" WIDTH="140" HEIGHT="120" BORDER="0"><P></TD>
	
<TD WIDTH=400>S E C U R I T Y &nbsp;P O L I C Y
<P>

<FONT SIZE=+2>You need a strategy to maintain security </FONT>
<HR>
<P>
We help the customer to make a working security policy and how to enforce its usage. As a base for the policy we use a commonly accepted standard and then make all necessary changes in order to customise it to the organisation. We help to create a flexible and not to complicated policy, which helps it to work in practice. It is also important to include all relevant items in the policy. Some parts that should
be included are computer security, information security, network security and segmentation and finally measures to enforce the policy by means of security budgets and security auditing at regular intervalls. 
<P>

<HR>
<P>

</td>

<tr>
<td WIDTH=180><A HREF="../seinfbe.html"><IMG ALIGN=Left SRC="../pil.JPG" WIDTH=31 HEIGHT=19 BORDER=0></A></td>
<td><IMG ALIGN=Left SRC="../infolog.JPG" WIDTH=112 HEIGHT=15><P>
</td>
</TABLE>

