<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ABB Infosystems Information Security</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../infback.JPG" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#FF0A11" VLINK="#7E0B06">
<IMG ALIGN=Right SRC="../logo.gif" ALT="ABB Logotype" WIDTH=116 HEIGHT=55>
<P>




<TABLE CELLSPACING=4 CELLPADDING=2 BORDER=0>
<TR>
<TD  height=120 WIDTH=180>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH=*>&nbsp;</TD>

<TR VALIGN=LEFT>
<TD WIDTH=180>
<A HREF="_welcome.html"><IMG SRC="../secbte+.JPG" ALT="Security" WIDTH=140 border=0 HEIGHT=35></A><br>
<IMG SRC="infosak.JPG" ALT="Data theft" WIDTH="140" HEIGHT="120" BORDER="0"><P></TD>
	
<TD WIDTH=400>I N F O R M A T I O N &nbsp; S E C U R I T Y
<P>

<FONT SIZE=+2>Protect from unwanted visitors </FONT>
<HR>
<P>
In all computer systems exists information that must be protected. We first check
that we have a solid base to build on. The computer network and the computers
must have a sufficient security level, which is checked with our <A HREF="_sakrev.html">Security Audit</A>. It is often adviseable to strip the operating system by removing components and services that are not needed, which can introduce vulnerabilities when used. After these steps are covered it is possible to make the information systems themselves secure, whether they are an economy system or a production system in an industrial environment. At this point we check that all prerequsites in form of customisation, documentation, surveillance and control measures are fulfilled. 
<P>
<HR>
<P>

</td>

<tr>
<td WIDTH=180><A HREF="../seinfbe.html"><IMG ALIGN=Left SRC="../pil.JPG" WIDTH=31 HEIGHT=19 BORDER=0></A></td>
<td><IMG ALIGN=Left SRC="../infolog.JPG" WIDTH=112 HEIGHT=15><P>
</td>
</TABLE>

