<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">
  <TITLE>Current Minneapolis Jobs</TITLE>
  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="Judy Brown">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000567" BGCOLOR="#ffffff">

<P><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="2" CELLPADDING="0">
<TR>
<TD VALIGN="TOP"><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" ALT="logo" ALIGN="BOTTOM"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="CENTER"><H1 ALIGN=RIGHT>City of Minneapolis</H1>

<H2 ALIGN=RIGHT>Job Listings for <BR>
the Week of January 13, 1997</H2>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<BR>
<BR>
<HR ALIGN=LEFT><A HREF="/index.html">Home</A> | <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's
Hot</A> | <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A> | <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A> | <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A> <HR ALIGN=LEFT><BR>
<I>All new City employees must become residents of the City of Minneapolis
within six months of passing probation.</I> <BR>
<I>This includes City Council Departments, Park and Recreation Board and
Public Library, but not Public Schools.</I> <BR>
<I>To apply, call the phone number listed with each job. All jobs require
completion of an application prior to the due date.</I> <HR ALIGN=LEFT><BR>
<B>BILINGUAL PROGRAM ASSISTANT - $12.92 per hour</B><BR>
Assist Minneapolis Public Schools' professional staff as an interpreter
to facilitate the provision of health, education, or other services to non-English
speaking and/or bilingual/bicultural community members, students, and their
families. Requires high school diploma/GED. Experience working with children
is highly desired. Closes January 24, 1997. For information, call 673-3332.<BR>
<BR>
<B>CLERK TYPIST I (BOARD OF EDUCATION) - $10.72 per hour</B><BR>
Performs routing, typing/data entry, office work; input data into computer
records through keyboard entry or CRT terminal; types from straight copy/longhand
draft/rough typescripts/dictaphone or other transcribing equipment. Must
be able to type 40 words per minute, adequately perform reading/writing/numerical
functions, and follow simple oral/written instructions. Closes January 24,
1997. For information, call 673-3332.<BR>
<BR>
<B>CLERK TYPIST II (BOARD OF EDUCATION) - $12.10 per hour</B><BR>
Types difficult letters/memoranda, statistical/brief/abstract/financial
reports, agenda, contracts, requisitions/vouchers, warrants, and/or other
matters from copy, rough draft, dictaphone, or other transcribing equipment.
May supervise clerical workers. Requires two full-time years experience
performing clerical duties in an office environment which must have included
one full-time year experience utilizing personal computers for word processing
and other uses. Closes January 24, 1997. For information, call 673-3332.<BR>
<BR>
<B>EDUCATIONAL ASSISTANT I - $8.55 per hour</B><BR>
Assist licensed Minneapolis Public Schools personnel in a variety of school
functions/locations; assist in programs focusing on developing/raising the
level of academics/social skills of students in curriculum instructional
areas who have fallen below their stage of development. Requires high school
diploma/GED. Must be able to exercise/use good judgment when interacting
with students. Closes January 24, 1997. For information, call 673-3332.<BR>
<BR>
<B>PUBLIC WORKS MAINTENANCE DISPATCHER I - $801. bi-weekly</B><BR>
Receives calls and dispatches emergency and routine services; answers telephone
inquiries from the public and other departments; relays data and other information
to service crews via two-way radio; maintains records and prepares reports.
Must be familiar with basic office skills and procedures; have good oral
communication skills; familiarity with geographic layout of City streets.
Closes January 17, 1997. For information, call 673-2281.<BR>
<BR>
<B>VEHICLE RECORDS AIDE $2108. per month </B><BR>
Maintains records related to vehicle towing impounding, provides information/assistance;
receives phone inquiries and/or reports of stolen or impounded and hold
vehicles; assists citizens and police officers in claiming or inquiring
about impounded vehicles. Requires two years clerical experience with similar
duties. Should be able to operate a computer, type 40 words per minute,
and deal effectively with the public. Open indefinitely. For information,
call 673-2281.<BR>
<BR>
<B>WATER WORKS SERVICE WORKER I - $1149. bi-weekly</B><BR>
Maintain/repair city water distribution system; excavate through concrete
and frost using jackhammers, shovels, and similar tools; repair/maintain
water mains, hydrants, manholes, gate valves, and stop boxes. Requires one
year of experience maintaining and repairing water mains, gates, and hydrants;
installing pipe and water mains or related construction experience providing
a good knowledge of materials, tools, and procedures used in water distribution
systems. Closes January 24, 1997. For information, call 673-2281.<BR>
<BR>
<B>YOUTH PROGRAM SPECIALIST - $848 bi-weekly</B><BR>
Work within the Minneapolis Park and Recreation Board's Youthline Outreach
Mentorship program; serve as primary contact person for youth in their participation
in recreational activities and leadership opportunities for youth ages 12-16.
Requires two years full-time experience in youth work similar to this position
and two years of college or technical school in Youth Studies, Sociology,
Psychology, Recreation, or a related field. Closes January 28, 1997. For
information, call 673-3104.<BR>
<BR>
<B>ASSISTANT CHILD CARE WORKER - EARLY CHILDHOOD FAMILY EDUCATION - Salary
$8.96 per hour</B><BR>
This position, under supervision, supervises and monitors children at all
times in classrooms, lunchrooms, while on field trips and on the playgrounds;
assists with goal setting as well as the implementation and evaluation of
various programs, projects and activities at a location for children from
birth to five years old. Education and experience required and may be met
in several different ways. NO RESIDENCY REQUIRED. Open indefinitely. For
information, call 673-3332.<BR>
<BR>
<B>ASSISTANT CHILD CARE WORKER, MPLS KIDS /LATCH KEY PROGRAM - Salary $8.96
per hour</B><BR>
Part-time and on-call substitute positions available working with children
ages 6-12 years of age before and after school to help lead sports, active
play, arts and crafts. Education and experience required. NO RESIDENCY REQUIRED.
Open indefinitely. For information, call 673-3332.<BR>
<BR>
<B>CITY PLANNER I - $1044. Bi-weekly</B><BR>
Generalist/specialist needed to research, develop plan, and program in a
wide variety of areas. Requires Master's degree in Planning or closely related
field by the date of hire OR a Bachelor's degree in Planning or a closely
related field, plus two full-time years planning experience. Open indefinitely.
For information, call 673-3332.<BR>
<BR>
<B>CONVENTION CENTER OPERATIONS AND MAINTENANCE SPECIALIST- $8.37 per hour</B><BR>
This position will be responsible for the day-to-day cleaning and maintenance
of the Minneapolis Convention Center and provide for set-up and tear down
labor for all events. Irregular schedules, such as evenings, weekends and
holidays will be required. There are no guaranteed working hours. THESE
ON-CALL POSITIONS MAY ALLOW INDIVIDUALS TO BE CONSIDERED FOR FULL-TIME STATUS
IN THE FUTURE. Must be at least 18 years of age to operate the equipment
and machinery. Must also have sufficient physical strength and the ability
to perform manual tasks and lift medium to heavy weights. Must be able to
walk for long periods of time. Open indefinitely. For information, call
673-2283.<BR>
<BR>
<B>EPIDEMIOLOGIST - Salary $1,457.00 Bi-weekly</B><BR>
Performs work in population-based assessment, analysis, and evaluation of
the health status of individuals, families, and communities in Mpls. Must
have a Master's degree in epidemiology and must possess knowledge of and
practical experience in core public health functions, state and local health
problems and programs related to diverse urban communities. Open indefinitely.
For information, call 673-2283.<BR>
<BR>
<B>FOOD SERVICE ASSISTANT I - BOARD OF EDUCATION - Salary $9.52 per hour</B><BR>
On-call substitute positions available working 2 or more hours per day.
Help prepare and serve meals (mostly midday hours) at the Nutrition Center
or schools. All are on-call substitute positions during school year, but
may lead to full-time permanent jobs. NO RESIDENCY REQUIRED. Open indefinitely.
For information, call 673-3332.<BR>
<BR>
<B>POLICE TYPIST - Salary $908.00 bi-weekly</B><BR>
Mpls Police Dept. is seeking applicants with two years of clerical experience
to process police department reports and documents on a rotating shift basis.
Must be able to type 50 wpm and have two years of clerical experience which
includes data entry or typing. Verbatim dictaphone or voice digital system
experience is highly desirable. Business education beyond high school may
be substituted for up to one year of experience. Open indefinitely. For
information, call 673-2281.<BR>
<BR>
<B>RECREATION PLUS COORDINATOR - $7.82 per hour</B><BR>
Assist in implementing programs, projects, and activities at a recreation
center for the Minneapolis Park and Recreation Board's Recreation Plus school-aged
child care program. Requires ONE of the following: a) two-year Child Development
degree; b) six months full-time (or equivalent part-time) experience as
a Child Care Aide in a licensed day care center; c) two years of post-secondary
education PLUS three post-secondary age related child development/human
relations training courses; d) one year full-time (or equivalent part-time)
work with children, six months of which must be with school-aged children.
Current First Aid/CPR certification desirable. Open indefinitely. For information,
call 673-3104. <BR>
<BR>
<B>SCHOOL BUS DRIVER - Salary $9.00 - $16.00 per hour</B><BR>
Positions available in the Mpls Public Schools. Requires MN commercial driver's
license with school bus Type I, passenger and air brake endorsements, good
driving record, effective behavior modification with children, the ability
to read, and be able to lift 50 lbs. NO RESIDENCY REQUIRED. Open indefinitely.
For information, call 673-3332.<BR>
<HR ALIGN=LEFT><B>THE CITY OF MINNEAPOLIS IS AN AFFIRMATIVE ACTION/EQUAL
OPPORTUNITY EMPLOYER</B><HR ALIGN=LEFT><BR>
For more information, call 673-CITY, ext. 11 <BR>
Deaf/hard of hearing may call TTY 673-2157</P>

<P>Or stop by our offices:<BR>
<BR>
City of Minneapolis Human Resources <BR>
Personnel Services Division <BR>
312 Third Avenue South, Suite 151 <BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415 <BR>
