<P><B>NEWS</B></P>

<UL>
   <LI>Yes, we are collecting Christmas trees. Just place them next
   to your garbage cart by 6:00 a.m. on any garbage collection day.
   Please remove ornaments and tinsel, and cut trees taller than six
   feet in half. If you want your tree composted, also remove plastic
   trees bags and save the tree in your back yard -- off the alley --
   until yardwaste collection begins in mid-April.
</UL>

<P><B>SERVICES</B></P>

<P>We provide a comprehensive solid waste and recycling service for
our customers:</P>

<UL>
   <LI><A HREF="garbage.html">Garbage collection</A>
   
   <LI><A HREF="large.html">Large item collection</A>
   
   <LI><A HREF="rec.html">Recycling collection</A>
   
   <LI><A HREF="yw.html">Yard waste collection</A>
   
   <LI><A HREF="voucher.html">Vouchers</A> for drop-off of excess
   garbage, construction and paving materials, and tires.
   
   <LI><A HREF="clean.html">Neighborhood clean sweeps</A>
   
   <LI><A HREF="holiday.html">Holiday collection schedule</A>
</UL>

<P><B>TIDBITS</B></P>

<P>For more about the Division of Solid Waste &amp; Recycling, check
out these references:</P>

<UL>
   <LI><A HREF="overview.html">Overview</A>
   
   <LI><A HREF="history.html">Historical highlights</A>
   
   <LI><A HREF="tech.html">Technical details</A> about contracts,
   equipment and routes.
   
   <LI>Tonnage Collected in <A HREF="tons95.html">1995</A>,
   <A HREF="tons94.html">1994</A>, <A HREF="tons93.html">1993</A>.
</UL>

<P><B>WHAT TO DO WITH . . .?</B></P>

<P>This section is still under construction. It will include an
alphabetical listing of <B>what to do</B> with a variety of materials
including <A HREF="hhw.html">household hazardous waste</A> and
<A HREF="motoroil.html">motor oil and filters</A>.</P>

<P><B>YOU CAN MAKE A DIFFERENCE </B></P>

<P>This section is still under construction. It will have information
about <A HREF="compost.html">home composting</A>, <B>recycling
drop-offs</B>, and other ways you can <B>reduce &amp; reuse</B>.</P>

<P>
<HR>
</P>

<ADDRESS><B>Division of Solid Waste &amp; Recycling</B><BR>

309 2nd Avenue South Room 210<BR>

Minneapolis, MN 55401</ADDRESS>

<P><B>Phone Number</B> <B>612-673-2917</B>
