<HTML>
<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">
  <TITLE>Minneapolis Snow Emergency Regulations</TITLE>
  <META NAME="AUTHOR" CONTENT="City of Mpls.">
  <META NAME="OPERATOR" CONTENT="City of Mpls.">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#010049" BGCOLOR="#ffffff">

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Welcome to Winter in Minneapolis!</H1>

<H2 ALIGN=CENTER><BR>
1996-97 Minneapolis Snow Emergency <BR>
Parking Information</H2>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>Please make your bookmark to our <A HREF="/index.html">Home
Page</A> to find out whether there is a snow emergency in effect.</P>

<P ALIGN=CENTER><STRONG><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Note: Due to snow accumulation,
Minneapolis has declared a </FONT><A HREF="#snowban">snow parking ban</A><FONT
 COLOR="#FF0000"> effective December 18, 1996 until April 1, 1997 unless
lifted earlier by City officials. <BR>
Click here to jump to the </FONT><A HREF="/publications/news-release/pkgban96.html">news
release</A><FONT COLOR="#FF0000"> for detailed information.</FONT></STRONG></P>

<H3><HR ALIGN=LEFT></H3>

<P ALIGN=CENTER>Jump to <A HREF="#maps">&quot;Where do I park?&quot;</A></P>

<H3><HR ALIGN=LEFT></H3>

<P><B>MAKE A SNOW SMART MOVE.</B> During Snow Emergencies, vehicles MUST
be moved for plowing. If your vehicle is parked in violation of the Snow
Emergency rules, it may be tagged and towed to the Municipal Impound Lot.
<BR>
<BR>
Call 348-SNOW, our 24-hour hotline, or watch City Cable Channel 34 for complete
Snow Emergency parking information. Your cooperation helps to ensure public
safety during heavy snowfalls. <BR>
<BR>
<B>COLOR-CODED STREET SIGNS.</B> Snow Emergency routes are marked in two
ways - with RED Snow Emergency signs and BLUE street name signs. Streets
that are not Snow Emergency routes have green or brown street name signs.
<BR>
<BR>
<B>OBSERVE EMERGENCY HOURS.</B> Be Snow Smart! Don't park your vehicle during
hours when parking is prohibited even if your street APPEARS to be plowed.
<BR>
<BR>
<B>TEMPORARY SIGNS.</B> Streets and alleys are often plowed, sanded and
salted without a Snow Emergency declaration. Temporary no-parking signs
will be posted if necessary. <BR>
<BR>
<B>PARKING TICKETS.</B> Tickets will be issued for parking violations, and
vehicles may be towed to the Impound Lot. <BR>
<BR>
<B>THE IMPOUND LOT.</B> The Municipal Impound Lot, located at 51 Colfax
Avenue North (2 blocks south of Glenwood Avenue and west of Lyndale Avenue),
is open 24 hours a day, 7 days a week. Call 673-5777 with your license plate
number to determine if your vehicle has been towed. Fees are $70 for towing
and $10 daily for storage. The lot accepts cash, personal checks, VISA and
MasterCard. <BR>
<BR>
<B>SEVERE WINTER STORMS.</B> When a major storm is predicted, Minneapolis
may impose temporary parking restrictions IN ADVANCE of the storm. Parking
may be prohibited on the EVEN side of residential streets for up to 48 hours.
<BR>
<BR>
<B>WINTER PARKING RESTRICTIONS.</B> Minneapolis officials will decide after
each Snow Emergency whether it is necessary to continue residential parking
restrictions. If required due to snow accumulation, parking will be banned
on the EVEN side of residential streets. Once imposed, this ban will remain
in effect until April 1 unless removed earlier by City officials. <BR>
<BR>
<B>SHOVEL YOUR SIDEWALKS PROMPTLY.</B> Keep a critical part of Minneapolis'
transportation system moving. City ordinances require that sidewalks of
single family homes and duplexes be cleared within 24 hours after a snowfall.
<BR>
<BR>
Sidewalks in commercial areas and adjacent to apartment buildings must be
cleared within four daytime hours. Removal of snow from private property
into streets and alleys is prohibited. <BR>
<BR>
<B>HELP YOUR NEIGHBORS.</B> Help your elderly neighbors and those with disabilities
clear their sidewalks. Remove snow build-up at corners and around fire hydrants.
When you go out of town, arrange to have your sidewalk cleared and your
vehicles moved during Snow Emergencies. <BR>
<BR>
<B>CALL FOR ASSISTANCE.</B> If you are physically unable to care for your
sidewalk, community organizations will provide snow removal assistance for
a fee. Seniors needing assistance can call the Senior Services Office, 673-3004.
<BR>
<BR>
Call 673-2441 to report unsafe sidewalks or to find out where to get free
sidewalk sand. <BR>
<BR>
<HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<H1><A NAME="maps"></A>Where do I park?</H1>

<P><A NAME="snowban"></A><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">Please note the City's Snow
Parking Ban now in effect until April 1, 1997, unless lifted earlier by
City officials. The snow ban prohibits parking on the even side of residential
streets anytime except Day Three of a snow emergency. Snow Emergency Routes
and Parkways are not affected by the ban.</FONT></P>

<P><FONT COLOR="#FF0000">This ban helps keep streets passable so that emergency
vehicles can get through quickly and safely. The graphics below have been
altered from their original versions to reflect the new parking restrictions.</FONT></P>

<H3><BR>
First Day</H3>

<P>SNOW EMERGENCY announced on radio and television.<BR>
<IMG SRC="day_1.gif" WIDTH="343" HEIGHT="195" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" ALIGN=
"BOTTOM" ALT="First day parking"><BR>
Parking prohibited from 9 p.m. to 8 a.m. on BOTH sides of Snow Emergency
routes. Snow Parking Ban still prohibits EVEN side parking on residential
streets.<BR>
<HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<H3>Second Day</H3>

<P><IMG SRC="day_2.gif" WIDTH="452" HEIGHT="196" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" ALIGN=
"BOTTOM" ALT="Second day parking"><BR>
Parking prohibited from 8 a.m. to 8 p.m. on the EVEN side of residential
streets and on BOTH sides of parkways. Move vehicles from the ODD side of
residential streets to the EVEN side after 8 p.m. <BR>
<HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<H3>Third Day</H3>

<P><IMG SRC="day_3.gif" WIDTH="343" HEIGHT="196" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" ALIGN=
"BOTTOM" ALT="Third day parking"><BR>
Parking prohibited from 8 a.m. to 8 p.m. on the ODD side of residential
streets.<BR>
<HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<H3>After Third Day</H3>

<P><IMG SRC="all_sts.gif" WIDTH="343" HEIGHT="196" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG=
"3"><BR>
At 8 p.m. on the THIRD DAY, parking resumes on all streets unless posted
otherwise. Snow Parking Ban prohibits parking on the EVEN side of residential
streets.<BR>
<BR>
