<TITLE>Assessor</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Assessor"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Assessor</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The function of this department is to accurately and equitably value and
classify all real estate in the city so that the tax base can be determined.

<P>State law requires that: 
<UL>
	<LI>The values are placed at 100&#37; of market value as determined by annual
	State Department of Revenue sale surveys.

	<LI>Each property in the city must be viewed and reappraised at least every
	four years.

	<LI>The property must be properly classified: <A HREF="#homestead">homestead</A>, non-homestead,
	taxable, exempt, apartment, industrial, etc.
</UL>

<P>The department can explain to property owners how the market value of their
property was determined, and also explain avenues of appeal if they disagree with
the assessment.

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Minneapolis Assessor's Office</B><BR>
Room 100<BR>
309 2 Av S <BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55401-2234
</ADDRESS>

<P><B>Phone Numbers</B><BR>
Homestead Information (612) 673-2382<BR>
Real Estate Information (612) 673-2387<BR>
Legal Descriptions, Lot Size, P.I.D. (612) 348-3271<BR>
Real Estate Taxes, Property Owners (612) 348-3011<BR>
Special Assessment (612) 673-2811<BR>

<P><HR>

<A NAME="homestead"></A>
<H2>Homesteading A Property in Minneapolis</H2>

<P>What is homesteading? Who qualifies? Refer to our list of
<A HREF="faq.html">common questions and answers to them</A>.

<P>If you think you want to file for a homestead, there is information on
<A HREF="homestead.html">requesting a homestead</A>.

