<HTML>
<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Cyberspace Rangers</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Cyberspace Rangers"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Cyberspace Rangers</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->
<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include --><P>
The Cyberspace Rangers are a diverse group of Minneapolis City employees
who meet as needed to share information and discuss Internet issues. The
group's mission is to assist and advise City departments as they explore
possible uses for emerging technological methods of communication. 
<H4>Major Goals </H4>
The Cyberspace Rangers will:
<UL>
  <LI>Examine the Internet, specifically the World Wide Web, as a site for
disseminating City information. The group will guide the process of setting
up a City home page, which will provide an umbrella of general information
under which departments will be able to place their own information. City
departments currently using the Web to provide information will be hotlinked
from the City's home page. This will provide a single starting point for
users. In guiding the CityWeb project, the group will consider the merits
of encouraging a standard stylesheet, including common graphics/text to
be found on all pages under the City's control. 
  <LI><BR>
  <LI>Support the Minneapolis CityNet project as it connects City employees
to a common WAN. 
  <LI><BR>
  <LI>Support the efforts of the River Project and the NRP to establish
public access terminals throughout the city. 
  <LI><BR>
  <LI>Examine other emerging technology for possible use by city departments
and communicate their findings to department heads. 
</UL>
<H4>Mission and Objectives </H4>
As a service to Minneapolis citizens, we will provide a citizen-oriented,
easy-to-use online presence containing information about Minneapolis' local
government services. The City's presence on the Internet will help make
the city a better place to live, work, learn and play by establishing a
foundation for greater access to government services. <P>
To accomplish this mission, the project and its coordinators will:
<UL>
  <LI>encourage participation in local government and city life; 
  <LI>make local government more accessible and more interactive to its
customers; 
  <LI>advocate for greater access to the City's Internet information, both
for all its citizens and for its employees; and 
  <LI>carry a consistent graphical look and will coordinate messages and
content wherever possible with other City-sponsored communication vehicles.
<BR>
</UL>
<H4>Values<BR>
</H4>
We place highest value on the information needs of Minneapolis' citizens:
the people who live work and play here. For the website, our values include:
<UL>
  <LI>Customer-focused layout
  <LI>Consistent, accurate information
  <LI>Ease of use
  <LI>Interactivity: an e-mail address on every page
  <LI>Compatibility with major Web browsers
  <LI>Accessibility from slow modems without significant delays<P>
</UL>
<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
