<html><head><title>Garbage Collection</title></head><body>City of Minneapolis, Division of Solid Waste & Recycling<H2>GARBAGE COLLECTION</H2><HR width=100%><p><b>COLLECTION BEGINS AT...</b><p>Garbage collection is weekly and begins at 6:00 am. Please have your cart at the curb-line or alley-line by 6:00 am.<p>When your regular collection day falls on or after New Year's Day, Memorial Day, Fourth of July, Labor Day, Thanksgiving Day, or Christmas Day, garbage collection will be one day later than normal <p>In the winter, shovel a 36" wide path through the snow, including snow left by the plow, to the curb or alley.<p><HR width=100%><p><b>HOW TO PREPARE</b><p>Bag garbage and place in the garbage cart.   Maximum weight for the large cart and contents is 200 lbs.  Garbage is not collected from cans or non-city carts.<p><ul><li><b>Ashes & Pet Feces - </b>Double bag and place in the cart.<p><li><b>Carpet - </b>Roll and tie with string or twine (not wire).  Rolls must be less than 5 feet long, 12 inches wide and 40 lbs. Set next to cart. Limit of two rolls a week.<p><li><b>Extra garbage - </b>Bag or box additional garbage and place next to the garbage cart.  Limit of two extra bags and boxes per week and each must weigh less than 40 lbs.  Excess garbage on a regular basis requires an additional garbage cart.<p><li><b>Large amounts of garbage - </b>Such as a move-out, are not collected, but you can get a <a HREF=voucher.html>voucher</a> and bring the garbage to the transfer station.<p><li><b>Large items</b> - See <a HREF="large.html">large item</a> collection.<p><li><b>Paint cans </b> - Must be empty or thoroughly dry. Remove lids and place in a bag or box next to the garbage cart.</ul><p><HR width=100%><p><b>ITEMS NOT COLLECTED WITH GARBAGE</b><p><ul><li>Auto Parts - antifreeze, brake fluid, motor oil & filters, scrap parts, and tires<p><li>Construction & Paving Materials - bricks, cement, lumber, plaster, roofing material, and sheetrock.<p><li>Commercial Trash<p><li>Dead Animals<p><li>Dirt, Rocks, Sod<p><li>Fluorescent lights<p><li>Hazardous waste - such as drain cleaners, herbicides, pesticides, paint, paint thinner, poison, wood preservatives and wood stains<p><li>Yard waste</ul><p><HR width=100%>Updated 3/8/96</body></html>
</DOC>
