<html><head>City of Minneapolis, Division of Solid Waste & Recycling<H2>LARGE ITEM COLLECTION</H2><HR width=100%><p></head><body><b>COLLECTION</b><p>Up to<b> two</b> large items are collected at a time. Please have your large items at your collection point by 6:00 am on the following days:<p><b>Garbage</b> day for burnable items such as:<ul>arm chairs, carpet, couches, wood chairs, wood tables...etc.</ul><p><b>Recycling</b> day for items such as:<ul><p><b>Major appliances</b> -- air conditioner, dehumidifier, dishwasher, dryer, freezer, garbage disposal, microwave, refrigerator, stove, trash compactor, and washer.<p><b>Metal items</b> -- bed frame, barbecue grill, bicycle, clothesline poles (cut off crossbar), file cabinet, metal shelves, pipes, swing set (take apart).<p><b>Hide-a-beds and console TVs</b></ul><p> If you are still not sure what is the correct day for a particular large item, put it out on your recycling day, and we will make sure the correct truck gets your large item.<p><HR width=100%><p><b>HOW TO PREPARE</b><p>Attach to each large item a note which says "For Sanitation" .<p><ul><li><b>Carpet</b> -- Roll and tie with string or twine (not wire).  Rolls must be less than 5 feet long, 12 inches wide and 40 lbs.<p><li><b>Clothesline poles</b> -- Cut off crossbar and remove concrete from poles.<p><li><b>Pipes</b> -- No longer than ten feet<p><li><b>Refrigerators and freezers</b> -- Remove doors<p><li><b>Swing set</b> -- Take apart and remove concrete from poles.</ul><p><HR width=100%><p><b>NOT COLLECTED WITH LARGE ITEMS</b><p><ul><li>Auto parts<li>Concrete tubs<li>Pianos<li>Propane tanks<li>55-gallon drums</ul><p><HR width=100%><p>Updated 12/1/95</body></html>
</DOC>
