<BODY>

<P>City of Minneapolis, Division of Solid Waste &amp; Recycling</P>

<H2>YARD WASTE COLLECTION</H2>

<P>
<HR>
<BR>

<B>COLLECTION BEGINS AT...</B></P>

<P>Yard waste collection ended for the season on November 24.</P>

<P>Check here in April for the start of yard waste collection in
1997.</P>

<P>
<HR>
<BR>

<B>HOW TO PREPARE</B></P>

<P><B>Grass and leaves:</B></P>

<UL>
   <LI>Place in plastic bags. Bags must weigh less than 40 lbs and be
   less than 33 gallons in volume.
   
   <LI>Also include other vegetation such as: acorns, apples, bark,
   garden plants, hay &amp; straw, pine cones, pine needles,
   tomatoes, twigs, weeds.
   
   <LI>Sod is accepted if the dirt is removed.
</UL>

<P><B>Brush and branches: </B></P>

<UL>
   <LI>No branches more than 3 inches in diameter.
   
   <LI>Bundle brush and branches
   
   <LI>Bundle with twine or rope. Bundles must be less than 3 feet
   long and weigh less than 40 lbs.
</UL>

<P>
<HR>
<BR>

<B>ITEMS NOT COLLECTED WITH YARDWASTE</B></P>

<UL>
   Dirt<BR>
   
   Kitchen scraps<BR>
   
   Logs<BR>
   
   Pet feces<BR>
   
   Sand<BR>
   
   Stumps<BR>
   
   Sod with dirt<BR>
   
   Trash (litter, plastic garden pots ...etc.)
</UL>

<P>
<HR>
Updated Monday, 25 November 1996.</P>
</BODY>
</HTML>
