<html><head><title>Vouchers</title></head><body>City of Minneapolis, Division of Solid Waste & Recycling<H2>VOUCHERS</H2><p><HR width=100%><p>With a voucher, a Solid Waste & Recycling customer is able to drop-off at our South Transfer Station, tires, garbage, or construction and paving materials at no additional charge.<p>Without a voucher, normal prices are:<pre>    $76/ton   Garbage <br>    $76/ton   Construction and paving materials<br>    $2/each   Tires</pre><p>Vouchers are only for materials from properties with Minneapolis Solid Waste & Recycling service. Items from other properties will be charged the prices listed above.<HR width=100%><p><b>GETTING A VOUCHER</b><p>Call Solid Waste and Recycling at 673-2917 to obtain your voucher.<p>Because of the large number of people using vouchers, you must choose a specific date to use the voucher. Please have your date ready when you call Solid Waste & Recycling at 673-2917.<p>Each property with our service is currently allowed to use two of each type of voucher per year. <p>However, you cannot use two vouchers of the same type on the same day. For example, you can use a clean-up voucher and a tire voucher on the same day, but not two clean-up vouchers.<HR width=100%><p><b>GUIDELINES FOR USING VOUCHERS</b><p>There are three types of vouchers. Click on any of the times below for specific information about using that voucher.<ul><li><a HREF=#clean-up>Clean-up</a> (excess garbage)<li><a HREF=#construction>Construction & Paving Materials</a><li><a HREF=#tire>Tire</a></ul><HR width=100%><p><b><a name=clean-up>CLEAN-UP VOUCHER</a> </b><ul><li><b>Identification:</b><br>Along with your voucher, you must present proof of ownership or residence:<br>- Residents: bring a valid drivers license which has the serviced address.<br>- Owners: bring a valid drivers license and a utility bill or property tax statement with the owner's name matching the drivers license.<p><li><b>Loads</b><br>Only one load per voucher (because of the computer and scale system).<p>Also, you cannot have one load and use multiple vouchers of the same type.  For example, a truck with one load of 4000 lbs of concrete cannot use two clean-up vouchers.<p><li><b>Vehicles: </b><br>A car, truck, or rented truck are all okay, and trailers are acceptable.  No commercial hauling vehicles (packers, semis, roll-offs ..etc) may be accepted at the South Transfer station.<p><li><b>Specifics:</b><ul><li>Auto parts such as car seats, fenders, hoods are accepted. Please keep these auto parts separate from household garbage.<p><b>No</b> auto parts that held fluids such as auto batteries, air conditioners, differentials, gas tanks, oil filters, oil pans, radiators, shocks & struts, or torque convertors.<p><li>Limited amounts of construction material are accepted.  However, if it is more than 20% of the load, there will be a charge for the construction materials. <p><li>Large items are accepted, but not from commercial uses.  You will have to unload these as the transfer station attendant directs.<p><li>Stumps, and logs greater than 3" in diameter are accepted.  You must be able to lift and place these where the attendant directs.  Grass, leaves, brush and other yard waste will not be accepted.</ul><p><li><b>Limit:</b><br>2000 lbs limit per voucher, there will be a charge for any amount over 2000 lbs.<p>Charge for excess garbage is $76/ton with a minimum charge of $30.40 for amounts of 1-800 lbs.  </ul><p><HR width=100%><p><b><a name=construction>CONSTRUCTION & PAVING VOUCHER</a></b><p><ul><li><b>Identification:</b><br>Along with your voucher, you must present proof of ownership or residence:<br>- Residents: bring a valid drivers license which has the serviced address.<br>- Owners: bring a valid drivers license and a utility bill or property tax statement with the owner's name matching the drivers license.<p><li><b>Loads</b><br>Only one load per voucher (because of the computer and scale system).<p>Also, you cannot have one load and use multiple vouchers of the same type.  For example, a truck with one load of 4000 lbs of concrete cannot use two Paving & Construction vouchers.<p><li><b>Vehicles: </b><br>A car, truck, or rented truck are all okay, and trailers are acceptable.  No commercial hauling vehicles (packers, semis, roll-offs ..etc) may be accepted at the South Transfer station.<p><li><b>Specifics:</b><ul><li>Separate materials into the following catagories:<ul>- lumber<br>- other building materials (sheetrock, plaster, shingles...etc)<br>- Paving materials (asphalt, brick, concrete, rock ...etc)</ul>Loads must be dumped as directed by the attedant.<p><li>No railroad ties or asbestos insulation.  Green treated lumber is accepted.</ul><p><li><b>Limit:</b><br>2000 lbs limit per voucher, there will be a charge for any amount over 2000 lbs.<p>Charge for excess materials is $76/ton with a minimum charge of $30.40 for amounts of 1-800 lbs. </ul><HR width=100%><b><a name=tire>TIRE VOUCHER</a></b><p><ul><li><b>Identification:</b><br>Along with your voucher, you must present proof of ownership or residence:<br>- Residents: bring a valid drivers license which has the serviced address.<br>- Owners: bring a valid drivers license and a utility bill or property tax statement with the owner's name matching the drivers license.<p><li><b>Loads</b><br>Only one load of tires per voucher. No more than one tire voucher per day.<p><li><b>Specifics:</b><br>Eight tires maximum at no charge. Any extra tires at $2 per tire.<p>No need to remove rims.</ul><HR width=100%><p><b>DIRECTIONS</b><p>The South Transfer Station at 2850 20th Ave South, just northwest of Hiawatha and Lake Street.<p>Go to Lake Street and 21st Ave South (there is a Burger King on the corner.)Go north one block to 29th Street.Turn left and go straight until 29th Street ends.<p><HR width=100%><p>Updated Monday, 20 May 1996.</body></html>
