</DOCHDR>
<html><head><TITLE>Neighborhood Clean Sweeps</TITLE></head><body>City of Minneapolis, Division of Solid Waste & Recycling<p><H2>NEIGHBORHOOD CLEAN SWEEPS</H2><p><HR width=100%><p>Clean Sweeps are Saturday clean-up events organized by registered neighborhood groups and assisted by Minneapolis Solid Waste & Recycling. <p>Neighborhood groups provide promotion and volunteers to help load materials. Solid Waste & Recycling provides a packer truck and pays disposal fees. This is a good opportunity for elderly residents to get assistance from their neighbors. <p>If you are interested in assisting with a clean sweep, contact your local neighborhood group.<p><HR width=100%><p><b>1996 NEIGHBORHOOD CLEAN SWEEP SCHEDULE</b><p><pre>Neighborhood                 Date           Contact Person    Phone #------------------------------------------------------------------------------Audubon                     May 4              Chris Grams   788-8790Bancroft                   June 22             Tim Gehring   823-6015Bryant                     June 22            Trudy Fuller   824-3453Carag                      June 8           Heidi Mitchell   825-9191Cedar-Isles-Dean          Cancelled          Pat Provinske   925-1621------------------------------------------------------------------------------Central                   April 27               Bob Allen   822-3302Cleveland                  July 20             Brigid Shea   529-4073Corcoran                    May 11            Julie Niccum   724-7457Diamond Lake               June 29           Linda Roberts   824-7707East Isles                 Sept 14                Pat Egan   377-7686------------------------------------------------------------------------------Elliot Park                 May 11             Lori Ricker   335-5846Fulton                     June 29             Ronald King   922-5536Hale                       June 29           Linda Roberts   824-7707Harrison                    May 