<HEAD>

<TITLE>Holiday Schedule</TITLE>
</HEAD>


<BODY>
<P>City of Minneapolis, Division of Solid Waste &amp; Recycling</P>
<p>
<H2>1996 Holiday Schedule</H2>

<HR width=100%>
When your regular collection day falls on or after New Years Day, Memorial Day, Fourth of July, Labor Day, Thanksgiving Day, or Christmas Day, your garbage, large items, recyclables, and yard waste will be collected one day later than normal 
<P>
<B>November 11</B> -- Collection of garbage, large items, recyclables, and yard waste is unchanged. South Transfer Station open. Office closed.
<P>
<B>November 28</B> -- No collection. South Transfer Station closed. Office closed.
<P>
<B>November 29</B> -- Collection of garbage, large items, recyclables, and yard waste will be one day later than normal for the remainder of the week. South Transfer Station open. Office open from 9:00 am - 12:00 pm.
<P>
<B>December 25</B> -- No collection. South Transfer Station closed. Office closed.
<P>
<B>December 26</B> -- Collection of garbage, large items, and recyclables will be one day later than normal for the remainder of the week. South Transfer Station open. Office open.
<P>

<HR width=100%>
Updated Monday, 11 November 1996.

</BODY>
