<P>City of Minneapolis, Division of Solid Waste &amp; Recycling</P>

<H2>Motor Oil and Oil Filter Drop-offs</H2>

<P>
<HR>
</P>

<P>It is illegal to dispose of motor oil and filters in the garbage
or in storm sewers. An oil filter contains about one cup of oil even
after draining. A single cup of motor oil is enough to contaminate
62,000 gallons of drinking water.</P>

<P>Fortunately, the locations below accept both motor oil and motor
oil filters, at no charge, from Minneapolis residents. These
drop-offs are for residential use only. So limit oil to five gallons
at a time. Do not mix oil with other auto fluids such as antifreeze.
Please drop-off oil and filters during business hours only. For
questions about hours, call the phone numbers listed below.</P>

<P>Also, if you decide to have your motor oil and filter changed,
please visit one of the locations listed below.</P>

