<HTML>
<HEAD>

<TITLE>Attorney</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Attorney"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Attorney</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The City Attorney's Office has a Civil Division and a Criminal Division. The
Civil Division protects the legal interests of the City by providing legal
counsel and representation to the City of Minneapolis and its elected and
appointed officials, departments, and commissions in all litigation and legal
matters. This division also drafts ordinances, resolutions, contracts and other
necessary documents. The Criminal Division reviews and prosecutes misdemeanor and
gross misdemeanor offenses against persons or property within the City of
Minneapolis including the University of Minnesota, Minneapolis Park land and the
airport.

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>City Attorney's Office</B><BR>
Metropolitan Centre, Suite 300<BR>
333 7 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55402-2453
</ADDRESS>

<P><B>Phone Number</B><BR>
(612) 673-2010<BR>


