<HEAD>

<TITLE>City Clerk</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="City Clerk"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>City Clerk</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Office of the City Clerk serves the public in the following ways: 
<UL>
  <LI>Records proceedings of <A HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City
Council</A> and City Council committee meetings and prepares them for publication
in <A HREF="http://www.finance-commerce.com/pubnot/city.htm"><CITE>Finance
and Commerce</CITE> </A>. 
  <LI>Files City records for public access. 
  <LI>Responds to requests for information about ordinances and resolutions
and <A HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City Council</A> actions.
You can browse and search City ordinances at the <A HREF="mcchelp/mcchelp.html">Municipal
Code Corporation</A> website. 
  <LI>Handles applications for special permits. 
  <LI>Maintains voter registration files and prepares ballot equipment and
polling places for operation on election day. 
  <LI>Assists the <A HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City Council</A>
in drafting proposed legislation for the City and lobbying for it at the
legislature. 
  <LI>Assists senior citizens with questions and problems and provides direct
help to seniors needing assistance with tax forms. 
  <LI>Staffs the Charter Commission. 
  <LI>Administers open appointments for City boards, commissions and committees.
  <LI>Manages the Municipal Information Library, a collection of resources
on local issues, urban development and neighborhood studies. The public
is invited to use these resources in the library's reading room. 
  <LI>Accepts claims filed against the City. 
  <LI>Issues encroachments. 
  <LI>Issues block party permits. 
  <LI>Issues street and alley vacations. 
  <LI>Schedules hearings for the Board of Equalization regarding property
values. 
  <LI>Registers domestic partners. 
  <LI>Provides records retention and disposal of city records. 
  <LI>Publishes weekly and monthly calendar of the <A HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City
Council</A> and its committees, and official meetings of other boards and
commissions. 
  <LI>Administers the Oath of Office to persons appointed to boards and
commissions. 
  <LI>Publishes notices of public hearings for City Council committees.
</UL>
<HR>
