<HEAD>

<TITLE>Civil Rights</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Civil Rights"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Civil Rights</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Minneapolis Department of Civil Rights investigates complaints of
discrimination in Minneapolis. Complaints must be filed within one year of the
alleged discrimination.

<P>The Department also monitors contractors with City contracts in excess of
&#36;50,000 to ensure that they are in compliance with equal opportunity and
affirmative action guidelines.

<P>The Department provides educational services about civil rights. For speakers,
videos, literature and other materials about civil rights issues, call (612)
673-2582. Watch for the program Your Civil Rights on public access television,
<STRONG>City Cable 34</STRONG>.

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Minneapolis Department of Civil Rights</B><BR>
City Hall, Room 239<BR>
350 5 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415-1371
</ADDRESS>

<P><B>Phone Number</B><BR>
(612) 673-3012


