<HEAD>

<TITLE>Civilian Police Review Authority</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Civilian Police Review Authority"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Civilian Police Review Authority</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Minneapolis Civilian Police Review Authority investigates complaints of
misconduct against Minneapolis police officers. The authority, which is
completely independent of the <A
HREF="/departments/police/index.html">Minneapolis Police Department</A>, has its
own staff of investigators. If complaints are sustained after the investigation
and after an administrative hearing, the authority sends its findings to the
Chief of Police for appropriate discipline of the officers involved. Upon the
agreement of the complainant and the officer, the complaint may be resolved in
mediation.

<P>Both victims and witnesses of alleged police misconduct may file a complaint.
Misconduct includes excessive force, inappropriate language or attitude, theft by
an officer, harassment, failure to provide adequate or timely police protection,
or discrimination on the basis of protected-class status.

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Civilian Police Review Authority</B><BR>
Suite 452<BR>
1111 3 Av S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55404-1008
</ADDRESS>

<P><B>Phone Number</B><BR>
(612) 348-9390 


