<HTML>
<HEAD>

<TITLE>Communications</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Communications"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Communications</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Communications Division of the <A
HREF="/departments/city-coordinator/index.html">City Coordinator's Office</A>
supervises <A HREF="opa.html">Public Affairs</A>; the Grants and Special
Projects Office, which includes the Arts Commission, International Trade, and
International Relationships; and Media Services.

<H3><BR>Grants and Special Projects</H3>
<P>The grants function maximizes the City's financial resources by obtaining
funding from non-property tax sources for programs and projects that are
consistent with City goals. Staff members prepare and submit applications for
annual federal grants and also assist departments in preparing and submitting
applications for one-time or special opportunity grants.

<P>The special projects function identifies and solicits special events to be
held in the Twin Cities, e.g., the Super Bowl and Special Olympics. Staff members
also assist with fundraising for and coordination of special events.

<H3><BR>Arts Commission</H3>
<P>The purpose of the Arts Commission is to work with the arts community, city
government, and neighborhood and community organizations to develop programs and
policies that benefit the arts and the city. The commission fosters the
development of the arts, seeks financial support for the arts, and stimulates
participation and appreciation of the arts by all Minneapolis residents.

<H3><BR>International Trade</H3>
<P>The International Trade Office is jointly funded by the City and <A
HREF="http://www.co.hennepin.mn.us">Hennepin County</A> to attract and coordinate
resources to enhance the global competitiveness of Minneapolis and Hennepin
County for the expansion of economic opportunity. Services offered include
computerized trade leads information, an electronic bulletin board with market
research information, a directory of business services, and public education
seminars about international trade.

<H3><BR>International Relationships</H3>
<P>The International Relationships Coordinator assists in the maintenance of the
City's &quot;Sister City&quot; relationships, arranges visits of city officials
to other countries, assists with visits of foreign officials and delegations to
Minneapolis, maintains the City's gift inventory, and organizes the annual
International Citizen of the Year Award dinner.

<H3><BR>Media Services</H3>
<P><STRONG>City Cable 34</STRONG> is the City's cable TV station. It provides
timely and accurate information about City issues and services to the citizens of
Minneapolis.

<P>Programs include live coverage of <A
HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">Minneapolis City Council</A>
meetings; <CITE>City Beat</CITE>, a discussion of City Council issues;
<CITE>Public Health Journal</CITE>, information on health issues; <CITE>Your
Civil Rights</CITE>, information about residents' rights; <CITE>Artifacts</CITE>,
highlighting local artists and arts issues; <CITE>Twin Cities 10 Most
Wanted</CITE>, a Crime Stoppers program encouraging citizen involvement in
solving crimes and apprehending criminals; and <CITE>The Mayor's
Roundtable</CITE>.

<P>To request a program guide or leave comments, call the <STRONG>City Cable 34</STRONG> Hotline,
(612) 673-2234. For program information, call (612) 673-2911.

<P>Media Services also coordinates with the <A
HREF="http://www.mtn.org">Minneapolis Telecommunications Network (MTN)</A>, which
provides cable access to the public. MTN can be reached at (612) 331-8575.

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Communications</B><BR>
City Hall, Room 301M<BR>
350 5 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415-1376
</ADDRESS>

<P><BR><B>Phone Numbers</B>
<PRE>
