<HEAD>

<TITLE>Contract Management</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Contract Management"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Contract Management</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Office of Contract Management, a division of <A
HREF="index.html">Neighborhood Services</A>, provides the following services:

<OL TYPE="1">
	<LI>Drafts and processes all contracts for the Department of Neighborhood
	Services;
	<LI>Administers all CDBG contracts by processing payments and monitoring
	their progress;
	<LI>Acts as a liaison between the City and HUD on all approved CDBG and
	UDAG projects;
	<LI>Enforces City and HUD Labor Standards Requirements.
</UL>

<H3><BR>Community Development Block Grants</H3>

<P><I><B>PLEASE NOTE:</B> Primary funding comes through federal and state
governments. Allocations, eligibility and program services are controlled by
granting agency. Funding changes yearly. A portion of CDBG funds, approximately
&#36;2 million annually, partially funds human service programs for low- and
moderate-income city residents.</I>

<P>Services supported this year are:

<DL>
	<DT><B>Minneapolis Community Clinics</B>
	<DD>Primary and preventive health care to individuals and families at Fremont
	Community Health Center, Cedar-Riverside Peoples Center, Health Etc./CUHCC,
	Southside Community Clinic, Teenage Medical Center, Uptown Community Clinic,
	and Central Avenue Clinic. For information, call (612) 588-9411.

	<DT><BR><B>Minneapolis Urban League Labor Education Advancement Program</B>
	<DD>Preparation and placement of city residents in registered apprenticeship
	programs. For information, call (612) 521-0399.

	<DT><BR><B>Minneapolis Age and Opportunity Center</B>
	<DD>Home care services, transportation, legal assistance, and home delivered
	meals to senior citizens. For information, call (612) 863-1066.

	<DT><BR><B>Parents in Community Action Head Start</B>
	<DD>Day care, child and family development, and education services for
	preschool children and their families. For information, call (612) 823-6361.

	<DT><BR><B>Greater Minneapolis Day Care Association</B>
	<DD>Funds partial subsidy of the sliding-fee child-care program. Licensed
	day-care centers and homes provide direct child care. For information, call
	(612) 341-1177.

	<DT><BR><B>Legal Aid Society of Minneapolis</B>
	<DD>Legal services and court representation on civil cases to low-income
	residents at the Northside and Southside Legal Aid offices. For information,
	call (612) 332-1441.

	<DT><BR><B>Loring Nicollet Bethlehem Community Centers MERC</B>
	<DD>Alternative education and part-time work opportunities for youth. For
	information, call (612) 871-2031.

	<DT><BR><B>Harriet Tubman Women's Shelter</B>
	<DD>Emergency shelter, advocacy, and referral for battered women and their
	children. For information, call (612) 827-6105.

	<DT><BR><B>Minneapolis Health Department Maternal and Child Health</B>
	<DD>For information, call (612) 673-2963.
</DL>

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Contract Management</B><BR>
City Hall, Room 321M<BR>
350 5 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415-1315
</ADDRESS>

<P><B>Phone Number</B><BR>
(612) 673-3350


