<HEAD>

<TITLE>Emergency Communications Center</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Emergency Communications Center"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Emergency Communications Center</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Emergency Communications Center (ECC) is staffed 24 hours a day every day
of the year. The ECC receives calls from citizens via both <B>9-1-1</B> and
conventional telephone numbers. Calls are screened to determine the need for
police, fire, and/or ambulance assistance and if a response is necessary,
department staff takes steps to dispatch the proper City <A
HREF="/departments/police/index.html">police</A> or <A
HREF="/departments/fire/index.html">fire</A> personnel.

<P>The department uses a call prioritization and classification system to insure
that those needing help most urgently get the fastest possible response. This is
necessary because during periods of peak activity, there are often more calls
awaiting service than there are available police squad cars to send.

<P>An advanced computer system is used to help employees inventory the calls that
are received and organize them for dispatch and later retrieval. All telephone
and radio conversations involving ECC operations are tape recorded and strict
attention to accuracy, speed and quality are maintained. More than 80 civilian
employees staff the ECC.

<P>ECC also provides Tele-serv, a system whereby the victims of crimes such as
thefts can make reports via telephone of crimes that do not require a police
response to the scene.

<P><I><B>NOTE:</B> As of January 1, 1996, the Tele-serv unit has been placed
under the <A HREF="/departments/police/index.html">Minneapolis Police
Department</A>.  The transfer of Tele-serv will be phased in over the next couple
of months.</I>

<P>Tours of the ECC are available by arrangement.

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Emergency Communications Center</B><BR>
City Hall, Room B911<BR>
350 5 St S<BR>
Minneaoplis, MN 55415-1318
</ADDRESS>

<P><BR><B>Phone Numbers</B>
<PRE>
