<HEAD>

<TITLE>Employment &amp; Training</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Employment &amp; Training"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Employment &amp; Training</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P><EM><B>PLEASE NOTE:</B> Primary funding comes through federal and state
governments. Allocations, eligibility, and program services are controlled by
granting agency. Funding changes yearly. METP is a division of <A
HREF="index.html">Neighborhood Services</A>.</EM>

<H3><BR>ADULT EMPLOYMENT AND TRAINING PROGRAMS</H3>

<P>Adult Employment and Training Programs provide assistance to city residents in
finding and retaining employment or pursuing vocational training which will lead
to a job. Most programs have a family income test to determine eligibility.
Service providers are:

<PRE>
Anishinabe Council of Job Developers               2309 Nicollet Av S       (612) 870-7281
Centre for Asians and Pacific Islanders            2200 Franklin Av E       (612) 672-0123
Coyle Center                                        420 15 Av S             (612) 338-5282
East Side Neighborhood Services                    1929 2 St NE             (612) 781-6011
HIRED                                               310 38 St E             (612) 822-9071
Loring Nicollet Bethlehem Center                   1925 Nicollet Av S       (612) 871-2031
Minneapolis Age and Opportunity Center             1801 Nicollet Av S       (612) 863-1000 (age 55 or more)
Minneapolis Urban League                           2000 Plymouth Av N       (612) 521-0342
Phillips Community Development Corporation         1014 Franklin Av E       (612) 871-2122
Twin Cities Opportunities Industrialization Center  935 Olson Memorial Hwy  (612) 377-0150
Unity Center                                       2507 Fremont Av N        (612) 529-9267
</PRE>

<P>The STRIDE program offers employment and training resources and case
management services to eligible AFDC recipients. Providers of STRIDE services
are:

<PRE>
Catholic Charities                                 2104 Stevens Av S        (612) 872-8777
Centre for Asians and Pacific Islanders            2200 Franklin Av E       (612) 672-0123
