Loring Nicollet Bethlehem Center                   1925 Nicollet Av S       (612) 871-2031
Minneapolis Urban League                           2000 Plymouth Av N       (612) 521-0342
                                                   2929 4 Av S              (612) 822-3645
New Chance                                          310 38 St E             (612) 823-5393
Parents In Community Action                         700 Humboldt Av N       (612) 377-7422
Project Self-Sufficiency                            600 18 Av N             (612) 521-1360
Sumner-Olson Resident Council                       900 8 Av N              (612) 342-1535
Twin Cities Opportunities Industrialization Center  935 Olson Memorial Hwy  (612) 377-0150
Unity Center                                       2507 Fremont Av N        (612) 529-9267
WINGS                                              3650 Fremont Av N        (612) 521-8750
                                                   3702 Lake St E           (612) 721-2714
</PRE>

<H3><BR>YOUTH EMPLOYMENT AND TRAINING PROGRAMS</H3>

<P>Youth programs offer full-time, part-time, permanent, and seasonal job
opportunities for Minneapolis youth.

<P>The Year-Round Youth Program offers permanent, part-time employment
opportunities for high school students who are members of families receiving
public assistance or have a family income below the poverty level. Services are
provided by a network of community agencies:

<PRE>
American Indian OIC                      1845 Franklin Av E   (612) 341-3358
Coyle Center                              420 15 Av S         (612) 338-5282
Centre for Asians and Pacific Islanders  2200 Franklin Av E   (612) 672-0123
Centro Cultural Chicano                  2201 Nicollet Av S   (612) 874-1412
Employment Action Center                  310 38 St E         (612) 823-5393
Greater Minneapolis Chamber of Commerce    81 9 St S          (612) 370-9168
Loring Nicollet Bethlehem Center         1925 Nicollet Av S   (612) 871-2031
Sumner-Olson Resident Council             900 8 Av N          (612) 342-1944
The City, Inc.                           1545 Lake St E       (612) 724-3689
YMCA Blaisdell                           3335 Blaisdell Av S  (612) 827-5401
</PRE>

<P>The Summer Youth Employment Program provides summer, full-time employment for
high school students from low-income families. Applications are available in
junior and senior high schools beginning in mid-March.

<P>The Transitional Work Internship Program provides a high support,
case-managed, six-month employment internship with City or County government. The
program leads to full-time, permanent employment or further education. For more
information, call (612) 673-5700.

<H3><BR>DISLOCATED WORKER PROGRAMS</H3>

<P>Dislocated worker programs provide employment and training assistance to
former employees of Minneapolis businesses who have lost their jobs due to a
plant closing or permanent layoff. Initial services are provided by the
Minneapolis Job Service:

<PRE>
North Office  1200 Plymouth Av N  (612) 520-3500
South Office   777 Lake St E      (612) 821-4000
</PRE>

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Employment &amp; Training</B><BR>
City Hall, Room 310 1/2<BR>
350 5 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415-1388
</ADDRESS>

<P><B>Phone Number</B><BR>
(612) 673-5700


