<HEAD>

<TITLE>Energy &amp; Environment</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Energy &amp; Environment"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Energy &amp; Environment</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Center for Energy and Environment (CEE), a division of <A
HREF="index.html">Neighborhood Services</A>, is a nonprofit corporation which
offers energy conservation and environmental programs to Minneapolis residents.
These programs include:

<DL>
	<DT><B>Operation Insulation</B>
	<DD>An easy, guaranteed program for major weatherization work such as
	insulation, house doctoring and furnace replacement. For information, call
	(612) 348-4367.

	<DT><BR><B>Project Choice</B>
	<DD>A successful program for low-income households (185&#37; of poverty level)
	providing energy education, energy bill budgeting and low-cost
	weatherization. For information, call (612) 348-4367.

	<DT><BR><B>Energy Bank</B>
	<DD>A consumer-friendly program providing low-interest financing of up to
	&#36;7,000 (no income limits) to homeowners and rental owners for energy
	conservation improvements. For information, call (612) 348-4834.

	<DT><BR><B>Multifamily Program</B>
	<DD>A cost-effective program, based on research and testing, that provides
	boiler controls training for maintenance personnel, energy consultants, and
	the easy installation of energy efficient measures in apartment buildings.
	For information, call (612) 348-4367.

	<DT><BR><B>Fluorescent Lighting Installation Program</B>
	<DD>A program to install high-efficiency lighting in businesses. Low interest
	financing with variable terms and competitive product pricing makes the
	installation of new lighting easy and affordable. For information, call (612)
	348-4367.
</DL>

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Center for Energy &amp; Environment</B><BR>
Butler Square, Suite 412A<BR>
100 6 St N<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55403-1520
</ADDRESS>


