<HEAD>

<TITLE>Human Resources</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Human Resources"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Human Resources</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Human Resources Department is a consolidated unit which includes <A
HREF="personnel.html">Personnel Services (Civil Service)</A>, Labor Relations and
Employee Benefits, Management Development and Training, Affirmative Action, Risk
Management, and the Urban Corps Intern Program, providing a full range of support
services for all classified and unclassified personnel for all <A
HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City Council</A> departments. In
addition, the Personnel Services Division provides services to the <A
HREF="/departments/other/parks.html">Park and Recreation Board</A>, <A
HREF="/departments/other/library.html">Library Board</A>, and Board of Education.

<P>The services provided include:

<UL>
	<LI>labor contract negotiations
	<LI>contract administration
	<LI>employee benefits
	<LI>employee relations
	<LI>workforce diversity/goal setting and monitoring
	<LI>recruitment
	<LI>selection
	<LI>testing/tutoring programs
	<LI>job classification
	<LI>record maintenance and audit
	<LI>other personnel related programs
	<LI>OSHA compliance
	<LI>workers compensation monitoring
	<LI>safety programs
	<LI>performance appraisal
	<LI>executive recruiting
	<LI>management training programs
	<LI>upward Mobility
</UL>

<P>The overall objective is to attract and retain a qualified workforce that is
representative of a diverse community in order to deliver services to the
citizens of Minneapolis.

<P>The responsibilities are implemented through the <A
HREF="/departments/city-coordinator/index.html">City Coordinator</A>, Civil
Service Commission, and appropriate City Council committees and independent
boards.

<P>

<HR>

