<HEAD>

<TITLE>Information &amp; Technology Services</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Information &amp; Technology Services"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Information &amp; Technology Services</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Information and Technology Services (ITS) department provides hardware and
software in support of application systems used by <A
HREF="/departments/city-coordinator/finance/index.html">Finance</A>, Utility
Billing, <A HREF="/departments/police/index.html">Police</A>, <A
HREF="/departments/fire/index.html">Fire</A>, <A
HREF="/departments/city-coordinator/operations/inspections/index.html">Inspections</A>,
and other departments.

<P>ITS also provides PC/LAN support services and data entry services for <A
HREF="/departments/index.html">City departments</A>.

<DL>
	<DT><B>CityNet</B>
	<DD>ITS is spearheading a project to unify the City's computer systems into a
	single network. The project will streamline information transfer, help avoid
	duplication of work and limit data errors.

	<DT><BR><B>FISCOL</B>
	<DD>ITS is working closely with the <A
	HREF="/departments/city-coordinator/finance/index.html">Minneapolis Finance
	Department</A> to implement FISCOL, the City's new financial accounting
	system.

	<DT><BR><B>Telephone Management</B>
	<DD>The Client Services office manages the City's phone system. Operators at
	the City Information Center answer a thousand calls per day from citizens
	needing phone numbers for anything from auto theft to zoning, as well as
	Minneapolis employee listings and general information. City information can
	be reached at (612) 673-3000 from 8 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Monday through
	Friday.<BR>
	<BR>
	<STRONG>City Line</STRONG>, the City's 24-hour automated phone service, is
	available by calling (612) 673-CITY (2489).
</DL>

<H3><BR>SERVICES FOR HEARING IMPAIRED PEOPLE</H3>

<P>The Client Services office provides sign language interpreting services and
houses the general City Information Telecommunications Device for the Deaf to
enable hearing-impaired people to access City information and services. To
request an interpreter, call (612) 673-3220. To access the TDD, call (612)
673-2157.

<H3><BR>SERVICES FOR NON-ENGLISH SPEAKING RESIDENTS</H3>

<P>The City Information Center can answer calls from non-English speaking
residents by connecting them to an interpreter. The center's hours are 8 a.m. to
4:30 p.m., Monday through Friday. Call (612) 673-3000.

<H3><BR>CABLE TV OVERSIGHT</H3>

<P>ITS monitors the city's cable company, Paragon. Complaints concerning Paragon
are handled by the office at (612) 673-2767.

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Information & Technology Services</B><BR>
Hennepin County Government Center, Room A25<BR>
300 6 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415-1323
</ADDRESS>

<P><BR><B>Phone Numbers</B>
<PRE>
City operators                         (612) 673-3000
City Line (24-hour automated service)  (612) 673-CITY
ITS                                    (612) 673-3190
</PRE>


