<HEAD>

<TITLE>Intergovernmental Relations</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Intergovernmental Relations"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Intergovernmental Relations</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Intergovernmental Relations Department has a federal legislative liaison,
a state legislative liaison, and a local government relations representative.

<P>The federal liaison lobbies the federal legislative process to maximize the
advantages to the City resulting from federal programs. The federal liaison
communicates regularly with federal elected officials and local elected
officials, exchanging information to keep them up-to-date with issues that have
an impact on the City. The federal liaison also provides information about
federal bills, hearings, regulations, reports, studies, agencies, national
organizations, and Congressional and Cabinet members.

<P>The state liaison coordinates the representation of the City before the state
government. The state liaison analyzes and researches legislative proposals,
proposes policy alternatives to the IGR Committee, keeps elected officials and
department heads informed of legislative activity, summarizes legislative
enactments affecting the City, and identifies future major issues on which the
City should take a position.

<P>The local government relations representative acts as a liaison with
metropolitan and local units of government. Metropolitan governments include the
Metro Council and the regional operating commissions. Local units of government
include both other cities and <A HREF="http://www.co.hennepin.mn.us">Hennepin
County</A>. This function also includes participation in such organizations as
the Association of Metropolitan Municipalities and the League of Minnesota
Cities. This position provides policy analysis on infrastructure issues,
financial issues, parks, recycling, and other issues.

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Intergovernmental Relations</B><BR>
City Hall, Room 325M<BR>
350 5 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415-1315
</ADDRESS>

<P><B>Phone Number</B><BR>
(612) 673-2043


<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_foot.incl" -->
