<HEAD>

<TITLE>Licenses &amp; Consumer Services</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Licenses &amp; Consumer Services"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Licenses &amp; Consumer Services</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>Licenses and Consumer Services, a division of <A HREF="index.html">Operations
and Regulatory Services</A>, is charged with protecting the health, welfare, and
safety of the Minneapolis citizens through a program of regulation, inspection,
testing, and enforcement of laws and ordinances pertaining to licensing
businesses, traffic control, weights and measures, trucking enforcement, and
consumer protection.

<P>The Licensing division has two main areas of service responsibility licenses
and consumer services and traffic control.

<H3><BR>LICENSES AND CONSUMER SERVICES</H3>

<P>This section provides inspections, investigations, and regulations of
approximately 120 licensed activities including:

<UL>
	<LI>mediation of homeowner/building contractor disputes
	<LI>taxicab service issues
	<LI>liquor and entertainment facility regulation
	<LI>towing regulation
	<LI>beautification and regulation of auto-related uses
</UL>

<P>Other services provided by this department include:

<UL>
	<LI>monitoring and enforcing truck routes and illegal truck parking
	<LI>investigating and eliminating home-based illegal industry
	<LI>administering 25,000 annual licenses
</UL>

<P>Many business and service activities conducted within the city require
licensing. Additionally, private citizens require licenses for things such as
pets and guns.

<H3><BR>TRAFFIC CONTROL</H3>

<P>The traffic control section provides traffic control during rush hours
downtown and for the Metrodome, <A HREF="convention.html">Convention Center</A>,
and Target Center; monitors all parking meters in the City; and provides
enforcement during street cleaning and snow emergencies.

<P>Services they can provide include:

<UL>
	<LI>Tagging and having towed illegally parked vehicles such as those blocking driveways
	<LI>Removal of abandoned vehicles
	<LI>Information and explanation of City parking regulations.
</UL>

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Licenses &amp; Consumer Services</B><BR>
City Hall, Room 1C<BR>
350 5 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415-1391
</ADDRESS>

<P><BR><B>Phone Numbers</B>
<PRE>
For information on licensing                   (612) 673-2080
For pet licenses                               (612) 673-2050
For traffic control services                   (612) 348-2052
Snow emergency parking regulations             (612) 348-SNOW
To find out if a car has been towed            (612) 673-5777
  <I>be sure to have car license number</I>
To contest the tagging or towing of a vehicle  (612) 348-2040
</PRE>


