<HEAD>

<TITLE>Mayor's Office</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Mayor's Office"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Mayor's Office</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Mayor's functions:
<UL>
	<P><LI>The Mayor outlines ideas for the current year and goals for the next
	year to the <A HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City Council</A>
	in the annual State of the City address (required by the <CITE>City
	Charter</CITE>). The Mayor also submits a budget proposal to the Council and
	the Directions Framework, a policy guide for the City's operating, capital
	improvement and community development programs.

	<P><LI>City Council actions and <A HREF="/departments/other/parks.html">Park
	and Recreation Board</A> actions are subject to the Mayor's approval.

	<P><LI>Recent Charter changes have given the Mayor more authority to hire and
	terminate the employment of heads of the City's charter-designated
	departments. In practice the Mayor consults with the City Council on such
	decisions. The Charter charges the Mayor with oversight of the <A
	HREF="/departments/police/index.html">Police Department</A>.

	<P><LI>The Mayor makes appointments to a number of City boards, committees,
	and task forces. Some appointments are made solely by the Mayor; some are
	made in conjunction with the City Council.

	<P><LI>The Mayor often represents the City on ceremonial occasions.

	<P><LI>The Mayor is an institutional member of the following boards and
	committees: <A HREF="/departments/other/taxation.html">Board of Estimate and
	Taxation</A>, Municipal Employees Retirement Fund Board, Municipal Building
	Commission, Youth Coordinating Board, Minneapolis Convention and Visitors
	Commission, City Council Executive Committee, Saint Anthony Falls Heritage
	Zone Board.
</UL>

<P>Services the Mayor's Office provides:
<UL>
	<P><LI>Information about the City's functions and operations.

	<P><LI>Referrals to appropriate departments and agencies.

	<P><LI>Permits for parades and street races (bicycle races, marathons, etc.).

	<P><LI>Mayoral greetings to appropriate groups and meetings.

	<P><LI>Proclamations (Minneapolis Arbor Day, Jane Doe Day in Minneapolis,
	etc.) The Mayor provides this service for legitimate requests. Citizens may
	provide the text of the proclamation, or staff can help write a proclamation.

	<P><LI>Scheduling the Mayor's appearances.

	<P><LI>Response to citizen concerns about City affairs.

	<P><LI>Other initiatives.

	<P><LI>The Mayor's Office has occasionally housed new initiatives which
	eventually become non-profit organizations in their own right, or go out of
	existence after serving their function. The office currently houses the
	Neighborhood Employment Network. Its operations are funded with non-city
	funds.
</UL>

<P>Staff includes the Chief of Staff, the Executive Secretary, five aides, five
secretarial and clerical employees, student interns as available, and a TWIP
intern.

<P>

<HR>

<P>The Mayor of Minneapolis is Sharon Sayles Belton.

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Mayor's Office</B><BR>
City Hall, Room 331<BR>
350 5 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415-1315
</ADDRESS>

<P><B>Phone Number</B><BR>
(612) 673-2100


