<TITLE>Operations &amp; Regulatory Services</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Operations &amp; Regulatory Services"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Operations &amp; Regulatory Services</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Operations Division of the <A
HREF="/departments/city-coordinator/index.html">City Coordinator's Office</A> is
responsible for the supervision and management of Regulatory Services Divisions
including the Convention Center, Inspections, and Licenses &amp; Consumer
Services. In addition, communications issues, Facility Coordination (Space
Planning), and the Americans with Disabilities Act are administered by the
Director of Operations and Regulatory Services.

<P>The Department of Regulatory Services contains three main divisions: the <A
HREF="inspections/index.html">Division of Inspections</A>, the <A
HREF="licensing.html">Division of Licenses &amp; Consumer Services</A>, and the
<A HREF="convention.html">Minneapolis Convention Center</A>. The Department is
charged with the responsibility of protecting the health, safety and welfare of
Minneapolis residents through a program of regulation, inspection, testing, and
enforcement of laws and ordinances pertaining to licensed business
establishments, building inspection, housing inspection, plan review, zoning
administration, pollution control, parking regulation/collection, weights and
measures, trucking enforcement, and consumer protection.

<P>Regulatory Services provides the investigation and enforcement of laws and
ordinances pertaining to:

<UL>
	<P><LI>Licensed businesses.

	<P><LI>Building and housing code inspections including plan review, zoning
	administration, condemnation and removal of hazardous buildings.

	<P><LI>Inspection of all construction activities.

	<P><LI>Trucking enforcement activities including certification of meters and
	commercial weighing devices, random checks of City purchases (salt and
	aggregate), fuel delivery, and prepackaged commodity checks.

	<P><LI>Pollution control activities including hazardous site cleanup, noise,
	illegal dumping, and the storage of hazardous materials.

	<P><LI>Traffic control including parking enforcement, directing traffic, and
	collecting from parking meters.

	<P><LI>Administration of Convention Center facilities including a 280,000
	square-foot exhibit hall, a 28,000 square-foot ballroom, and 54 meeting
	rooms.
</UL>

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Operations &amp; Regulatory Services</B><BR>
City Hall, Room 1C<BR>
350 5 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415-1391
</ADDRESS>

<P><BR><B>Phone Numbers</B>
<PRE>
Inspections Division            (612) 673-5800
Licenses and Consumer Services  (612) 673-2080
Convention Center               (612) 335-6000
</PRE>


