<HEAD>
    <TITLE>Personnel Services</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!-- #include &amp;amp;quot;city_head.incl&amp;amp;quot;
	#MY_BGCOLOR#=&amp;amp;quot;ffffff&amp;amp;quot;
	#MY_HEADER#=&amp;amp;quot;Personnel Services&amp;amp;quot;
-->
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<TABLE border=0> <TR> <TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" ALT="logo"
ALIGN="BOTTOM"></TD> <TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
<H2 align=right>Personnel Services</H2></TD> </TR></TABLE> <!-- end include -->
<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" --><BR>
<BR>
<HR><A HREF="/index.html">Home</A> | <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A> | <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A> | <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A> <HR><!-- end include -->The City
of Minneapolis is hiring. check out the <A HREF="/departments/city-coordinator/hr/jobs/index.html">current
job openings</A>.<BR>
<BR>
Personnel Services has three main responsibilities: recruitment and staffing,
test development and tutoring, and job classification. <BR>
<BR>
Recruitment and staffing functions are carried out to keep more than 8,000
positions filled under the jurisdiction of the <A HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City
Council</A>, Board of Education, <A HREF="/departments/other/parks.html">Park
and Recreation Board</A> and the <A HREF="/departments/other/library.html">Library
Board</A>, by providing the operating departments with qualified candidates
and helping them meet their affirmative action goals. Many new employees
are subject to pre-employment drug testing and medical examinations. New
employees of the City and the Park Board will be required to be residents
of the city within six months of completing their probationary period. <BR>
<BR>
The test development and tutoring unit of Personnel Services develops job-related
tests and provides tutoring to help test takers do their best. The unit
aims to select the best qualified employees and to improve employment opportunities
for women and minorities. <BR>
<BR>
The department also maintains a fair and objective system for classifying
jobs based on their job-related contribution and/or assessed value to the
goals of the City. <BR>
<BR>
For employment opportunities with the City of Minneapolis and the boards
listed above, call the Hot Line at (612) 673-2666. This recorded message
lists all jobs that are currently open for application. The Personnel office
is open to the public from Monday through Friday 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. Applications
can be filled out in the office. If a job is not currently open for application,
an interest postcard can be filled out for that job and the Personnel Department
will send notification when the job opens. <BR>
<BR>
<HR>
<ADDRESS><BR>
<B>Personnel Services</B><BR>
Public Health Center<BR>
312 3 Av S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415-1042 </ADDRESS>
<BR>
<BR>
<B>Phone Numbers</B> 
<PRE>
Employment Hot Line  (612) 673-CITY
Personnel Services   (612) 673-2282</PRE>
