<HTML>
<HEAD>

<TITLE>Planning</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Planning"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Planning</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The primary functions of the Planning Department are:

<UL>
	<LI>to provide information and public policy options to elected officials
	based on sound research and analysis;

	<LI>to develop and maintain the City's comprehensive plan, to plan for
	geographic areas of the City at the neighborhood or community level, and to
	plan in functional areas such as transportation, economic development,
	housing, etc.;

	<LI>to maintain development controls by receiving and making recommendations
	on development proposals, zoning change requests, environmental impacts, etc.
</UL>

<P>To do this, the Planning Department maintains a development controls function,
a state-of-the-art research capability, and, at the direction of the <A
HREF="/departments/mayor/index.html">Mayor</A> and <A
HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City Council</A>, the department
undertakes special initiatives such as staffing and support for the <A
HREF="/departments/other/nrp.html">Neighborhood Revitalization Program</A> and
the <B><I>Minneapolis Initiative Against Racism</I></B>; and the development of a
City economic development strategy and city-wide housing strategy. The department
is part of the planning/budgeting process through participation in, and support
of, the Directions Framework.

<P>

<HR>

<P>The Planning Department provides staff support for the following committees,
functions, and initiatives:

<H3><BR>Heritage Preservation Committee</H3>

<P>The Heritage Preservation Committee's purpose is to recommend structures and
districts to the <A HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City Council</A>
for historical designation as part of the City's heritage that should be
preserved. The HPC also reviews and approves or disapproves, subject to appeal to
the City Council, building permit requests for work on designated buildings or
buildings in heritage districts.

<H3><BR>Capital Long Range Improvement Committee (CLIC)</H3>

<P>The CLIC makes recommendations to the <A
HREF="/departments/mayor/index.html">Mayor</A> and <A
HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City Council</A> on capital
improvement programs.

<H3><BR>Committee on Urban Environment (CUE)</H3>

<P>CUE proposes aesthetic guidelines for the built environment of the fully-built
central city.

<H3><BR>Planning Commission</H3>

<P>The Planning Commission is charged with long-range planning for the city and
is responsible for advising the <A
HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City Council</A> on matters of
development, zoning, and capital improvement. It is staffed by the Planning
Department.

<H3><BR>Neighborhood Revitalization Program (NRP)</H3>

<P>The Planning Department provides information, technical research, and
significant staff support to the <A HREF="/departments/other/nrp.html">NRP</A>
process.

<H3><BR>Directions Framework</H3>

<P>The Directions Framework is a process through which it is assured that the top
annual priorities of the <A HREF="/departments/mayor/index.html">Mayor</A> and <A
HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City Council</A> will receive
budgetary resources and management emphasis by <A
HREF="/departments/index.html">City departments</A>. This planning/budgeting
process is staffed jointly by program planners and budget analysts.

<P>The department is a source of information and data regarding City forecasts
and trend analysis and maintains numerous databases that are descriptive of the
city, including such summaries as the annual State of the City report.

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Minneapolis Planning Department</B><BR>
City Hall, Room 210<BR>
350 5 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415-1385
</ADDRESS>

<P><B>Phone Number</B><BR>
(612) 673-2597


