<HEAD>

<TITLE>Public Affairs</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Public Affairs"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Public Affairs</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Office of Public Affairs' mission is to increase public awareness of the
performance of City government and the advantages of City living by providing
accurate and timely information about City policies, programs, services and
neighborhoods.

<H3><BR>SERVICES</H3>
<UL>
	<LI>Answers general inquiries regarding City services and activities.
	<LI>Maintains mailing lists of media and neighborhood organizations.
	<LI>Assists the <A HREF="/departments/mayor/index.html">Mayor</A>, <A
	HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City Council</A>, and departments
	with media relations, including news conferences and news releases.
	<LI>Assists departments with marketing/advertising campaigns, special events
	and communications plans.
	<LI>Staffs the Minneapolis Real Estate Advisory Board (REAB), which advises
	the Mayor, City Council and departments on means of increasing the
	marketability of residential real estate in the City and means of promoting
	Minneapolis as a place to live.
</UL>

<H3><BR>PUBLICATIONS</H3>
<DL>
	<DT><B>On the Agenda</B>
	<DD>Biweekly mailing to neighborhood organizations, interested residents and
	the media, listing <A HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">City
	Council</A> and Council Committee agendas, public hearings, open appointments
	and other information of interest to neighborhood groups.

	<DT><BR><B>For Your Information</B>
	<DD>Monthly City employee newsletter.

	<DT><BR><B>Guide to City Services</B>
	<DD>This publication; describes the programs and services that <A
	HREF="/departments/index.html">City departments</A> offer.

	<DT><BR><B>Choose Minneapolis</B>
	<DD>A brochure about living in Minneapolis for persons considering buying or
	renting a home in the City.

	<DT><BR><B>Home Owners Folder</B>
	<DD>A packet of information distributed by the <A
	HREF="/departments/assessor/index.html">City Assessor</A> to people when they
	homestead their newly purchased Minneapolis home.
</DL>

<H3><BR>SPECIAL PROJECTS</H3>
<UL>
	<P><LI>Office of Film, Video and Recording -- an office which provides
	information, promotion and logistical support to Minneapolis' film, video and
	recording industries.

	<P><LI>Minneapolis Awards -- an annual awards presentation recognizing
	individuals who have enriched the Minneapolis community.

	<P><LI>Choose Minneapolis -- a campaign to promote living in Minneapolis,
	including: Annual Minneapolis/Saint Paul Home Tour -- a tour of Minneapolis
	and <A HREF="http://www.stpaul.gov">Saint Paul</A> homes designed to promote
	City living. Minneapolis Ambassadors -- volunteers answer questions about
	Minneapolis neighborhoods from potential home buyers and renters. Courses for
	Real Estate Agents -- courses that provide real-estate agents with
	information about the <A HREF="/departments/other/mcda.html">MCDA</A>, <A
	HREF="/departments/other/nrp.html">neighborhood revitalization</A>, community
	crime prevention and other City programs.
</UL>

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Public Affairs</B><BR>
City Hall, Room 323M<BR>
350 5 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55415-1300
</ADDRESS>

<P><BR><B>Phone Numbers</B>
<PRE>
Office of Public Affairs             (612) 673-2491
Office of Film, Video and Recording  (612) 673-2947
Fax                                  (612) 673-2011
</PRE>


