<HEAD>

<TITLE>Public Works</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Public Works"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Public Works</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Public Works Department has a number of areas of service responsibility.
The following list includes some of the more visible types of services:

<UL>
	<LI><A HREF="#sidewalk">Sidewalk Inspection</A>
	<LI><A HREF="#str-fix">Street Maintenance and Repair</A>
	<LI><A HREF="#str-cln">Street Cleaning</A>
	<LI><A HREF="#snow">Snow and Ice Removal</A>
	<LI><A HREF="solid-waste/index.html">Solid Waste &amp; Recycling</A>
	<LI><A HREF="#trans">Transportation and Special Projects</A>
</UL>

<A NAME="sidewalk"><H3><BR>SIDEWALK INSPECTION</H3></A>

<P>The Public Works Department has divided Minneapolis into three
sidewalk-inspection districts, with one inspector assigned to each district. Each
inspector visually inspects sidewalk sections for major cracks, hazardous
conditions and general deterioration from May 1 to Nov. 1. If a repair is deemed
necessary, the property owner has 15 days in which to respond. If there is no
response, a City-approved contractor makes the repair and the property owner is
billed for the work. The property owner can either pay the bill or have the cost
assessed over five years. Inspectors strive to carry out routine inspections of
all sidewalks every seven to eight years. Other inspections are made in response
to complaints from residents or other City personnel.

<P>The Sidewalk Department is also responsible for enforcement of the snow
shoveling ordinance. Commercial properties are required to remove snow within
four daylight hours. Residential properties must clear their sidewalks within 24
hours.

<P>Sidewalk Department: (612) 673-2441

<A NAME="str-fix"><H3><BR>STREET MAINTENANCE AND REPAIR</H3></A>

<P>To maintain Minneapolis streets, Public Works Department personnel perform the
following repairs: 1) pothole filling, 2) crack filling, 3) seal coating, and 4)
thin overlays. Various criteria are used to determine which type or combination
of repairs are best suited for a given situation. Most repairs can only be made
during warmer months. The Department strives to carry out routine inspections of
all streets and alleys every year. They will also investigate any complaints they
receive of problems in streets and alleys.

<P>Street Maintenance: (612) 673-5720

<A NAME="str-cln"><H3><BR>STREET CLEANING</H3></A>

<P>To keep streets free of litter and other debris, Public Works Department
personnel perform the following cleaning services: 1) a complete sweeping of all
streets and alleys each spring (typically mid-April to May); 2) the
<A HREF="sweepoct.html">collection of leaves and sweeping of all streets each fall</A>
(typically late October to
mid-November); 3) night sweeping of streets and alleys in central business
district approximately twice per week if weather permits; 4) targeted sweeping of
other commercial areas and some residential streets on an as needed basis
throughout the summer; 5) miscellaneous sweeping and cleaning (i.e. after an
extraordinary storm or special event); and 6) catch-basin and drain cleaning as
required.

<P>Street Maintenance: (612) 673-5720

<A NAME="snow"><H3><BR>SNOW AND ICE REMOVAL</H3></A>

<P>The Public Works Department provides snow and ice control on all City streets
and alleys. In general, at least four inches of snow must fall before a snow
emergency is declared. Snow plowing activities are prioritized as follows: 1)
snow emergency routes, 2) alleys, and 3) residential streets.

<P>The appendix contains information on parking restrictions during a snow
emergency.

<P>Snow and ice removal personnel also provide the following services on an
as-needed basis:

<UL>
	<LI>Clear sidewalks and parking lots of City-owned buildings.
	<LI>Sand arterial and residential streets and alleys.
	<LI>Open frozen or clogged storm drains.
	<LI>Clear bus stops.
	<LI>Clear corners.
	<LI>Remove ice from water main break.
</UL>

<P><A HREF="snow.html">Snow emergency information</A> is available 24 hours/day at (612) 348-SNOW. For
any problems or complaints call (612) 673-5720.

<A NAME="trans"><H3><BR>TRANSPORTATION AND SPECIAL PROJECTS</H3></A>

<P>The Division of Transportation and Special Projects is responsible for transit
operations, the parking system, bicycle operation, movement of pedestrians,
movement of goods, and the safety of people who use the City's transportation
system.

<P>The system consists of over 28,000 street lights, 100,000 signs, 750
intersections with traffic signals, 6400 parking meters, and nine parking ramps.
The Transportation and Special Projects division manages all street uses
throughout the city, including the Impound Lot.

<P>The division is also responsible for the oversight and management of special
construction projects, including four new fire stations, light-rail transit
development, parking ramps and skyways, the Nicollet Mall Extension, and other
special construction projects.

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Public Works</B><BR>
City Hall, Room 203<BR>
350 5 St S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN-1314
</ADDRESS>

<P><BR><B>Phone Numbers</B>
<PRE>
Municipal Impound Lot                (612) 673-5777
Street lighting                      (612) 673-2429
Street use permits                   (612) 673-5750
Transportation and Special Projects  (612) 673-2411
</PRE>


