e first African-American      elected to city council1982  Fire destroys Donaldsons and Northwestern       National Bank buildings1987  Minnesota Twins play the St. Louis Cardinals      to win the World Series1988  Minneapolis Sculpture garden opens1991  Minnesota Twins play the Atlanta Braves to      win the World Series1991  Minneapolis Convention Center opens1991  Historic State Theatre reopens with      &quot;Carousel&quot;1993  Sharon Sayles Belton is the first woman and      first African-American elected as      Minneapolis mayor<HR></PRE>Back to <A HREF="#Top">top</A> of this document <PRE><HR></PRE>Copyright &copy; 1996, City of Minneapolis. See <A HREF="http://www.ci.mpls.mn.us/disclaimer.html">Disclaimer</A>for legal information.<BR>Maintained by the <A HREF="http://www.ci.mpls.mn.us/rangers.html">CyberspaceRangers</A>. Updated Wednesday, 24 July 1996. <BR><BR>Comments or suggestions? Send email to <I><A HREF="mailto:opa_mpls@ci.mpls.mn.us">opa_mpls@ci.mpls.mn.us</A></I>.</BODY></HTML>
