<BODY>

<H2>Requesting a Homestead <BR>
In person, by Mail or by Fax</H2>

<P>
New home owners in the City of Minneapolis can file for a homestead
by mail, fax, or in person after they move into their new home.
Filing by mail or fax is very easy. The following information
and documents are required in order to process the request: 
<PRE WIDTH=132>
<I><B>Information or Document</B></I>       <I><B>Reason</B></I>                                   

Copy of deed (Warranty Deed,  Proof that you own the property          
Contract-for-Dead, etc.)

Copy of the <I>Certificate of</I>    The CRV and the deed must be filed with the
<I>Real Estate Value (CRV)</I>       Registrar-of-Deeds before final approval 

Social Security Number        Required by state law                    
of each owner-occupant                                                 

The date you moved in         Occupancy is a homestead requirement     

Your daytime phone number     If we need further documentation or if 
                              we have question, then we will need to 
                              contact you.
</PRE>

<P>
If the documents provided show that your new home should be classified
as homestead, then you can expect the following:
<OL>
<LI>If the property <B>was not</B> previously classified as homestead,
then within ten days of receiving your request, you will receive
by mail an application that must be signed by all the homesteaders
and returned to the City Assessor.
<LI>Within ten days of the 2<U>nd</U> of January you will receive
by mail an application that must be signed by all the homesteaders
and returned to the City Assessor. 
</OL>

<P>
Failure to sign and return the application will result in the
property being classified <BR>
as non-homestead.
<P>
Applications are only sent in the first year after purchasing
the new home. So, if you sell or move out of your home, then you
must inform the City Assessor within 30 days of vacating or selling
the home.
<PRE WIDTH=132>
Mailing Address:                        Fax number:  673-3538          
Homesteads - City Assessor                                             
309 2nd Ave. S.  -  Room 100            For more information call us at
Minneapolis,  Minnesota  55401-2234     Telephone number:  673-2382    
</PRE>

</BODY>

