<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>Cable Proposals</TITLE></HEAD><BODY TEXT="#00002b" BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><H1><CENTER>Institutional Network (I-NET) Expansion Negotiations </CENTER></H1><P><CENTER><A HREF="#anchor149190">Who gets what</A> <BR><A HREF="#Benefits">Potential benefits</A> <BR><A HREF="#Issues">Unresolved issues</A> <BR><A HREF="#Next Steps">Recommended next steps<BR></A><A HREF="#Conclusions">Conclusions</A> </CENTER><P><HR><A NAME="Who Gets What"></A><H2>City Gets</H2>A lease of a Fiber optic network connecting City Hall with <UL>  <LI>MCDA   <LI>Precincts 2-5   <LI>Traffic Center   <LI>Equipment Division   <LI>Street Dept   <LI>Convention Center   <LI>MTN   <LI>Super Computer Center (for Internet) </UL>Paragon values this infrastructure at $354,520 installed** 24 hour a daysupport for the network. Paragon values this benefit at $75,000 annually*&quot;Nominal&quot; fee from Paragon for the use of 18 channels*** * Paragonwould be held to any Rights of Way moritorium put in place by the City.* *No independent estimate exists currently. Paragon will have the abilityto extend their own network as part of this project. They state they havehave no plans to do so at this time. ** * The formula for setting the &quot;nominal&quot;fee is an open issue at this time. <H2>MTN Gets</H2>Consolidation of MTN into main location (St. Anthony Main). Move of &quot;Playback&quot;facility from Paragon (Plymouth Ave N) into main location. Fiber connectionsbetween Paragon and St. Anthony Main. A lease for access to a fiber Internetprovider. This will allow MTN to continue to pursue Internet service fornon-profits. <BR><BR>Paragon values this investment at $243,410* * Paragon will have the abilityto extend their own network as part of this project. They state they havehave no plans to do so at this time. No independent estimate exists currently.<H2>School Gets</H2>Fiber optic network connecting seventeen school sites: <UL>  <LI>Anthony   <LI>Henry   <LI>Sanford   <LI>Anwatin   <LI>North   <LI>South   <LI>Edison   <LI>Northeast   <LI>Southwest   <LI>Folwell   <LI>Olson   <LI>Middle   <LI>Washburn   <LI>Franklin Roosevelt   <LI>District Service Center Work Opportunity Center   <LI>Fire Training </UL><BR>Paragon values this investment at $495,597* <BR><BR>Total Paragon investment: $1,093,567* <H5>* Paragon will have the ability to extend their own network as partof this project. They state they have have no plans to do so at this time.No independent estimate exists currently. </H5><H2>Paragon gets</H2>2300 square feet of space at Plymouth Ave. Lease of 18 access channels untilthe year 2004 (end of franchise) (1 &quot;A&quot; cable, 17 &quot;B&quot;cable channels) Agreement to shut off FM Service <BR><HR><H2><A NAME="Benefits"></A><BR>Potential Benefits </H2><B>Community gets the potential of: </B><UL>  <LI>More cable programs (figure 5 more per year)*   <LI>Better, expanded Institutional Network (needs to be replaced)   <LI>Improved access to Internet for non-profit groups   <LI>Potential future competition to US West for residential services suchas voice, data (Internet) and video programming </UL><H5>*Paragon has not committed to adding more programming but states itintends to. Paragon has several unused channels now. </H5><BR><BR><B>Potential Benefits of the I-Net* </B><BR>City Government and School benefits of a high speed network: Schools willuse it to create &quot;virtual&quot; classrooms and alternative ways ofteaching students and managing schools (3-7 years out) <BR>City will use it for high speed communication. It could replace pieces ofCityNet, charges from US West, etc. (3-7 years out) City could save $50kannually in US West data line charges in 1997. Cities and school could savemore in lease costs in 1998 and beyond* <H5>* The long term benefit of the I-Net is dependent on our ability todevelop it for government and educational use. We do not have good estimatesat this time of the cost/benefit of developing this potential. We know thatthere would be significant additional investment to use the I-Net for simultaneousvoice, data and video transmission. </H5><BR><BR><B>Paragon benefits include: </B><UL>  <LI>Relief from the current franchise language obligating Paragon to providethe city with 25% of its channel capacity.*   <LI>More channels -- allowing them to add more programming and generateadditional revenue (at a cost to their customers)   <LI>More channels -- enabling them to remain competitive with newer suppliers(satellite)   <LI>Higher market value -- should Time/Warner decide to sell Paragon </UL>*Under this arrangement, the 25% capacity language in the current franchiseremains, but we lease our excess channels to Paragon until the end of thefranchise. <BR><HR><H2>What are we giving up? </H2><UL>  <LI>Use of 18 channels subject to the City's right to claim additonalPEG channels when needed.   <LI>Space at Paragon   <LI>With funding,* those channels could be used for additional City programmingfor the benefit of the community such as: Stolen goods, Preview Channel,Freeway traffic cameras, MTC bus schedule information, Youth by youth/ Homeworkhelp, Council committee meetings, Foreign language programming.   <LI>By franchise agreement, these channels have little or no classic &quot;marketvalue&quot; in markets where Paragon competes and we cannot lease them toa Paragon competitor.** </UL><H5>*Funding could come from the $1.5M of franchise fees. These dollarsare now funneled directly to the General Fund. <BR>**There is potential to obtain financial benefit from the I-Net throughcollaboration with other government and non-profit agencies. Unfortunately,we do not have estimates at this time. </H5><HR><A NAME="Issues"></A><H2>Unresolved Issues </H2>Determining fair value for use of the channels: Is the lease of the I-Neta fair exchange? <BR><BR>Example formulas for getting to an equitable lease: A) New channels increasevalue of Paragon infrastructure by $30M Use rate of 3% = $900K fee annuallyB) New channels increase Paragon capacity by 20% 20% of current franchisefee ($1.5M) = $300K annually C) New channels will increase paragon revenuesby $3M Additional franchise fee (5%) = $151K annually D) $1.00 &quot;Nominal&quot;fee (original position) E) Continued expansion and maintenance of the I-Netover the life of the franchise Service Level Agreement - City must insurequality of network &quot;up time.&quot; Negotiations on this point havenot begun.<BR><HR><A NAME="Next Steps"></A><H2>Recommended Next Steps</H2>With Paragon: <BR>Establish a Memorandum of Understanding that allows Paragon to proceed withtheir Capital request <BR>Establish a fair and reasonable lease arrangement for the use of the channels<BR>Write a service level agreement that insures a highly reliable I-Net. WithIndependent consultant(s) --- $10k Conduct an independent study of TimeWarner's business strategy using a non-disclosure approach Complete detailedanalysis of future cost/benefit of the fiber I-Net <BR><HR><A NAME="Conclusions"></A><H2>Conclusions </H2>Several major issues remain. They will take time to work out. The City shouldnot feel pressured to strike a deal immediately. The City could immediatelyand agressively negotiate the remaining issues: <UL>  <LI>Lease arrangement that maintains City's 25% capacity   <LI>Fair value of channels   <LI>Ownership   <LI>Service level agreement </UL>The City could complete further independent study to conclude the potentialsavings to the City and the potential value to Paragon of the proposal.($10K) <BR><BR><HR><A HREF="http://www.ci.mpls.mn.us/">Home</A> | <A HREF="http://www.ci.mpls.mn.us/hot">What'sHot</A> | <A HREF="http://www.ci.mpls.mn.us/events.html">Events</A> | <A HREF="http://www.ci.mpls.mn.us/topics">Topics</A>| <A HREF="http://www.ci.mpls.mn.us/departments">Departments</A> | <A HREF="http://www.ci.mpls.mn.us/publications">Publications</A>| <A HREF="http://www.ci.mpls.mn.us/friends.html">Other Sites</A> <HR><BR>Copyright &copy; 1996, City of Minneapolis. See <A HREF="http://www.ci.mpls.mn.us/disclaimer.html">Disclaimer</A>for legal information.<BR>Maintained by the <A HREF="http://www.ci.mpls.mn.us/rangers.html">CyberspaceRangers</A>. Updated Tuesday, September 10, 1996. <BR><BR>Comments or suggestions? Send email to <I><A HREF="mailto:opa_mpls@ci.mpls.mn.us">opa_mpls@ci.mpls.mn.us</A></I>.</BODY></HTML>
