<HEAD>

<TITLE>Minneapolis Community Development Agency</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Minneapolis Community Development Agency"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Minneapolis Community Development Agency</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P>The Minneapolis Community Development Agency (MCDA) is an arm of the City
of Minneapolis, directed by a Board of Commissioners consisting of the 13
members of the <A HREF="/departments/city-council/index.html">Minneapolis
City Council</A>. The MCDA is administered by an executive director.

<P>The MCDA seeks to sustain and improve the residential, economic, and aesthetic
environment of the city for the benefit of residents, employees, and businesses
through the implementation of development financing programs. To accomplish these
goals the MCDA:

<UL>
	<P><LI>Sells bonds and assists in land acquisition and development for a
	variety of commercial, industrial, business, health-care, nursing home and
	educational facilities.

	<P><LI>Attracts and supports new and existing businesses by providing loans
	and other assistance to settle, expand, or relocate.

	<P><LI>Provides grants, low-interest mortgages, and home improvement and
	substantial rehabilitation loans to homeowners to build, buy, or upgrade
	their homes.

	<P><LI>Provides loans to rental-property owners to upgrade their buildings.

	<P><LI>Provides financing and other assistance to provide affordable housing
	for residents, particularly low- and middle-income families.

	<P><LI>Removes or rehabs blighted buildings and works with nonprofit and
	neighborhood organizations to sell rehabbed or new homes to low- and
	middle-income owner-occupants at affordable prices.

	<P><LI>Provides funding, programs, and other assistance to neighborhood
	organizations to revitalize neighborhoods.
</UL>

<P>Most of the revenue for MCDA activities is generated by the sale of bonds and
activity from development districts, current investment, and real estate
proceeds. The MCDA also administers funding from various state and federal
sources such as Community Development Block Grants (CDBG) and the Minnesota
Housing Finance Agency (MHFA).

<P>

<HR>

<ADDRESS>
<P><B>Minneapolis Community Development Agency</B><BR>
Crown Roller Mill<BR>
105 5 Av S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55401-2517

<P>or

<P><B>Minneapolis Community Development Agency</B><BR>
Ceresota Building, Suite 600<BR>
155 5 Av S<BR>
Minneapolis, MN 55401-2527
</ADDRESS>

