<HTML>
<HEAD>
  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">
  <TITLE>Absentee Ballot Application</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#15053d" BGCOLOR="#ffffff">

<FORM ACTION="default.cgi" ENCTYPE="x-www-form-encoded" METHOD="POST">
<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Absentee Ballot Application</H1>

<P><BR>
<HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

<PRE>I want an absentee ballot for the <INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox"
VALUE="checkbox"> PRIMARY  <INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE=
"checkbox"> GENERAL election. 

REASON: 
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox">absence from precinct 
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox">religious discipline or observance of religious holiday 
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox">illness or disability 
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox">service as election judge in another precinct 
<INPUT TYPE="checkbox" NAME="checkbox" VALUE="checkbox">permanent (see instructions, below) 

My legal name and address:              Mail my absentee ballot to: 

_____________________________________   _____________________________________

_____________________________________   _____________________________________

_____________________________________   _____________________________________



Signature____________________________ Date________________________________</PRE>

<PRE ALIGN=CENTER>Mail or fax your completed Absentee Ballot Application 
to the Minneapolis Elections Department.</PRE>

<PRE>
                            Minneapolis Elections 
                            City Hall, Room 1B 
                            350 South 5th St  
                            Minneapolis MN 55415-1396 
                            Phone: (612) 673-2070 
                            Fax: (612) 673-3399</PRE>

<H2><HR ALIGN=LEFT>Instructions</H2>

<P>In order to vote by absentee ballot you must be an eligible voter, a
resident of the election precinct indicated by your legal residence address
on this application, and do not intend to abandon this residence prior to
election day. Please note that Minnesota law provides that it is a felony
to make a false or untrue statement in an application for an absentee ballot,
to apply for an absentee ballot more than once in an election with the intent
to cast an illegal ballot, to exhibit a ballot marked by a person to another
person, or to violate an absentee ballot provision for the purpose of casting
an illegal vote in a precinct or to assist anyone to cast an illegal vote.
<BR>
<BR>
Be sure to check the appropriate box indicating why you are unable to go
to your polling place on election day; these are the only reasons that entitle
you to vote by absentee ballot. <BR>
<BR>
An eligible voter who reasonably expects to be permanently unable to go
to the polling place on election day because of illness or disability may
apply to automatically receive an absentee ballot application before each
election and to have the status as a permanent absentee voter. <BR>
<BR>
Be sure to give your correct legal residence address as completely as possible,
since this is used to verify your precinct number. <BR>
<BR>
Be sure to sign the application. <BR>
<BR>
Return the completed application as soon as possible to the Minneapolis
Elections Department. You may fax the application to 673-3399. <BR>
<BR>
Your absentee ballot will be mailed or delivered to you as soon as they
are available. <BR>
<BR>
REMEMBER: YOU MUST INDICATE WHETHER YOU ARE REQUESTING BALLOTS FOR THE PRIMARY
OR GENERAL ELECTION, OR BOTH. <BR>
<BR>
Do not submit more than one application for each election. <BR>
<BR>
<HR ALIGN=LEFT></P>

