<HTML>
<HEAD>

<title>Fall Street Sweeping</title>

</HEAD>

<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<P>City of Minneapolis, Department of Public Works, Street Maintenance Division
<H2>Street Sweeping and Fall Leaf Removal Information</H2>
<P>
<HR width=100%>
<P>
The Street Maintenance Division will start the fall sweeping and leaf removal of the City's streets and parkways on October 22. Fall sweeping and leaf removal will be complete in approximately one month.
<P>
Please do not rake any additional leaves into the street. Leaves in the street cause a variety of problems: 
<UL><LI>Plug drains when it rains.
<LI>Create a fire hazard when cars park in them.
<LI>Increase danger to small children who like to play in the leaf piles.
<LI>Become slippery when wet and can cause car accidents.
<LI>Blow into previously raked yards.
<LI>If  raked out after the sweeping has been done, leaves remain in the street all winter causing drainage problems.</UL>
For information about bagging fall leaves and collection, see the <A HREF="http:solid-waste/yw.html">yard waste collection</A> page.
<P>
Posting of "No Parking" signs will be done the morning of the day prior to the actual sweeping.	Business and commercial areas will be a priority for sweeping each day so as to restore critically needed parking as soon as possible. Signs will be removed on the same day as the sweeping occurs.
<P>
For questions or more information about the fall street sweepings and leaf removal, call the Street Maintenance Division at 673-5720.
<P>
<HR>
 Updated Tuesday, October 18, 1996. <BR>
</BODY>
</HTML>
