Two positions are vacant on the Real Estate Advisory Board. The board advises
the City on residential real estate trends and issues in Minneapolis with
attention to programs that help market Minneapolis as a place to live. The
11-member board meets monthly. Members must be registered agents who live
in the city. Members are not compensated. <BR>
