<H2>School Board Vacancy</H2>
The Minneapolis Board of Education will appoint one person to serve the
remainder of the term of board member Len Biernat who will resign to take
a seat in the Minnesota House of Representatives. The term will begin in
January and end on December 31, 1997. Applicants must reside in Minneapolis,
be at least 18 years old, and have been a citizen for at least three months.
Board members devote at least 100 hours a month to their duties. Compensation
is $800 a month plus $175 for expenses.<BR>
<BR>
<I>To obtain an application form and background materials, write to Bill
Green, Chair, Minneapolis Board of Education, 807 NE Broadway, Minneapolis,
MN 55413. Application materials should be requested by November 21. Applications
are due November 25. Direct questions to David Dudycha, 627-2009.</I><HR>
