in assessing delivery of youth employment services in Phillips.<BR>
- Authorized contract with State Department of Economic Security to receive
grant funds to be used to inform women of training and employment opportunities
in non-traditional jobs.<BR>
- Passed resolution increasing the Employment and Training Department appropriation
in recognition of the receipt of Job Training Partnership Act funding.<BR>
- Concurred with Mayors recommendation to appoint/reappoint the following
persons to Minneapolis Commission on Civil Rights: Lisa Albrecht, James
F. Cannon, Robert B. Fine, Anne LaLonde Laux and Ophelia Balcos; Dianne
G. Marsh, Ron Ellwood. <I>(This is corrected copy. Orignal transmission
on November 15 contained an error. Please see note above.)<BR>
</I><B>ZONING &amp; PLANNING<BR>
</B>- Granted waiver from moratorium on auto service and sales uses to permit
Bryant Auto Repair to move from 1706 E Lake St to 1111 E Lake St, subject
to approval of site plan review.<BR>
- Amended Title 21 of the Minneapolis Code of Ordinance by adding a new
Chapter 584 relating to Interim Ordinances: Moratorium on the establishment
of elderly housing with special services and correctional facilities in
residential districts.<BR>
- Amended land use plan map of Minneapolis Plan for the 1980s by changing
the designation of light industrial to general commercial for the Quarry
Project, a proposed retail shopping center in area bounded by Johnson St
NE, 18th Av NE, Stinson Blvd, New Brighton Blvd &amp; I-35W.<BR>
<B>ELECTIONS COMMITTEE<BR>
</B>- Certified election results from November 5, 1996, general elections.<BR>
<B>RESOLUTIONS</B><BR>
- Passed resolution commending the Home and Garden Show and other trade
shows.<BR>
<I>This is partial list of Council actions. For a full list, or for details
on any action, call 673-3130. The minutes of City Council meetings can be
found at http://www.finance-commerce.com. The next Council meeting begins
at 9:30 a.m. November 22. Watch live on City Cable 34 or repeats Mondays,
Wednesdays and Fridays at 6 p.m. <BR>
