<HEAD>

<TITLE>Solid Waste &amp; Recycling</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Solid Waste &amp; Recycling"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Solid Waste &amp; Recycling</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P><B><I>Organize a Neighborhood Clean Sweep</I></B><BR>
Clean Sweeps are Saturday clean-up events organized by registered neighborhood
groups and assisted by Minneapolis Solid Waste and Recycling. Neighborhood groups
promote the event, and volunteers load neighborhood garbage into trucks provided
by Solid Waste and Recycling, which also pays disposal fees. This is a good
opportunity for elderly residents to get assistance from their neighbors. If you
are interested in helping with a Clean Sweep, contact your local neighborhood
group. For additional information about solid-waste disposal, call Solid Waste
and Recycling, 673-2917.

<P><B><I>Leave Clippings When You Mow</I></B><BR>
For an easy way to a thick, healthy yard, leave grass clippings as you mow. Short
grass clippings filter down to the soil, protecting your lawn's roots from the
sun and helping to retain moisture. As grass clippings decompose, nutrients are
recycled back into your soil. Leaving clippings for a whole year is equal to one
fertilizer application. For a brochure about grass clippings and lawn care, call
Solid Waste and Recycling, 673-2917.

<P><B><I>Transfer Station Takes Old Carpet</I></B><BR>
Minneapolis residents with City solid-waste collection services can drop off
carpet at the Transfer Station for no extra charge. Just obtain a voucher from
Solid Waste and Recycling. There is no limit to the length and weight of a carpet
roll dropped off at the Transfer Station. For a voucher, call 673-2917.

<P><B><I>Vouchers Let Residents Drop Off Building, Paving Materials</I></B><BR>
Save on disposal costs when you remove a sidewalk or tear off a roof. Minneapolis
residents with City solid-waste collection services can obtain vouchers
permitting them to drop off building or paving materials at no additional charge.
Best of all, concrete and asphalt will be recycled in City paving projects. For a
voucher or more details, call 673-2917.

<P><B><I>Buy Reusable Building Materials</I></B><BR>
Located in the Hi-Lake Shopping Center, 2216 Lake St E, the Reuse Center sells
reusable building materials. The inventory includes items such as hardware,
fixtures, doors, cabinets, molding, and dimension lumber. Purchase reused
building materials to match an existing architectural style, to create unique
signature pieces, to save money, and to help the environment. The Reuse Center
also provides home-improvement classes and is working with the Science Museum of
Minnesota on environmental education. For more information, call 724-2608.

<P><I>Lend A Hand: Purchase products made from recycled materials. Examples range
from recycled lawn edging to polar-fleece jackets. Look for the words
&quot;post-consumer recycled.&quot;</I>

<P><A HREF="index.html">(Table of Contents)</A>


