<HEAD>

<TITLE>Weathering Winter</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Weathering Winter"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Weathering Winter</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P><B><I>Holidazzle Lights Up the City Beginning November 24</I></B><BR>
The annual Holidazzle celebration will transform downtown Minneapolis into a
colorful wonderland with 28 free evening parades, beginning Friday, November 24.
A marching band and a choir accompany lighted floats with nursery-rhyme and
fairy-tale themes down Nicollet Mall from 12th Street to Fourth Street. Santa
Claus and his lighted reindeer provide the grand finale. The parades start at
6:30 p.m. and last about 30 minutes. See the November and December calendars for
the complete schedule.

<P><B><I>Avoid a Tow - Call 348-SNOW</I></B><BR>
A towed vehicle makes winter much colder, so please review the 1995-96
Minneapolis Snow Emergency regulations. For up-to-the-minute parking information,
call 348-SNOW (7669). In general, at least four inches of snow must fall before a
snow emergency is declared. Don't park in the street during hours when parking is
prohibited, even if your street appears to be plowed; additional plowing may be
necessary. When you go out of town, please arrange for someone to clear your
sidewalk and move your vehicles during Snow Emergencies.

<P><B><I>Safe Sidewalks Are Every Citizen's Responsibility</I></B><BR>
Everyone gets involved in keeping our sidewalks clear of snow during the winter
months. Older neighbors or those with disabilities may need a helping hand, and
everyone can pitch in to remove built-up snow from corners and fire hydrants.
City ordinances require that sidewalks of single-family homes and duplexes be
clear 24 hours after a snowfall. Sidewalks of commercial areas or apartment
buildings must be cleared within four daytime hours. Community organizations can
provide shoveling assistance for a fee to people with disabilities. Seniors can
call 673-3004 for a referral. Call 673-2441 to report unsafe sidewalks.

<P><B><I>Do the Town and Park for Free in Downtown Minneapolis</I></B><BR>
Park free downtown with a purchase of $20 or more at any one of nearly 200
participating shops and restaurants on weekday evenings and weekends. Just enter
any parking facility displaying the green &quot;Do The Town&quot; parking sign
after 4 p.m. Monday through Friday or anytime weekends. Ask for a free parking
voucher when you make your purchase (receipts will not be accepted), then present
the voucher to the parking attendant when you head home. For more information,
call the Downtown Council, 338-3807.

<P><I>Lend a Hand: Please clear snow down to the pavement 
and across the full width of your sidewalk so that 
people traveling in wheelchairs can get by.</I>

<P><A HREF="index.html">(Table of Contents)</A>


