<HEAD>

<TITLE>Pedaling &amp;  Parking</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="Pedaling &amp;  Parking"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>Pedaling &amp;  Parking</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P><B><I>Parking Lots - Not Just for Cars</I></B><BR>
The City's parking ramps and lots serve thousands of downtown commuters and
shoppers daily. They also offer convenient, low-cost parking for people attending
events at the Convention Center, the Metrodome, and Target Center. The ramps are
a vital part of the transit system, and some include terminals for MCTO buses and
lockers for bicycles. The City's parking lots also provide sites for downtown
events such as Ribfest. Habitat for Humanity even built a house on a parking lot
and then moved the home to a neighborhood. For information on municipal parking,
call 673-2411.

<P><B><I>300 More Places to Park</I></B><BR>
Watch for the opening of a new municipal parking ramp in December 1996. The ramp
in the Federal Courts Building will connect to the skyway system, and it will
include lockers and showers for bicyclists.

<P><B><I>Cedar Lake Commuter Bicycle Trail Opens</I></B><BR>
Minneapolis residents are among the most avid bicyclists in the country, and
their city reflects that. Broad, smooth and traffic-free, the new Cedar Lake
Commuter Trail is the latest addition to a world-class system of bicycle lanes
and paths. The system spans 77 miles and includes bicycle lanes in downtown
Minneapolis; smooth, flat trails for commuters and recreational cyclists; and
convenient bicycle racks and lockers. To protect your safety as a bicyclist, the
City enforces bicycling &quot;rules of the road.&quot; For a copy of these rules,
call 673-2411.

<P><B><I>Road and Home Construction Continue Along Hiawatha Avenue</I></B><BR>
Watch for progress on the missing link in Hiawatha Avenue. Construction will
start in Spring 1996 on the overpass at Lake Street. By 1998, Hiawatha will be
completed from downtown to 46th Street. Construction south of 46th Street is
scheduled to start in late 1997. With help from the MCDA, new homes are being
built along the &quot;Hiawatha Corridor.&quot; For more information on home
building, call the MCDA, 673-5233.

<P><B><I>Carpool and Park for Less</I></B><BR>
Sharing rides helps the community by saving energy, improving air quality, and
easing rush-hour congestion. Carpooling will also help you save money. The City
works with Minnesota Rideshare and the Minnesota Department of Transportation to
support ridesharing. Special rates for carpools are available in some municipal
parking ramps and lots. Call 349-RIDE for more rideshare information.

<P><B><I>Move Cars for Street Sweeping</I></B><BR>
Minneapolis sweeps its streets each spring and fall. Sweeping begins in mid-April
and mid-October and takes about four weeks. Be careful where you park during
street sweeping. The City posts &quot;No Parking&quot; signs the day before it
sweeps streets. Vehicles illegally parked during sweeping are towed to the
Municipal Impound Lot.

<P><A HREF="index.html">(Table of Contents)</A>


