<HEAD>

<TITLE>City Living</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<!-- #include "city_head.incl"
	#MY_BGCOLOR#="ffffff"
	#MY_HEADER#="City Living"
-->
<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">

<TABLE border=0>
<TR>
	<TD valign=top><IMG SRC="/pict/sails.gif" alt="logo"></TD>
	<TD valign=center><H1 align=right>City of Minneapolis</H1>
	<H2 align=right>City Living</H2></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<!-- end include -->

<!-- #include "city_navbar.incl" -->
<P><HR>

<A HREF="/index.html">Home</A>
| <A HREF="/hot/index.html">What's Hot</A>
| <A HREF="/events.html">Events</A>
| <A HREF="/topics/index.html">Topics</A>
| <A HREF="/departments/index.html">Departments</A>
| <A HREF="/publications/index.html">Publications</A>
| <A HREF="/related.html">Other Sites</A>

<HR>
<!-- end include -->

<P><B><I>Low-interest Loans Available for Home Improvements</I></B><BR>
Want to expand your kitchen? Add a bathroom? Repair the roof? Low-interest
home-improvement loans are available from the MCDA. Homeowners with incomes of
$41,000 or less may qualify. Some MCDA loans don't even have to be paid back
unless you sell the house, move, or transfer the title. For more information,
call the MCDA, 673-5286.

<P><B><I>Keep Your House Up, Taxes Down</I></B><BR>
This Old House, a tax incentive approved by the legislature in 1993, offers
savings to owners of older homes. Those who have improved their property since
Jan. 1, 1993, are eligible for these savings. If your home is between 35 and 70
years old, you can get a property-tax exclusion equal to half of the increase in
property value, up to $25,000. If your home is more than 70 years old, you can
get an exclusion equal to the entire increase in value, up to $50,000. For
example, if a new kitchen and bath raise the market value of your 78-year-old
home from $80,000 to $100,000, you won't be taxed on the $20,000 increase for 10
years. The exclusion will then phase out over the next five years. The deadline
for This Old House applications is June 30. For more information, call the City
Assessor, 673-2382.

<P><B><I>MCDA Provides Below-Market-Rate Loans to Home Buyers</I></B><BR>
The Minneapolis Community Development Agency (MCDA) has helped thousands of
people realize the dream of home ownership through a variety of below-market-rate
home loans for buyers -- and homeowners looking to refinance -- with incomes up
to $89,250. If you're planning to fix up an old home or build a new one, or if
you're just looking for a traditional mortgage, the MCDA can provide mortgage,
closing-cost, and down-payment assistance. To talk with a mortgage representative
about the best program for you, call 673-5288.

<P><B><I>Your Neighborhood Organization Needs You</I></B><BR>
Minneapolis neighborhood organizations are an important part of making the city
work. Members work closely with Community Crime Prevention/SAFE, the Neighborhood
Revitalization Program, the MCDA, and other City offices on safety and livability
issues. They also plan neighborhood festivals, ice-cream socials, and other
community-building events. To find out which organizations are active in your
neighborhood, please call 673-5239.

<P><I>Lend A Hand: Volunteers for the Metro Paint-A-Thon help 
elderly, disabled, and low-income residents paint their 
homes. Call 870-3660 by June 1.</I>

<P><A HREF="index.html">(Table of Contents)</A>


