<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>Relative Homestead Information</TITLE>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Word 2.0z Beta">
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<H2>THE RELATIVE HOMESTEAD</H2>

<P>
A qualifying relative of a residential property owner may become
a substitute occupant for the owner, so that the property might
be classified as homestead, as provided for under <I>Minnesota
Statutes</I>, Chapter 273.124, Subdivision 1. 
<H4>Limitations:</H4>

<OL>
<LI>The homestead tax benefit for a property with a relative occupant
cannot exceed the benefit the owner would attain as the occupant.
<LI>Property currently classified as seasonal-recreational must
be occupied by the relative for four years before the property
can be classified as homestead.
<LI>Neither the owner nor the relative occupant may claim a property
tax refund for a property homesteaded by a relative, unless the
relative occupant is a partial owner of the property.
</OL>

<H4>Qualifying Relatives:</H4>

<P>
The following relative qualify to substitute for the owner:
<P>
Parent:  Mother or father of the owner;<BR>
Stepparent:  Mother or father of owner's spouse;<BR>
Child:  Son or daughter of owner;<BR>
Stepchild:  Son or daughter of owner's spouse;<BR>
Grandparent:  Mother or father of the owner's parent;<BR>
Grandchild:  Son or daughter of owner's child;<BR>
Brother:  Son of owner's parent;<BR>
Sister:  Daughter of owner's parent;<BR>
Uncle:  Brother or brother-in-law of parent; and<BR>
Aunt:  Sister or sister-in-law of parent.
<P>
Relationships are defined by birth or legal adoption. <U>No other
relatives qualify.</U>
<H4>Application:</H4>

<P>
The relative occupant must be the applicant.
<P>
A special relative application form must be completely filled
out.
<P>
The following documents are required.
<UL>
<LI>Copy of Deed, Contract-for-Deed, or Torrens Title Certificate
<LI>Copy of birth certificates that show the relationship of the
occupant to the owner.
<LI>Marriage licenses, adoption papers, court orders, or other
documents that show the relationship between the relative occupant
and the owner.
<LI>If recently purchased, a copy of the <I>Certificate of Real
Estate Value</I>.
<LI>Valid Driver's license of relative occupant showing the homestead
property address.
<LI>Upon request, any other documents deemed necessary.
</UL>

</BODY>

</HTML>
</DOC>
