<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>Mpls National Night Out</TITLE>    <!-- Date: Tuesday, July 2, 1996  10:08 AM --></HEAD><BODY TEXT="#ffffff" BGCOLOR="#000000" LINK="#aeaeff" ALINK="#bdf6d5" VLINK="#ffc0ff"><H3><CENTER>Thirteenth Annual</CENTER></H3><P><CENTER><BR><IMG SRC="nnomain.gif" WIDTH="436" HEIGHT="318" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" ALT="National Night Out Logo"> </CENTER><H2><CENTER>Focus on Community <BR>Tuesday, August 6, 1996 </CENTER></H2><BR><HR><IMG SRC="group.jpg" BORDER="2" VSPACE=4 HSPACE=4 WIDTH="227" HEIGHT="203" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALT="Group of Neighbors"> <FONT SIZE=+1><H3>Join the Fun! National Night Out is Coming to Your Block</H3>All over Minneapolis and the rest of the nation, neighbors and neighborhoodsare gearing up for the 13th Annual National Night Out (NNO) to take placeon August 6, 1996. This year's NNO theme is &quot;Focus on Community.&quot;Start planning now so that you and your neighbors can get together and havea great time when National Night Out arrives.<BR><BR><BR>National Night Out, sponsored by Minneapolis Community Crime Prevention/SAFE(CCP/SAFE) and the Minneapolis Police Department, is designed to help createhealthy neighborhoods block by block, helping neighbors to know one another,to celebrate community and to take steps to make neighborhoods safer forthe children, elders and all residents. National Night Out helps form goodrelationships between the community and the Police Department. CCP/SAFEand NNO help to create a neighborhood network to find ways to prevent crimeand to enhance the livability of neighborhoods and the city.<BR><BR><BR><HR><H3>Downtown Parade</H3>This year for the first time, there will be a National Night Out kickoffparade sponsored by the Minneapolis Downtown Council and the MinneapolisDowntown Residents' Association. All neighborhoods and block clubs are welcometo participate in the parade, which will travel down the Nicollet Mall inMinneapolis from 11th Street to 4th Street from 12:00 Noon - 1:00 p.m. onAugust 6th. For information about the parade call 673-3015.<BR><BR><BR><HR><IMG SRC="gruffpic.jpg" BORDER="2" VSPACE=4 HSPACE=4 WIDTH="147" HEIGHT="212" ALIGN="RIGHT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALT="McGruff and Children"> <H3>Information about events and/or forming Block Clubs</H3>To get more information about National Night Out, creating a block clubor having an NNO event, call 673-3015.<BR><BR><BR><HR><IMG SRC="police1.jpg" BORDER="2" VSPACE=4 HSPACE=4 WIDTH="166" HEIGHT="234" ALIGN="LEFT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALT="Future Police Officer"> <H3>Minneapolis NNO effort ranked high amongst major cities</H3>Last year in Minneapolis, more than 800 block parties took place representingmore than 1,650 block clubs with more than 40,000 people participating.This year CCP/SAFE expects more people and block clubs to join the celebration.The National Association of Town Watch ranked Minneapolis among the top5 major cities in the country for the 6th year in a row because of its largecitizen participation and overall community effort.<BR><BR><BR><HR><IMG SRC="mcgruff.gif" BORDER="0" VSPACE=4 HSPACE=4 WIDTH="139" HEIGHT="142" ALIGN="RIGHT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALT="McGruff"> <H3>Sponsors for 1996</H3>Sponsors for NNO 1996 are General Mills Foundation, Honeywell, Minnegasco,NSP, TCF Banks, and Voss Lighting.</FONT> <BR><BR><HR><BR><BR><BR>Questions or comments? Email <A HREF="mailto:%20opa_mpls@ci.mpls.mn.us">opa_mpls@ci.mpls.mn.us</A><BR>You can also Email the National Association of Town Watch at <A HREF="mailto:%20natwnno@aol.com">natwnno@aol.com</A>.</BODY></HTML>
