<HEAD>
<TITLE>Earth and Environmental Sciences</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<PRE><IMG SRC="/images/spotgr.gif">       <IMG SRC="/images/cnes.gif"> <P></PRE>
<H1><A NAME="index">The French Space Agency (CNES) actions in the field of Earth and 
Environmental Sciences</A></H1> 

<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif">
<H2>Table of contents</H2>
<UL> 
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="glob_scale.html#GlobalScale">
<B> Research concerning changes on a global scale</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><P></B><UL> 
<IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"> <A HREF="ocean.html">Ocean and Climate : WOCE, CLIVAR and GCOS </A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><BR><IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><A HREF="gewex.html"> Aerosol-cloud-radiation interactions and GEWEX</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><BR><IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"> <A HREF="cont_bio.html#ContBiosph">Continental biosphere</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><BR> <IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><A HREF="polder.html"> A multidisciplinary program: POLDER </A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><BR> <IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><A HREF="atmos_che.html#AtmChem"> Middle-atmosphere and atmospheric chemistry</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><P> </UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="solid_ea.html#SolidEarth"><B>Space geodesy and the study of Solid Earth</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM></B> </UL>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
In the field of Earth and Environmental Sciences, CNES' action is indissociable from that of the French science research national center, CNRS, (Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique), the French Universities and the other national research organizations. Indeed, they are directly responsible for defining the scientific objectives and the national research programmes in which they participate. Furthermore, wherever the space research carried out in this field promotes the progress or the emergence of applications such as meteorology, harvest forecasts or monitoring of natural risks, it also mobilizes, along with CNES, the major French organizations responsible for these applications. <P>
CNES'action aims to define, to design, develop and operate, in close collaboration with the laboratories, the space systems, the ground segments and certain airbone experiments which meet the needs expressed by the scientific community, and its action also aims to promote the use of the observations collected by orbiting systems. CNES participates directly in space research in the fields of oceanography, geodesy and of the continental biosphere through two French laboratories it shares with CNRS, the LERTS and the UMR39/GRGS. <P>

<!--<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>-->
