<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Research concerning the continental biosphere</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<A NAME="ContBiosph">
<CENTER><img src="/images/cnes.gif"></CENTER><P>
<H1>Research concerning the continental biosphere</H1></A>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_forest.gif"><P>
<H2>Missions list</H2>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B> <A HREF="../spot/Mission.html">SPOT</A>: Earth observation mission Near Infrared and Visible imaging<BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><P></B><IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B> <A HREF="../polder/Mission2.html">POLDER</A>: POLarization and Directionality Of the Earth's Reflectances<BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 4, 1996</EM><P></B><IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B> <A HREF="http://www-projet.cnes.fr:8050/">VEGETATION</A>: Observation of the continental biosphere<P></B>
<IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B> <A HREF="http://www.orstom.fr/hapex/index.ht
ml">HAPEX/SAHEL</A><P></B>
</UL>

<IMG SRC="/icones/line_forest.gif"><P>
The complexity of the operating processes of the ecosystems and the heterogeneity of the coverage imposes an observation strategy concentrating on the integration of the scales and of the various parameters observed. This is supported by the combination of high and medium resolution spaceborne and airborne imagery and ground-based measurements. In this field the french space effort is based on the continuity and evolution of the SPOT programme. <P>

HVR (High Resolution Visible) imagery is particularly used in the framework of the SALT experiment to characterize the evolution of zones of sensitive gradients and <A HREF="http://www.orstom.fr/hapex/index.html">HAPEX</A> type surveys. <A HREF="../spot/Mission.html">SPOT 4</A> will constitute a decisive evolution with the addition of a mid-infrared channel to the HRV imager (having become HRVIR) and above all, thanks to the <A HREF="http://www-projet.cnes.fr:8050/">VEGETATION</A> system, co-financed by the European Union, France, Belgium, Sweden and Italy, and designed for permanent observation of the continental biosphere. On board SPOT, VEGETATION will provide a decisive advance in comparison with AVHRR, thanks to its capacity for medium resolution repetitive global coverage (1 km), to the improved atmospheric corrections (blue and mid-infrared bands) and to the simultaneous observation capacity at medium and high resolution which makes it possible to use it together with the HRVIR instrument. The data from <A HREF="../polder/Description.html">POLDER</A> on ADEOS and from VEGETATION on SPOT-4 will also be combinable to improve the atmospheric corrections, filter the angular effects or to provide complementary contributions to the characterization of vegetation. <P>

Many airborne surveys have been organized to study the processes, define and prepare the use of future satellites and carry out analyses at the scale of the grid of climate models. They utilize the airborne sensors VARAN, PORTOS, POLDER and ISM installed on the ARAT aircraft as well as other data which are accessible within the framework of international cooperation.  <P>

<!--<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>-->
