<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Space Geodesy and the study of Solid Earth</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<A NAME="SolidEarth"></A>
<PRE><IMG SRC="/images/p3559.gif">    <IMG SRC="/images/cnes.gif"><P></PRE>
<H5><I>Starlette</I></H5>

<H1>Space Geodesy and the study of Solid Earth</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<H2>Missions list</H2>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B> <A HREF="#Texte1">STARLETTE</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B> <A HREF="#Texte2">STELLA</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B> <A HREF="/topex/Mission.html">TOPEX/POSEIDON</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><P></B><IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B> <A HREF="/radar/Mission.html">SAR Interferometry</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><P></B><IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B> <A HREF="/doris/Mission.html">DORIS</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><P></B><IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B> <A HREF="/oersted/Mission.html">&Oslash;RSTED</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><P></B><IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B> <A HREF="/spot/Mission.html">SPOT</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><P></B><IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B> <A HREF="/tp-follow/Mission.html">TOPEX/POSEIDON Follow On</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><P></B></UL>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<A NAME="Texte1">
The study of the terrestrial potential fields, of terrestrial kinematics and of geodynamics is the French priority in this field.<P>

<A NAME="Texte2">
The laser reflecting satellite, STELLA, was launched by ARIANE at the end of 1993, to accompany SPOT-3, on an orbit selected to complete the coverage of STARLETTE, which is still operational. Its data are used to study the terrestrial gravity field and kinematics. The DORIS programme, thanks to the centimetric coherence of the earliest DORIS measurements obtained on SPOT-2 and  <A HREF="/topex/Mission.html">TOPEX-POSEIDON </A>and the homogeneous global coverage of the ground network of beacons makes it possible to study the relative movements of the plates as a whole, and to improve the gravity field on a large scale. The <A HREF="/doris/Mission.html">DORIS</A> system is also used on SPOT for a positioning mission whose development will be continuing on future SPOT (4 and 5) beyond the conclusive experiments conducted as part of SPOT 2&3 missions. Thanks to an evolution on the DORIS system, it is planned to perform, on <A HREF="/tp-follow/Mission.html">TOPEX-POSEIDON FOLLOW-ON (TPFO)</A>, from a higher altitude orbit, a still more accurate position determination mission in order to study lithospheric deformations. <P>

In 1993, CNES decided to participate in the Danish <A HREF="/oersted/Mission.html">&Oslash;RSTED </A>programme and began the development of a scalar magnetometer, destined for that magnetic field study microsatellite whose launching is planned for 1996.  <P>

