<HEAD>
<TITLE>Site du Mexique effondrement</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<IMG SRC="/icones/logo_radar.gif" ALIGN=LEFT> 
<H1>UNITED STATES / MEXICO : Field setting after irrigation</H1>

<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

The specific phase reflection of terrain is affected by a change of nature (growing vegetation, man-made changes, water content ...) which is detected by radar interferometry. <P>

<CENTER><TABLE>
<TR><TD><IMG SRC="/images/mex_13657_13614_amp.gif"><TD><IMG SRC="/images/mex_13657_2790_pha.gif">
<TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER>Amplitude image<TD ALIGN=CENTER>Phase image
<TR><TD ALIGN=CENTER>(observe the fields' sizes : small and desorganized in Mexico, broad and aligned in USA; the frontier is very clear).<TD ALIGN=CENTER>(observe the deflating of the terrain of about 6 cm, due to an intensive pumping of water, shown by the interferometric fringes).
</TABLE></CENTER> <P>

