<HEAD>
<TITLE>SCARAB Data Processing Center</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<H1>ScaRaB Data Processing Center</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

The ScaRaB Ground Segment joins two principal centers : The telemetry receiving and the remote control sending in Obninsk, Russia; the data processing and the instrumental programming at the CST. The communications between those two principal centers are made through a specialized and multi-projects connection installed by the "telematique" Division between the CNES and Moscow. The french part of the ground Segment is composed of three main systems "delocalized" which exchange necessary informations to progressively build more and more elaborated scientific products (data files).<P>

<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

The Ground Segment is composed of three main systems :
<UL>
 <LI> <STRONG>The Control and Survey Ground Segment</STRONG> (SSCS) which assure the operational missions in almost real time (in about 24 hours):
 <UL>
  <LI> The receiving and the setting of the scentific and constraints telemetry, the orbital reports and the informations of time adjustments.
  <LI> The survey of technological parameters (lamps and calibration black bodies), memories, control mechanisms.
  <LI> The instrumental operating mode control (programmation),here again, essentialy for onboard calibration domain.
  <LI> The decommutation, geographical localization of the measures and first level data production for the usable raw data.
 </UL><P>

 <LI> <STRONG>The Processing, Distribution and Archiving Ground Segment</STRONG> (SSEV) which offers, with a little longer time span :
 <UL>
  <LI> The realization of upper level data products, in "luminance" (level 1b), in flux after spectral corrections and geophysical transformations (level 2) and space-time averages, on eventually several onboard instruments (level 3).
  <LI> The centralized archiving of all the processing chain products and their access or their distribution to the whole scientific community involved.
 </UL><P>

 <LI> <STRONG>The Calibration and Validation Ground Segment</STRONG> (SSTDA) is the system specialized in calibration (transformation of the raw data in physical "luminance") and the validation which generates coefficients for level 1b products computation. It needs a precise knowledge based on an onboard calibration technology with different lamps, black bodies and filters.
</UL><P>

<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

From the data processing point of vue, the ScaRaB Ground Segment is a shared system which divides the different centers (operational for the SSCS, valuation for the  SSEV, computation and data conservation for the SSTDA) and based on various technologies (commercial-off-the-shelf <EM>Probe</EM> for the survey, <EM>Ingres and Oracle Data Base Managers, Files Transfert and Archiving Service</EM> and CD-ROM for the distribution).<P>

<!--<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>-->
