<HEAD>
<TITLE>ETHER access service</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<PRE><img src="/images/p6260.gif">     <img src="/images/cnes.gif"></PRE><P>
<H5><I> KIRUNA: ozone clouds</I></H5>
<A NAME="TOP"></A>
<H1>Ether : Access service to atmospheric chemistry data </H1>
<PRE>
"L'harmonieux Ether dans ces vagues d'azur <P>
Enveloppe les monts d'un fluide plus pur" <P>
              Lamartine (1790 1869) <P>
</PRE>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<H2> Table of contents</H2>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#introduction">Introduction</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#products">Products</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#cnes">CNES Contribution</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#planning">Development planning</A></B>
</UL>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

<H2><A NAME="introduction">Introduction</A></H2>

ETHER will be an access service to atmospheric chemical data, obtained thanks to space programs in which France has participated.<P>
ETHER will be installed for the benefit of the french scientific community. That is why ETHER will be a restricted access service.<P>
The french laboratories involved in research on atmospheric chemistry, are:
<P>
<UL>
<LI> Centre National de la Recherche M&eacute;t&eacute;orologique<BR>
<LI> DEMIRM/Observatoire de Paris<BR>
<LI> Institut Pierre Simon Laplace<BR>
<LI> Laboratoire d'A&eacute;rologie Toulouse <BR>
<LI> LERTS Toulouse<BR>
<LI> LOA Lille<BR>
<LI> Laboratoire de m&eacute;t&eacute;orologie dynamique/IPSL<BR>
<LI> LPCE Orl&eacute;ans<BR>
<LI> LPMA Paris-Universit&eacute; de Jussieu<BR>
<LI> Observatoire de Bordeaux<BR>
<LI> ONERA Palaiseau et Chalais-Meudon<BR>
<LI> Service d'A&eacute;ronomie/IPSL Verri&egrave;res le buisson, Paris-Universit&eacute; de Jussieu
</UL><P>

<A HREF="#TOP"">back to index </A><P>

<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

<H2><A NAME="products">Ether products</A></H2>
ETHER will allow access to public level 2, 3 data.<P>
The first experiences from which data will be available via ETHER, are: <P>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B>  <A HREF="../poam/Mission.html">POAM II</A> : boarded experience on SPOT 3 satellite</B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B>  <A HREF="../odin/Mission.html">ODIN</A> : boarded experience on ODIN satellite</B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B>  <A HREF="../uars/Mission.html#Windii">WINDII</A> : boarded experience on UARS satellite</B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> ILAS : boarded experience on ADEOS satellite</B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> IMG : boarded experience on ADEOS satellite</B><P>
</UL><P>

<A HREF="#TOP"">back to index </A><P>

<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

<H2><A NAME="cnes">CNES contribution</A></H2>
Ether is developped under CNES responsibility, with the collaboration of a mission group composed of french scientists. This group is responsible, in a scientific point of view, for the services ensured by Ether, and for the coherence of data available in Ether. <P>

<A HREF="#TOP"">back to index </A><P>

<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

<H2><A NAME="planning">Development planning</A></H2>
A first version of Ether, which allows access to POAM II, should be available end 96. <P>

<A HREF="#TOP"">back to index </A><P>

