<HEAD>
<TITLE>THE POLDER GROUND SEGMENT</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/logo_polder.gif"></CENTER>
<H1>THE POLDER GROUND SEGMENT</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<P>

<H2>Overall organization of  the POLDER on ADEOS Ground Segment</H2>

The ADEOS Ground Segment is responsible for command and control of the ADEOS Satellite telemetry acquisition, orbit control and restitution and processing of raw sensor data into level 0 data. Its NASDA/EOC component in charge of data acquisition and processing into level 0 data, delivers POLDER level 0 data to the CNES POLDER Ground Segment. <P>

The POLDER Ground Segment is located in CNES, Toulouse. <P>

It generates POLDER commands and delivers them to the NASDA/TACC element of the ADEOS Ground Segment for uplinking to ADEOS.  <P>

The CNES POLDER Ground Segment processes POLDER level 0 data into POLDER Standard Products. Such products are distributed by the CNES POLDER Ground Segment and the ADEOS Data Center to the worldwide user community. <P>

<A HREF="/images/Ground_segm1.gif">POLDER/ADEOS Ground Segment environment</A> <P>

<H2>Basic functions and architecture of the CNES POLDER Ground Segment</H2>

The CNES POLDER Ground Segment is made up of three components :
<UL>
- the POLDER <STRONG>Processing Centre</STRONG>;<BR>

- the <STRONG>Image Quality System</STRONG> responsible for the computation of calibration parameters and the verification of the radiometric and geometric quality of Level 1 Products;<BR>

- the <STRONG>Scientific Quality System</STRONG> responsible for the verification of the quality of Level 2 and 3 Products.<BR>
</UL> <P>

The POLDER Processing Centre itself is composed of four systems:
<UL>
- the <STRONG>Instrument Control System</STRONG> responsible for the generation of POLDER commands and for the control of housekeeping data,<BR>

- the <STRONG>Data Processing System</STRONG> responsible for processing level 0 data into higher level products,<BR>

- the <STRONG>Archiving and Management System</STRONG> responsible for the archiving of level 0 data and POLDER Standard Products,<BR>

- the <A HREF="/polder/Products.html#Information"><STRONG>User Interface System</STRONG></A> responsible for the delivery of POLDER Standard Products and the processing of user requests.<BR>
</UL> <P>

<A HREF="/images/Ground_segm3.gif">The POLDER Ground Segment architecture</A> <P>

<!--<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>-->
