<HEAD>
<TITLE>The DORIS Mission</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<A NAME="TOP"DORIS :></A>
<PRE><IMG SRC="/images/doris.gif">    <IMG SRC="/images/cnes.gif"></PRE><P>

<H1>DORIS: Doppler Orbitography and Radiolocation Integrated by Satellite</H1>

<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<H2>Table of contents</H2>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="descr.html">System description</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><P></B><IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="orbit.html">Orbit determination</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><P></B><IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="position.html">Positioning</A><BR>
<EM> Latest Update: April 2, 1996</EM><P></B></UL><P>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
The DORIS (Doppler Orbitography and Radiolocation Integrated by Satellite) system was developed by CNES to meet the needs in very precise satellite orbit determination and high accuracy location of ground beacons for point positioning. <P>

<!--<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>-->
