<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Polder Products</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<A NAME="TOP"></A>
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/logo_polder.gif"></CENTER>
<H1>The POLDER Products</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="#Levels">Three Levels of Products</A> <P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="#List">List, volume, media</A> <P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="#data">Data policy</A> <P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="#distribution">Distribution plan</A> <P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="#Information">Data distribution and information system (SIU)</A> <P>
</UL><P>

<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

The POLDER standard products are generated by the POLDER Ground Segment located at CNES and distributed to the users by CNES and NASDA for peaceful and non-commercial purposes only. <P>

<A NAME="Levels"><H2>Three Levels of Products</H2></A>

<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=3>
<TR><TD>3 levels of products and 3 geophysical processing lines will be available, namely : <STRONG>Ocean Color &amp; Marine Aerosols,  Land Surfaces &amp; Continental Aerosols, Radiation Budget & Clouds.
</TABLE></CENTER> <P>

<TABLE>
<TR><TD><IMG SRC="/images/grille.gif"><TD>All POLDER products are projected on a geocoded sinusoidal equal area projection grid of 6 km resolution. </TABLE><P>

<UL>
<LI> <STRONG>Level 1 :</STRONG> Measurements are radiometrically corrected, registred and organized pixel by pixel. The following parameters are included for each pixel of the viewing segment :<BR>
viewing geometry, normalized radiances and Stokes parameters at the Top Of the Atmosphere, for every channels and available viewing directions (with a maximum of 14). <P>

<STRONG>Browse :</STRONG> subsampled (1:5) from the level 1 product for only one channel (443nm over Ocean, 670nm over Land) and one direction (lowest reflectance over Ocean, smallest viewing angle over Land).<P>

<LI> <STRONG>Level 2 :</STRONG> the following geophysical parameters are computed from the level 1 product by the 3 processing lines ,  by orbit segment and <EM>after atmospheric corrections</EM> : <P>

<EM><STRONG>Ocean Color & Marine Aerosols :</STRONG></EM><BR>
  <UL>
  <LI> marine directional radiances at 443,490,565nm<BR>
  <LI> water leaving radiances at 443,490,565nm, pigment concentration, water type<BR>
  <LI> marine aerosols (3x3 resolution ) : optical thickness at 865nm, Angstr&ouml;m coefficient, refractive index, aerosol model<BR>
  </UL>

<EM><STRONG>Land Surfaces & Aerosols over Land :</STRONG></EM><BR>
  <UL>
  <LI> directional surface reflectances<BR>
  <LI> aerosols & water vapor over land (3x3 resolution) : optical thickness at 865nm, Angstr&ouml;m coefficient, refractive index, water vapor content<BR>
  </UL>

<EM><STRONG>Radiation Budget & Clouds :</STRONG></EM><BR>
  <UL>
  <LI> 9x9 pixels synthesis of the following parameters : cloud cover, optical thickness, oxygen pressure, rayleigh pressure, cloud phase (water or ice), albedo, normalized directional radiances at 443, 670, 865nm,and Short Wave, angular distributions.
  </UL>
<P>

<TABLE>
<TR><TD><IMG SRC="/images/projec.asie3.gif"><TD><IMG SRC="/images/projec.europ3.gif">
</TABLE> <P>
<EM>POLDER level 1 and 2 products are provided by orbit segment</EM><P>

<LI> <STRONG>Level 3 :</STRONG> temporal synthesis (month or decade) on POLDER global grid of the level 2 geophysical parameters (see above), plus: <P>
  <UL>
  <LI> vegetation index and surface directional model (Land Surfaces, level 3)<BR>
  <LI> angular distributions of total polarized reflectances by scene type (Radiation Budget and Clouds, level 3).<BR>
  </UL>
</UL>

<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to contents </A><P>

<A NAME="List"><H2>List, volume, media</H2></A>

<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=3>
<TR><TH ALIGN=CENTER>PRODUCT<BR>LEVEL<TH ALIGN=CENTER>PRODUCT<BR>LINE<TH ALIGN=CENTER>GENERIC CODE<TH ALIGN=CENTER>COVERAGE<BR>/frequency<TH ALIGN=CENTER>RESOLUTION<BR>(pixel x pixel)<TH ALIGN=CENTER>MEDIA<BR>for global<BR>distribution**<TH>PRODUCT<BR>SIZE<BR>ESTIMATION<BR>(Mbyte)
