<HEAD>
<TITLE>The START project</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/plaket33.gif" ALIGN="MIDDLE"></CENTER><P>
<H1>THE START PROJECT</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
A worldwide fieldwork programme and research network are required to achieve these goals, involving scientists from all nations. There is a critical need to stimulate research which focus on regional origins and implications of global change and to promote interdisciplinary studies on a regional basis.
<BR>
The <A HREF="geobio.html">IGBP</A> SysTem for Analysis, Research and Training (START) provides the necessary structure of networks, centres and sites to address the regional aspects of global change. It also provides training, to strengthen the much-needed participation of developing countries in IGBP research. Regional Research Networks should progressively be established in each of the 13 regions which have been defined as a primary basis in terms of scientific needs, biogeographical features and existing regional collaborations.
<BR>
An important effort in developing START activities is being directed at the Mediterranean (MED) and Northern Africa (NAF) region. These are currently subject to strong interannual climate variability, and could be severely impacted by further shifts in climate patterns. <P>

