<HEAD>
<TITLE>SEAWIF</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<A NAME = "TOP"></A>
<CENTER><img src="/images/cnes.gif"></CENTER><P>
<H1>The CNES SeaWIFS Data and Information Service</H1>

<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

The objective of the CNES SeaWIFS Data and Information Service consists in acting as the unique interface between the <A HREF="http://seawifs.gsfc.nasa.gov:80/SEAWIFS.html">GSFC/DAAC</A> that archives all SeaWIFS products derived from the NASA/GSFC ground segment processing, and the french scientists selected as PIs or CoIs by <A HREF="http://seawif.gsfc.nasa.gov:80/SEAWIFS.html">NASA</A> in the frame of the NASA announcement of opportunity. It is thus a restricted access service. It will help the selected scientists to get the data they need for their scientific investigation and will set up a long term reference central archive.<P>

The CNES SeaWIFS data and Information Service should be active 10 years after the end of the nominal lifetime of the SeaWIFS space segment. Thus, it will help selected scientists to jointly use SeaWIFS data with data from other orbiting space sensors.<P>

