<HEAD>
<TITLE> Description</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<A NAME="TOP"></A>
<PRE><IMG SRC="/images/topex2.gif">       <IMG SRC="/images/cnes.gif"></PRE>
<H1>TOPEX/POSEIDON CNES Contribution : Payload and Services</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<H2>Table of Contents</H2>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B><A HREF="/topex/description.html#payload"> Payload contribution </A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B><A HREF="#services"> Services contribution </A></B><P>
</UL>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

<A NAME="services"><H2> Services Contribution </H2></A>
Raw data from the two French instruments are extracted and transmitted daily to the french ground segment (SSDP) located in Toulouse. Within the SSDP is the DORIS - POSEIDON Control Centre, the CTDP, operated and run by CNES subsidiary CLS. The CTDP preprocesses the data, does the scientific processing, monitors the French instruments, and generates the work program and the commands. The DORIS Orbitography Department at CNES calculates the precise satellite ephemeris from the DORIS measurements.In parallel, data from the US instruments are processed at JPL. The two agencies exchange the processed informations. Then, each science investigator can access the whole data set from the mission thanks active archive centers located in the US (PO-DAAC, JPL) and France (AVISO, CNES).<P>

