<HEAD>
<TITLE>SCARAB Aims and Organization</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/cnes.gif"></CENTER>
<H1>Mission Aims and Organization</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

ScaRaB observations are expected to contribute to advances in climate-related resarch on claoud/radiation interactions, participating to the Global Energy and Water cycle Experiment (GEWEX), in the frame work of the Word Climate Research Programme. <P>
ScaRaB(Scanner for Radiation Budget) is a cooperation between :
<UL>
<LI> the French Centre National d'Etudes Spatiales (CNES)
<LI> the French Institut National des Sciences de l'Univers of Centre National de la Recherche Scientifique more particularly with the <A HREF="http://www.lmd.ens.fr/observations-spatiales.html#1">Laboratory of Dynamic Meteorology</A> (LMD/INSU/CNRS)
<LI> the Russian Federal Service for Hydrometeorology and Environmental Monitoring (ROSHYDROMET)
<LI> the company responsible for the METEOR satellite (NIIEM)
<LI> the Deutsche Agentur f&uuml;r Raumfahrt-Angelegenheiten (DARA) 
</UL>
ScaRaB has  already been flown on METEOR 3-7 satellite launched on January, 25 1994. One year of data has been acquired. <P>
A second instrument is considered for flight on board RESSURS satellite in 1997. <P>

