<HEAD>
<TITLE>The SCARAB Instrument</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/cnes.gif"></CENTER>
<H1>The ScaRaB Instrument</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

ScaRaB is a broad band, four channel scanning radiometer, measuring radiance upwelling from the top of the atmosphere. <P>
The instrument was launched on January 25, 1994. The data were recieved and processed from February 24, 1994 to March 6, 1995.<P>
The channels are :
<UL>
<LI> 2 "narrow" bands
<UL>
<LI> 0.55 to 0.65   &#181;m (visible) <BR>
<LI> 10.5 to 12.5 &#181;m (IR window)<P>
</UL>
for characterization of cloudy views<P>
<LI> 2 broad bands
<UL>
<LI> 0.2 to 4  &#181;m (short wave)<BR>
<LI> 0.2 to &gt; 50 &#181;m (total channel)<P>
</UL>
for measurement of radiation budget
</UL>
For ScaRaB on METEOR 3, the pixel size at nadir is 42.5 km and the total swath width is about 3200 Km.<P>

<IMG SRC="/images/instr_ScaRaB.gif"><P>
The model number 0 of ScaRaB instrument. <P>

