<HEAD>
<TITLE>SCARAB Products</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/cnes.gif"></CENTER>
<H1>ScaRaB Products</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
ScaRaB/METEOR is operated by TSOUP (Russia). Telemetry data are recieved at NPO-PLANETA (Russia) data centre then transmitted to ScaRaB data
centre in Centre Spatial de Toulouse. <P>
Standard products are then elaborated :
<UL>
<LI> LEVEL 0 products are :
<UL>
<LI> corrected, ref-formatted and chronological telemetry.
</UL>
<P><LI> LEVEL 1 products are :
<UL>
<LI> filtered radiances ( 4 bands) with datation and localisation at the pixel level. These data are ordered following the acquisition time.
</UL>
<P><LI> LEVEL 2 products are :
<UL>
<LI> filtered radiances (4 bands)<BR>
<LI> unfiltered SW and LW  radiances and radiant exitances<BR>
<LI> cloud scene identification<BR>
</UL>

<P><LI> LEVEL 3 products are :
<UL>
<LI> quasi instantaneous regional mean values, on a 2.5&#176; by 2.5&#176; grid, for SW and LW radiant exitances<BR>
<LI> daily mean regional values<BR>
<LI> monthly mean of the diurnal variation and of the cloud coverage<BR>
</UL>
</UL> <P>

