<HEAD>
<TITLE>The &Oslash;RTED Mission Summary</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/cnes.gif"></CENTER>
<H1>&Oslash;RSTED Mission Summary</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<P>
<H2>Table of Contents</H2>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B><A HREF="#objectives.html"> &Oslash;RSTED mission objectives</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#project">The &Oslash;RSTED project</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#payload">The payload</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B><A HREF="#segment">The ground segment</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#contribution"">CNES contribution</A></B><P>

</UL>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<H2><A NAME="objectives">Mission Objectives</A></H2>
<P>
The primary science objectives of &Oslash;RSTED are:
<UL>
<LI> the studies of the generation of the magnetic fields in the fluid core and the magnetic and electrical properties of the solid earth
<LI> the studies of Earth's magnetic field as the controlling parameter of the magnetosphere and of all the physical processes that take place in the Earth's plasma environment, including phenomena like aurora and magnetic storms.
The secondary mission objectives are related to the contribution to the technological advancement of small satellites and associated flight and ground based subsystem development and to the demonstration of the feasibility of small satellites as a means of performing well focused world-class space science exploration, within a relatively short time horizon.
</UL>

<P><A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<H2><A NAME="project">The &Oslash;RSTED Project</A></H2>
The &Oslash;RSTED Project has been initiated as a cooperative effort between Danish research institutions and space related industry. The project started in september 1993. The satellite will be launched in early 1997. After a two month commissioning phase, a one full year of science observation, including science analysis is foreseen.

<P><A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<H2><A NAME="payload">The Payload</A></H2>
The science payload shall consist of four basic subsystems: a Compact Spherical Coil (CSC) triaxial magnetometer for measuring magnetic field vectors, an Overhauser proton-precession magnetometer (OVH) for measuring magnetic field amplitude, a Star Imager (SIM) to determine the attitude of the CSC magnetometer and a Six solid-state Charged Particles Detectors (CPD) to measure energetic particle radiation in the upper polar atmosphere.

<P><A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<H2><A NAME="segment">The ground segment</A></H2>
The Science Data Center (SDC) is under control of the Danish &Oslash;rsted Project. The SDC will archive the &Oslash;rsted mission raw data and shall provide CNES with an access point to the dataset. SDC is in charge of higher level processing of the dataset.
CNES shall distribute the high level datasets provided by SDC to the French Science community.

<P><A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<H2><A NAME="contribution">The CNES contribution</A></H2>
Considering the long term involvement of the french scientific community in studies of the internal and external magnetic fields, CNES has decided to provide the Overhauser magnetometer (OVH).<P>

The flight model of the OVH magnetometer has been delivered in october 1995.

<P><A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<!--<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>-->
