<HEAD>
<TITLE>The &Oslash;RTED Science Organization</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/cnes.gif"></CENTER>
<H1>&Oslash;RSTED Science Organization</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<P>
<H2>Danish Investigators</H2>
Danish Scientific Institutes participating in the project are :<BR>
<UL>
<LI> Solar-Terrestrial Physics Division, Danish Meteorological Institute (DMI)
<LI> Department of Electrophysics, Technical University of Denmark (TUD)
<LI> Geophysical Department, Niels Bohr Institute, University of Copenhagen (NBI)
<LI> Danish Space Research Institute (DSRI)
</UL><P>

<H2>International Investigators</H2>
in addition to NASA and Institut de Physique du globe de Paris (IPGP). The Principal Investigators (PIs) for the various scientific experiments listed below .<P>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<PRE>
 Compact Spherical Coil (CSC) Fluxgate Magnetometer   F.Primdahl, O.V.Nielsen, TUD
 Overhauser Proton-Processing Magnetometer (OVH)      J.Achache, IPGP
                                                      I.Laursen, TUD
 Star Imager                                          J.J&oslash;rgensen, TUD
 High-Energy Particle Detectors                       P.Stauning, DMI
 Main Magnetic Field Modelling                        C.C.Tscherning, T.Risbo, NBI
                                                      R.Langel, NASA
 External Magnetic Field Analysis                     E.Friis-Christensen, DMI
 _________________________________________________________________________________
<STRONG>
 Project Scientist                                    E.Friis-Christensen, DMI
</STRONG>
</PRE>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif">
<P>
<H2>Co-investigator Team</H2>
Completing the group of PIs, an International Co-investigator Team will be established based on proposals submitted by the international scientific community. 77 research groups from 54 institutes in 17 countries have indicate their interest. The selected co-investigator team will <BR>
<UL>
<LI> obtain access to the full, validated &Oslash;rsted data set
<LI> provide auxiliary data, derived products, reports, services, etc. to the &Oslash;rsted Project
<LI> obtain access to the &Oslash;rsted Newsletter file.
</UL><P>

Support to the team from &Oslash;rsted Solar-Terrestrial Physics Laboratory at DMI is planned to consist of <BR>
<UL>
<LI> arrangement of international &Oslash;rsted workshops / team meetings in Denmark
<LI> sponsorship for limited number of visiting scientist positions (each of three to six month duration).
</UL><P>

<H2>Science Advisory Committee</H2>
An Internatioanl &Oslash;rsted Science Advisory Committee is beeing organized, including representations from the selected Co-investigators. Its members<BR>
<UL>
<LI> have access to the full &Oslash;rsted data set in satellite coordinates
<LI> are expected to contribute significantly to the overall objectives of the &Oslash;rsted mission
<LI> are expected to participate actively in the planning, calibration, or derivation of products based on &Oslash;rsted data
<LI> are expected to be fully funded by their national agencies.
</UL><P>

