<HEAD>
<TITLE>The &Oslash;RTED Science Data Policy</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/cnes.gif"></CENTER>
<H1>&Oslash;RSTED Science Data Policy</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<P>
A Data Publication Policy with three basic elements has been defined for the mission :<P>

<STRONG>Basic Data</STRONG><BR>
Products form the &Oslash;rsted Science Data Centre (SDC), available only to satellite Principal Investigators and members of the &Oslash;rsted Science Advisor Committee :<BR>
<UL>
<LI> Level 0 data set
 <UL>
 - raw data set after initial verification<BR>
 - available 24 to 48 hours after acquisition at the SDC<BR>
 </UL>
<LI> Level 1 data set
 <UL>
 - calibrated and corrected data in instrument coordinates<BR>
 - full time resolution<BR>
 - available 3 to 5 weeks after acquisition.<BR>
 </UL>
</UL><P>
Both data sets will be archived on CD-ROM and will be copied to the satellite investigators.<P>

<STRONG>Processed Data</STRONG><BR>
SDC Data products available to the &Oslash;rsted Science Co-investigators Team :<P>

<UL>
<LI> Level 1 vector magnetometer data set
 <UL>
 - calibrated and corrected<BR>
 - Earth-oriented coordinates<BR>
 - available 3 to 5 weeks after acquisition.<BR>
 </UL>
<LI> Level 1 particle data set
 <UL>
 - particle count rates and direction cosines in Earth-oriented coordinate system.<BR>
 </UL>
<LI> Level 2 data set
 <UL>
 - subset of Level 1, selected according to investigator criteria.<BR>
 </UL>
<LI> Level 3 data set
 <UL>
 - geomagnetic field model coefficients.<BR>
 </UL>
<LI> Summary listings of processing characteristics and data characteristics.
<LI> Summary plots (all data) and polar orbit plots (selected data).
</UL><P>

Initial Level 1 data will be provided on CD-ROM. Updates will be provided as calibration constant and algorithms through on-line access via Internet connections.<P>

<STRONG>Final Data</STRONG><BR>
SDC data products freely available to the scientific community (after 12 months) :<P>

<UL>
<LI> Reduced data set
 <UL>
 - final calibrated and corrected data<BR>
 - time resolution approximately 10 sec, corresponding to a spatial resolution of 80 km.
 </UL>
</UL> <P>

