<HTML>
<HEAD>
TITLE>The &Oslash;RTED Science Instrument</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<CENTER>une image de l'instrument</CENTER>
<H1>The &Oslash;RSTED Science Instrument</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<P>
<H2>Fluxgate Magnetometer</H2>
Two of the instruments have been developed at the Technical University of Denmark :
<UL>
<LI> The compact Spherical Coil (CSC) Triaxal Fluxgate Magnetometer comprises three orthogonal fluxgate sensors inside lightweight coils on a spherical surface. It has measurement error less than 1.5 nT.
</UL><P>

<H2>Star Imager</H2>
<UL>
<LI> The Star Imager instrument measures satellite attitude based on an onboard star catalogue. It contains a Charge Coupled Detector (CCD) camera with 752 x 52 pixels, and an Intel 80486, 50 MHz processor. It has an angular resolution of 2 arcsec.
</UL>
These instruments are optically aligned, so magnetic field vectors can be measured directly without distortion from movements in the mechanical structure of the satellite.<P>
<BR>

The &Oslash;rsted payload also includes the following instruments :<BR>
<H2>Overhauser Magnetometer</H2>
<UL>
<LI> The <STRONG>Overhauser Proton-Precession Magnetometer</STRONG> provides magnetic field scalar values with an absolute measurement error of less than 0.5 nT. The instrument is supplied by LETI/CNES.<P>
</UL><P>
<H2>Charged Particle Detectors</H2>
<UL>
<LI> Six Solid State <STRONG>Charged Particle Detectors</STRONG> are build at the Danish Meteorlogical Institute to measure :
 <UL>
 <LI> High energy electrons (30 KeV to 1 MeV)
 <LI> Protons (200 KeV to 30 MeV) and
 <LI> Alpha particles (1 to 100 MeV).
 </UL><P>
</UL><P>
<H2>TurboRogue</H2>
<UL>
<LI> A <STRONG>TurboRogue</STRONG> GPS reciever is being flown to generate atmospheric occultation data for GPS satellites on an experimental basis. It is supplied by JPL/NASA.
</UL><P>
<A HREF="/images/schema_instr_oerst.gif"><H2>Science Instruments schema</H2></A> <P>

<!--<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>-->
<HR>
<A HREF="/Is.html"><IMG SRC="/icones/Left.gif"></A>
<A HREF="/Missions.html"><IMG SRC="/icones/Right.gif"></A>
<A HREF="/introGEO.html"><IMG SRC="/icones/home.gif"></A>
