<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>The &Oslash;RTED Ground Segment</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<CENTER><IMG SRC="/images/cnes.gif"></CENTER>
<A HREF="/images/grnd_segm_oerst.gif"><H1>&Oslash;RSTED Ground Segment</H1></A>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<P>
<H2>Control Centre</H2>
The &Oslash;rsted control Centre has been designed using a commercial product environment (EasyMAP). It has the same standardization features as mentioned for the <A HREF="/oersted/Spaceseg.html#Equipment">Ground Support Equipment</A>. Functions of the Centre include :<BR>
<UL>
<LI> Mission Management
<LI> Satellite monitoring and control
<LI> Flight dynamics
<LI> Ground station monitoring and control
<LI> Science data pre-processing
<LI> Simulation
<LI> Emergency backup facilities
</UL><P>

<H2>Ground Stations</H2>
Ground stations in Copenhagen, Aalborg and Ballerup are linked to the Control Centre via ISDN communication line. Each station contains the following modules :<BR>
<UL>
<LI> Receiver / transmitter electronics
<LI> Telemetry encoder / decoder
<LI> Automatic antenna tracker
<LI> Communication computer
<LI> Archiving capability
<LI> Power supply and stand-by power backup
</UL><P>

<H2>Science Data Centre</H2>
The Science Data Centre (SDC) supports scientific analysis of data by the Principal Investigators (PIs). It is also responsible for archiving of final data sets, and for distribution of processed data to the co-investigators. Major SDC functions include :<BR>
<UL>
<LI> Validation and data quality check
<LI> Determination of instrument calibration parameters
<LI> Correction and calibration of raw data, conversion to scientific units
<LI> Conversion to Earth-oriented coordinates
<LI> Generation of summary plots
<LI> Archiving of all data parameters
<LI> Updating of on-line catalogues
<LI> Preparation of specialized data sets for scientific investigators
<LI> Acquisition of ancillary ground data
</UL><P>
The core of the SDC is located at DMI, the host institution for the Science Coordination Office. It is equipped with network connections to Danish PIs as well as to the international scientific network, Internet.<P>

