<A NAME="Flight"><H2>Flight opportunity</H2></A>

The first flight opportunity for IASI is the <A HREF="/images/metop.gif">METOP-1 satellite</A>, which is being developed by ESA in cooperation with EUMETSAT for launch by the end of 2001 and will be operated by EUMETSAT. METOP-1 within the EPS programme is the first satellite of a series of polar orbiting satellites in the monitoring (AM) orbit, as part of the Joint Polar Orbiting Satellite System with the NOAA afternoon (PM) satellites which will provide services for operational meteorology and climate monitoring.<P>

The meteorological core payload of the METOP-1 satellite comprises (see <A HREF="/iasi/Annexe1.html">Meteorological payload</A> for more details) : <P>

<UL>
<LI> the Advanced Microwave Sounding Unit (AMSU-A), a microwave 15 channels multispectral temperature sounder ;
<LI> the Microwave Humidity Sounder (MHS) (replaces the Advanced Microwave Sounding Unit (AMSU-B)), a 5 channels humidity sounder ;
<LI> the High Infrared Sounder (HIRS/3), a sounder with 19 infrared and one visible channels ;
<LI> the Advanced Very High Resolution Radiometer (AVHRR/3), a cloud and surface imager with 6 channels in the visible and infrared.
</UL> <P>

Some of the operational features of IASI such as the scan cycle will be synchronised with the companion meteorological payload to facilitate a synergic use of data from all instruments, which is essential to achieve the EPS mission objectives. <P>

