<HEAD>
<TITLE> CNES payload and services</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<A NAME="TOP"></A>
<H1>CNES Payload and Services contribution</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<P>
<H2>Table of contents</H2>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF ="#Payload">Payload contribution</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF ="#Services">Services contribution</A></B>
</UL>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<P>
<A NAME="Contrib"><H1>Payload  Contribution</H1></A>
WINDII is the result of a cooperation between CNES and CSA (Canadian Space Agency) <P>

CNES with Service d'A&eacute;ronomie has participated and supported CSA in the design, development, test, integration, verification and on-orbit validation of the WINDII system where appopriate. <P>

It has participated with CSA in the definition and update of the telemetry and command interface between the WINDII instrument and the ground system. <P>

It has designed, developped, tested, integrated and provided to CSA the WINDII optical baffles and the WINDII instrument in-fligth calibration system. This system includes a laser source, RF calibration lamps and a tungsten lamp.<P>

In accordance with the scientific requirements, it has defined, designed,developped, tested, integrated and provided to CSA the scientific data processing software. <P>

The CNES has supported spatial laboratories involved in atmosphere studies, to put in place correlation experiences of UARS. Those experiences are done using ground , ballons or airborne mittels. for a precise instant, they give for a particular site equivalent data to UARS data. The correlation of this data from different origine, allows the UARS experiences validation. <P>
 
Thanks to this block of actions, the french laboratories involved in the UARS program dispose of all WINDI data and a part of UARS data. <P>

<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>
<HR><P>

<A NAME="Services"><H1>UARS Services in CNES</H1></A>

WINDII data and a little part of UARS data could be fetchable through <A HREF="../ether/Ether.html">Ether</A> at the middle of 1997 by French scientists <P>

<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

