<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ADEOS Services</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<A NAME="TOP"></A>
<PRE>Logo NASDA                           <IMG SRC="/images/cnes.gif"> <P>
</PRE>
<H1>CNES contribution: Payload and Services</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<P>
<H2>Table of contents</H2>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><A HREF="#payload"><B> Payload contribution</B></A><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><A HREF="#services"><B> Services contribution</B></A><P>
</UL><P>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<P>

<H2><A NAME="payload">Payload contribution</A></H2>

The French Centre National d'Etudes Spatiales (CNES) and the National Space Development Agency of Japan (NASDA) jointly announce the opportunity to conduct climate-related research on aerosol cycling, aerosol-cloud-radiation interactions, the Earth radiation budget, ocean primary production and continental biosphere dynamics using data from the POLDER (POLarization and Directionality of Earth Reflectances) sensor developed by CNES and the other ADEOS instruments developed by the agencies NASDA, NASA and other organisms as MITI (Ministry of International Trade and Industry) and EA (Environmental japanese Agency). <P>
<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<H2><A NAME="services">Services contribution</A></H2>
CNES is setting up two data management systems :

<UL>
<LI> The POLDER production center (POLDER Ground Segment). This center will generate high level results from raw data, and dispatch them to scientific teams involved in the POLDER program.
<LI> The ADEOS node. This node enables all selected french scientific teams to fetch all ADEOS experiences data.
</UL>
To access to informations and data from ADEOS missions, you can connect to:
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/balljaun.gif"><B><A HREF="../polder/GroundSegm.html"> CNES Polder Ground Segment</A></B><P>
</UL>
<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

