<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Payload Composition</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<A NAME="TOP"><H1>Payload Composition</H1></A>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

<H2> Table of Contents</H2>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#EDIs">ESA Developed Instruments (EDI's)</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#AO">Announcement of Opportunity (AO) Instruments</A></B><P>
</UL>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

The payload for the ENVISAT - 1 mission consists of 2 categories of instruments, viz: 
<UL>
<LI> ESA Developed Instruments (EDI's) <BR>
<LI> Announcement of Opportunity (AO) Instruments<BR>
</UL>
This grouping of insruments into 2 categories reflects the mechanism by which individual instruments are planned to be financed, developed and delivered. 

<H2><A NAME="EDIs">ESA Developed Instruments</A></H2>
These comprise:
<UL>
<H3><IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="meris.html">MERIS (MEdium Resolution Imaging Spectrometer)</A></H3><P>
A wide swath, medium spatial resolution, imaging radiometer operating in the visible/near infrared for utilisation over both oceans and land surface.<P>
 
<H3><IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="mipas.html">MIPAS (Michelson Interferometric Passive Atmospheric Sounder)</A></H3><P>
A limb sounding passive Michelson interferometer operating in the mid infrared for studying atmospheric trace gases.<P>
 
<H3><IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="RA2.html">RA - 2 (Radar Altimeter - 2)</A></H3><P>
An active microwave altimeter based on the ERS radar altimeter but with an improved perfrormance, in particular over land and ice. As is the case for the ERS instruments, it will include a Laser Retro-Reflector (LRR) and a Microwave sounder . A DORIS instrument (AO) for determining the precise orbit will complement the altimetry package.<P>
 
<H3><IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="asar.html">ASAR (Advanced Synthetic Aperture Radar)</A></H3><P>
An advanced C-band imaging SAR with active array antenna beam pointing, horizontal and vertical polarisations, and including a wave directional spectra monitoring mode.<P>
 
<H3><IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="gomos.html">GOMOS (Global Ozone Monitoring by Occultation of Stars)</A></H3><P>
A limb viewing, UV/visible/near infra red spectrometer monitoring the concentration of ozone and other traces gases by stellar occultation. <P>
</UL>
These instruments will be developed and produced by ESA within the ENVISAT -1 programme.<P> 

<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<H2><A NAME="AO">Announcement of Opportunity (AO) Instruments</A></H2>
These comprise: 
<UL>
<H3><IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="sciamachy.html">SCIAMACHY (Scanning Imaging Absorption Spectrometer for Atmospheric CHartographY)</A></H3> <P>
A UV/visible/near infra red grating spectrometer (limb and nadir viewing) measuring the concentration of various chemical species in both the troposphere and stratosphere (an evolution of GOME on ERS - 2) <P>

<H3><IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="aatsr.html">AATSR (Advanced Along Tracks Scanning Radiometer)</A></H3><P>
A UV/visible/near infra red/thermalinfra red, conically scanning, imaging radiometer viewing each point through two different atmospheric slant paths (and at two different incidence angles) for precise ocean surface temperature measurements and for land observations (derived from the ATSR on ERS - 1 and the ATSR - 2 on ERS - 2)<P>

<H3><IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"> <A HREF="/doris/descr.html">DORIS(Doppler Orbit Radiopositioning Integrated by Satellite)</A></H3> <P>
An utmost precise orbit determination system based on Doppler signal measurements between a spaceborne receiver and a worldwide network of emitting ground beacons.<P>
</UL>
The instruments in this category would be developed nationaly and would therefore be provided in kind to the programme. <P>
<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<!--<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>-->
