<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ENVISAT Ground Segment</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<A NAME="TOP"><H1>ENVISAT - 1 Ground Segment</H1></A> 
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<P>
<H2> Table of contents</H2>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#facilities">ESA Facilities</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#services">National Facilities Providing ESA Services</A></B><P>
</UL>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

The ENVISAT - 1 ground segment includes a flight operation segment, dedicated to mission control and operations, a payload data segment ensuring payload operation planning, data acquisition, processing, distribution and archiving, and user services. The ENVISAT - 1 ground segment is composed of ESA own facilities and National Facilities of ESA members.
 
<H2><A NAME="facilities">ESA Facilities</A></H2>
ESA provides the Flight Operation Segment (FOS) managed from ESOC and in charge of mission and operation planning and command / control of the satellite and the Payload Data Segment (PDS) incharge of data acquisition, near real time and Fast Delivery (FD) services, archiving of low rate instrument data and distribution of data sets to National Processing and Archiving Center for further processing, distribution and archiving of value added products.<P>
 
<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<H2><A NAME="services">National Facilities Providing ESA Services</A></H2>
The national Processing and Archiving Centers (PACs, concept drawn from the ERS - 1 experience) will be centers for off-line production and archiving of mission products, with the product validation being under ESA supervision and relying upon support and advice from Expert Support Laboratories (ESLs).<P>
The roles of the various national PACs are envisaged to be as follows: 
For high rate instruments: 
<UL>
<LI> ASAR High Rate Data are assigned to D-PAC (Germany), I-PAC (Italy) and UK-PAC (United Kingdom), <BR>
<LI> MERIS Full Resolution Data would be assigned to UK-PAC (United Kingdom), I-PAC (Italy) and Spain,</UL> 

For low rate instruments, the thematic split is: 
<UL>
<LI> Altimetry (i.e. RA-2, MWR and DORIS) including precise orbit determination is assigned to <A HREF="/fpac/Is.html">F-PAC</A> (France), with support of D-PAC and I-PAC for coordination of the international laser network for precise orbit determination validation, <BR>
<LI> ASAR wave is assigned to F-PAC, <BR>
<LI> Atmospheric chemistry (MIPAS, SCIAMACHY and GOMOS) is assigned to D-PAC, with Finland contribution for GOMOS and I-PAC for SCIAMACHY, <BR>
<LI> AATSR are assigned to UK-PAC, <BR>
<LI> MERIS low Rate Global is assigned to S-PAC (Sweden), with contribution of I-PAC.</UL>  <BR>

In addition, National Stations of several participating states are already considering providing ASAR and MERIS regional near real time services as well as offlines services><P>
<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

