<HEAD>
<TITLE>POLDER Partners</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<A NAME="TOP"></A>
<H1>POLDER Partners</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

The POLDER <STRONG>instrument</STRONG> has been developed by CNES in partnership with the industrial contractors shown on the diagram. <P>

<TABLE>
<TR><TD><IMG SRC="/images/instpol1.gif"><TD>
instrument manager : SERESO<BR>
onboard software : ALTEN<BR>
converters and housekeeping : EREMS<BR>
optomechanical block : CERCO<BR>
detection unit : SOPELEM/SOFRETEC<BR>
CCD : THOMSON<BR>
bearings : ADR<BR>
motor : SAGEM<BR>
structure : LATECOERE<BR>
multilayer insulation : ZODIAC<BR>
video : SEXTANT
</TABLE><P>

The POLDER <STRONG>ground segment</STRONG> has been developed, under cnes prime contractorship, in conjunction with various industrial contractors:<BR>
<UL>
THOMSON SYSECA (POLDER production center and level 1 processing system)<BR>
CAP SESA REGIONS (image quality system)<BR>
CISI Ingenierie (level 2 and 3 processing systems)<BR>
and partners:<BR>
CEA/LMCE (scientific processing expertise)<BR>
Mto France (supply of meteorological data)<BR>
</UL>

The <STRONG>scientific</STRONG> algorithms have been defined and validated by several science laboratories:<BR><BR>
<UL>
Laboratoire d'Optique Atmosphrique (<A HREF="http://loasys.univ-lille1.fr/Welcome.html">LOA</A>)<BR>
Laboratoire de Modlisation du Climat et de l'Environnement (LMCE)<BR>
Centre d'Etudes Spatiales de la BIOsphre (<A HREF="http://www.cesbio.cnes.fr">CESBIO</A>)<BR>
Laboratoire de Physique et Chimie Marines (LPCM)<BR>
Laboratoire de M&eacute;t&eacute;orologie Dynamique (<A HREF="http://www.lmd.ens.fr">LMD</A>) <P>
</UL>

