<HEAD>
<TITLE>MIPAS</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<H1>MIPAS - Michelson Interferometric Passive Atmospheric Sounder</H1>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<P>
<H2>Table of contents</H2>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#description">Description and characteristics</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#synergism">Synergism with other ENVISAT - 1 instrument</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#dependance">Dependance on other data</A></B><P>
</UL>
<P><IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

<H2><A NAME="description">Description and characteristics</A></H2>
MIPAS is a limb sounder operating in emission in the near to mid infrared. The overall aim of MIPAS is to obtain new information on the composition, the dynamics and the radiation balance in the middle atmosphere and possibly in the upper troposphere. To this end it is intended to measure H<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>O, O<MATH><SUB>3</SUB></MATH>, CO, N<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>O, F11, F12, F22, CCl<MATH><SUB>4</SUB></MATH>, CF<MATH><SUB>4</SUB></MATH>, NO, NO<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>, ClO, H<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>O<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>, HNO<MATH><SUB>4</SUB></MATH>, N<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>O<MATH><SUB>5</SUB></MATH>, ClONO<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>, HOCl, HNO<MATH><SUB>3</SUB></MATH>, OCS, C<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>H<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>, and C<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>H<MATH><SUB>6</SUB></MATH> plus temperature (CO<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>) and possibly thin cirrus and polar stratospheric clouds. MIPAS will provide data not only of relevance to "chemical" investigations but also to radiative studies.<P>
MIPAS is a cooled, high resolution (about 0.05 cm&#175; &#185; apodised), radip scanning Michelson interferometer. It has a scanning FOV in the horizontal both rearwards and to the side. It is intended to operate over the height range 5 to 150 km with a vertical resolution of 3 km and a resolution in the horizontal of 30 km. Spectroscopically it spans the range 4.15 to 14.6 &#181;m. The MIPAS instrument is capable of acquiring data continuously.<P>

<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<H2><A NAME="synergism">Synergism with other ENVISAT - 1 instruments</H2>
GOMOS and SCIAMACHY  both provide data which could complement those from MIPAS as they can cover other relevant species as well as providing different information on some of those observed by MIPAS.<P>

<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<H2><A NAME="dependance">Dependance on other data</A></H2>
MIPAS does not depend on other instruments to observe the spectra of chemical species in the middle atmosphere.<P>

<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<!--<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>-->
