<HEAD>
<TITLE>SCIAMACHY Y</TITLE>
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/icones/back8.gif">
<A NAME="TOP"></A>
<H1>SCIAMACHY - SCanning Imaging Absorption spectroMeter for Atmospheric CHartographY</H1>

<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>
<UL>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#description">Description and characteristics</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#synergism">Synergism with other ENVISAT - 1 instruments</A></B><P>
<IMG SRC="/images/ballroug.gif"><B> <A HREF="#dependance">Dependance on other data</A></B><P>
</UL><P>
<IMG SRC="/icones/line_fusee.gif"><BR>

<H2><A NAME="description">Description and characteristics</A></H2>

SCIAMACHY is intended to enhance our understanding of the composition, radiative balance and dynamics of the middle atmosphere (and possibly the upper troposphere). It will be capable of operating in either nadir or limb viewing modes and is intended to make observations in both the troposphere and the stratosphere. It is an evolution of the ERS - 2 GOME instrument.<P> 
It will operate in the UV, visible and near infrared regions of the spectrum, in principle being capable of observingthe following species H<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>O, O<MATH><SUB>3</SUB></MATH>, NO, NO<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH> , NO<MATH><SUB>3</SUB></MATH>,ClO, SO<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>,  CH<MATH><SUB>4</SUB></MATH>, BrO, OClO, HCHO, CO and CO<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH> plus temperature (O<MATH><SUB>2</SUB></MATH>)  and aerosol. To a certain extend, in its limb sounding mode, SCIAMACHY should complement GOMOS and MIPAS.<P> 
Its grating spectrometer should be capable of recording atmospheric spectra at fairly  high resolution (0.2 to 0.5 nm) over the spectral range 0.24 to 1.7 &#181;m (six overlapping channels) and selected spectral regions between 1 and 2.4 microns. In the limb scanning mode, it will cover altitudes from 20 to 100 km with an intended vertical resolution of 1 km. In the nadir viewing mode the cross track scan as at least &#177; 500 km to either side or nadir, and the minimum pixel exposure time across track correspond to 32 km. SCIAMACHY is intended to produce a continuous stream of data during daylight whatever used in nadir of limb sounding mode. SCIAMACHY will provide data not only of relevance to "chemical " investigations but also to radiative studies.<P>
 
<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<H2><A NAME="synergism">Synergism with other ENVISAT - 1 instruments</A></H2>
MIPAS and GOMOS both provides data which could complement that from SCIAMACHY as they can cover relevant species simultaneously at different times during the diurnal cycle. <P>

<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

<H2><A NAME="dependance">Dependance on other data</A></H2>
SCIAMACHY does not depend on other instruments to observe the spectra of chemical species in the middle atmosphere or nto monitor trends.<P>

<A HREF="#TOP"> Back to index </A><P>

