<P>
<H1>How to boost your own WWW site hits<BR>with The Shetland News</H1>

<HR>
</CENTER>

<P>


<P>
<CENTER><B> <U>Are your pages getting the hits they deserve?</U></B></CENTER>
<P>
 The Internet is like a dense forest, where readers can easily miss well-designed, attractive, fast-loading pages.
<P>
The Shetland News is a popular clearing in the cyberforest, where up  to 12,000 readers a day pass through. This figure is steadily rising.  We already have an annual hit rate in excess of 1.6 million. 
<P>
We are read every day in more than 55 countries, worldwide. A large  proportion of our readers are business computer users with relatively  high disposable incomes.
<P>
A sponsored link from The Shetland News, one of the UK's most  frequently visited sites, can help your pages make the breakthrough  from disappointing obscurity to popular success.
<P>
Our advertising rates are highly competitive and you can choose which  of our pages is most suited for the link to your target audience.
<P>
E-mail our <A HREF="mailto:sales@shetland-news.co.uk">sales representative</A> at (sales@shetland-news.co.uk) now or call John on  +44 (0)1595 692661, to discuss your requirements.
<P>

<P>

<P>
<CENTER><B> <U>Let us help you make your pages better</U></B></CENTER>
<P>

<P>
We also offer a commercial service advising clients how to improve  the quality and loading speed of their home pages, to maximise  returns from your investment in a presence on the Internet.
<P>

<P>

<P>

<P>
<CENTER><B> <U>No page of your own yet? We can make it happen!</U></B></CENTER>
<P>

<P>
If you don't yet have a home page of your own, The Shetland News is a  broker for Force 10 Photos, which produces some of the world's  fastest-loading and best-designed pages, at rates which will  pleasantly surprise you. 
<P>
E-mail <A HREF="mailto:force10.photos@zetnet.co.uk">Force 10 Photos</A> today for full details.
<P>
<I><CENTER><B> The Shetland News - where your customers really CAN see the wood for the trees.</B></CENTER></I>
