<H2 ALIGN=center>Brevin House, Levenwick, Shetland, UK</H2>

<I>Click on picture for bigger version</I>
<P>

<A HREF="brevinhouse.jpg"><IMG SRC="brevinhouses.jpg" ALIGN=left WIDTH=252 HEIGHT=189 HSPACE=10 VSPACE=5 BORDER=0></A>
<B>Former hotel converted into an impressive executive dwellinghouse, whilst still retaining enormous commercial potential.</B>
<P>
Situated on 1.5 acre site commanding superb views over Levenwick Bay, South Mainland, Shetland, UK. 
<p>
The property has been extensively upgraded throughout  to the highest specifications. Accomodation comprises: Hall, Cloakroom, 6 Bedrooms (4 <I>ensuite</I>), newly fitted Kitchen with integral fridge, oven & hob, Utility Room, Bathroom, Toilet, Diningroom with archway through to Lounge. <p>
Also self-contained flat, large garage, workshop, and a single garage. 
 
Garden includes large circular pond.
<p>
Most rooms enjoy a spectacular sea view. Double glazed, Oil-fired central heating. Parking for up to 25 cars. All carpets and curtains included in the price.
<P>
<B>Viewing highly recommended.</B>
