<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>The Shetland News - Wool pirates steal islands' good name
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/pics/parch.gif">
<center>
<IMG SRC="/pics/header.gif">
<BR>
<font size=-1>
<A HREF="/appeal.html">Help fight the legal battle for free WWW links</A>
</font>
<P>
<H1>Wool pirates steal islands' good name
</H1>
<H2></H2>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt6.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt7.gif">
<A HREF="http://www.zetnet.co.uk/ska/"><img src="/ska/ska.gif" hspace=5 border=0></A>
<img SRC="/pics/ftt9.gif">
<img SRC="/pics/ftt5.gif">
<HR>
</center>
<P>

<P>
10th January 1997
<P>
Knitwear pirates all over the world are still selling bogus Shetland  woollies, despite protests by islanders who manufacture the real thing.
<P>
Lorna Graham of <A HREF="http://www.zetnet.co.uk/skta/">Shetland Knitwear Trades Association</A> said yesterday  [THURS] it was proving 'almost impossible' to control abuse of the  islands' name and trademarks.
<P>
'Unfortunately, the word Shetland is now almost a generic term for  some kinds of wool and garments,' she said. 'An increasing number of  manufacturers claiming 100 per cent Shetland wool, pure Shetland and  real Shetland are appearing worldwide.'
<P>
A recent report to Shetland Islands Council's Knitwear Advisory Panel  suggested applying for European Union 'Leader' funding for a renewed  campaign to report fraudulent manufacturers to the trading standards  authorities in their own countries.
<P>
Complaints to the International Wool Secretariat had not led to any  action, the panel heard.
<P>
Frank Miller, managing director of Judane Ltd, Shetland's largest  knitwear manufacturer, said: 'Shetland has a strong case and I think  political lobbying would help.' He pointed to the example of  champagne, where French vintners in the Campagne region had achieved  trade mark protection.
<P>
Members of the panel agreed to pursue the matter and pointed out that   three-quarters of the Shetland wool clip comes from pure Shetland  sheep. Much of it is spun and knitted in the islands.
<P>



<P>
<BR clear=all>
<HR>

